title: walnut dream bars
directions: Cut the butter into 1 cup flour and 1/4 cup brown sugar until it resembles coarse meal.
Press this mixture firmly into ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes in a 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Mix taco seasoning, corn and beans with juice into hamburger.
Crush chips and place in bottom of a long casserole dish.
(Any amount you like.) Pour meat mixture over chips and bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle grated cheese over top of meat mixture and heat until cheese melts. Serve with sour cream and mild taco sauce.

title: spicy ginger chicken
directions: Season chicken with salt and pepper.
Combine barbecue sauce, juice, sugar and ginger.
Place chicken in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chicken is fork-tender, brushing occasionally with sauce mix last 15 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli curry
directions: Simmer or bake chicken breasts or cook in microwave.
Cook packages of broccoli; drain.
Place broccoli in baking dish; place chicken over broccoli.
Mix soup, mayonnaise and curry together and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle butter and bread crumb mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
During last 10 minutes, cover with grated cheese.

title: dirt cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Cool.
Prepare pudding mix as directed on package.
Fold Cool Whip into prepared pudding mix.
After cake has cooled, break into bite size pieces. Put a layer (half of cake) into large bowl and cover with half of pudding mix.
Repeat and top with sprinkles of cake crumbs, a spoonful of Cool Whip and a maraschino cherry.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients and 1/2 cup of the blueberries, then add the milk.
Add vanilla and 1 1/2 cup blueberries.

title: pancakes
directions: Stir lightly; do not overstir.
Fry in Crisco oil until golden brown.

title: sugar "n" spice coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease two 8-inch square cake pans. Combine sugar, pecans, cinnamon and cereal.
Set aside.
Prepare cake mix using water required on box.
Add sour cream and eggs. Place 1/4 of batter in bottom of each pan; cover batter in each pan with 3/4 cup cereal mixture.
Divide remaining batter between cake pans.
To remaining cereal mixture, stir in butter.
Spread over cake batter.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: sour cream(low calorie)
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend at high speed.

title: festive 3 c bread
directions: Stir together thoroughly the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Combine eggs, oil and milk, then add this to the flour mixture and stir until blended.
Stir in carrots, coconut, cherries, raisins and pecans.
Turn into four well-greased and floured 16 ounce fruit or vegetable cans.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Remove from cans and allow to completely cool. Store wrapped in foil; refrigerate.

title: caramel apple fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, place in large bowl and mix in peanuts, chopped up red and green apples, chopped up snickers candy bar, marshmallows and add cool whip.
Once mixed well, refrigerate for 1 hour or until ready to serve.

title: orange dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill overnight.

title: old fashioned baked beans
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Cook 1 hour in plenty of water and salt. Drain.
Place in old fashion crockery bean pot and pour remaining ingredients over beans.
Place bacon strips on top.
Add about 2 inches water over all.
Bake 7 1/2 to 8 hours in oven at 275° to 300°.
Never stir beans.

title: grilled chicken with apricot glaze
directions: Cut chicken breasts into thin strips.
Skewer onto long bamboo skewers and grill or bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Heat spinach as directed on package.
Add beef bouillon to drained spinach.
Add next 5 ingredients.
While still warm, add water chestnuts.
Put in baking dish.
Cover, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: 15 minute chili
directions: Cook ground beef until no red appears.
Add all ingredients and cook until heated through.

title: fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk to soft ball stage or 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and add Hershey bars, chocolate chips, marshmallow cream, nuts and vanilla.
Press into a greased jelly roll pan. Cut into squares after cooling.

title: lentil and barley soup
directions: Melt butter; cook onion and celery.
Add tomatoes, water, lentils and barley (salt and pepper to taste).
Cover tightly and boil gently for 45 minutes.
Stir often.
Add carrots and cook 5 minutes more.
If thinner stew is desired, add 1 cup of water.

title: bread custard (or pudding)
directions: Pour milk over crumbled bread. Set aside to soak. Mix sugar, cornstarch, eggs, vanilla and salt thoroughly. Pour over crumbs and lightly sprinkle with cinnamon. Beat until foamy.

title: spice pound cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar and oil well.
Add vanilla and plums (or prunes).
Mix together flour, cinnamon and cloves.
Add to mixture and cream well.
Bake in Bundt or angel food pan in 325° oven for 60 minutes.
Cool thoroughly before removing cake from pan. Powdered sugar may be sprinkled on cooled cake.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together and let set overnight in refrigerator.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix like biscuits.
Work in flour until dough is stiff.
The more flour you use, the crisper the tea cakes will be.
Roll out dough, cut out and bake at 350 degrees, about 12 minutes.

title: old fashion tea cakes
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add plain flour, soda, vanilla and lemon flavoring.
Chill dough overnight or put in rolls and freeze.
You can just take out and slice as needed.
Bake at 325° until lightly brown.
Do not overcook.

title: wildfire rye bread(so named because it disappears so fast)
directions: In large bowl combine 1 1/4 cups whole wheat flour, 1 1/4 cups rye flour, yeast, orange rind, fennel, anise and salt; mix well. Heat buttermilk, molasses, water and oil until very warm (120° to 130°).
Add to flour mixture.
Stir until moistened.
Gradually stir in remaining rye and whole wheat flours and enough all-purpose flour to make a firm dough.
Knead on floured surface about 5 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise until double, 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Punch down dough. Divide.
Shape into 2 long loaves and place on greased cookie sheets sprinkled with cornmeal.
Cover and let rise until doubled, about 30 minutes.
With very sharp knife make 5 diagonal slashes across top of loaves.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes, until loaves sound hollow when tapped.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut corn kernels and scrape milk from cobs.
Melt fats in heavy iron skillet.
Add corn and seasonings.
Stir constantly as it cooks.
Use low heat and cook until it is thick and tender, about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: delicious salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate until served.

title: one pot pasta
directions: Bring to boil, tomatoes, chicken broth, oil and seasoning. Add spiral pasta.
Cover and simmer 16 to 18 minutes.
Stir twice.

title: tiramisu (from northern italy)("lift me up")
directions: Chop chocolate coarsely.
Arrange half of the ladyfingers in one layer on a rectangular serving dish with sides at least 2 inches high.
Lightly soak them with some of the cold coffee. Beat the egg yolks together with the sugar until creamy color. Add the Ricotta and mix gently.
In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold whites into the the egg-cheese mixture. Layer half of this mixture on the ladyfingers.
Sprinkle half of the chopped chocolate.
Repeat with a second layer of soaked ladyfingers, the remaining cheese mixture and the chopped chocolate.
Cover with foil and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate caramel apples
directions: In top of double boiler over hot water, heat chocolate caramel candy salt and water, stirring frequently, until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Keeping sauce over hot water, place each apple in hot caramel sauce.
Spoon sauce over apple until it is completely coated.
Insert wooden skewer in stem end.
Remove from sauce and place on waxed paper.
Chill until caramel coating is firm.

title: eggplant and sausage casserole
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch pieces.
Cook until done in frypan. Cut eggplant into 1/2-inch pieces.
Add onion, eggplant and garlic to sausage skillet; cook 5 minutes.
Stir in paprika; cook 2 minutes more.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, basil and 1 teaspoon salt to eggplant mixture; bring to boil.
Reduce heat, partially cover pot and simmer 35 minutes, or until thick.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring 4 quarts water to boil.
Add pasta for 10 minutes. Drain; stir into sauce.
Spread 1/2 of eggplant-pasta mixture into 2 1/2-quart dish.
Top with Ricotta cheese; sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Top with eggplant and pasta mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in saucepan.
Cook until it begins to thicken (about 30 minutes).
Add cooked beef, pork or chicken and simmer at least 15 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Add soup and tuna and stir.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix the 3 ingredients and drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet.
Press down with fork.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Cookies will seem soft when they first come out of the oven, but after they cool they tend to be a little crisp.
Do not overcook.

title: clam dip
directions: Drain clams, but keep the juice.
Combine the cream cheese, onion and clams.
Mix well.
Add clam juice a little at a time until desired thickness.
Serve with corn chips.

title: oven baked shrimp stroganoff
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside. Combine sour cream, soup and dill weed in a large bowl, mixing well. Add onion, olives, 1/2 cup cheese and shrimp; Stir well.
Stir in noodles.
Spoon mixture into a lightly greased shallow 2 quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup cheese.
Bake an additional 5 minutes or until the cheese melts.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: butter cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: beef horseradish spread
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate. Serve with crackers.

title: cereal peanut butter bars
directions: Combine sugar and corn syrup in saucepan and bring to boil. Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Pour over cereal in a bowl and mix well.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Let cool.
Cut into 2 x 1-inch bars.
Makes about 32.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cover pan on the bottom with a thin layer of meat.
Slice potatoes, then carrots and onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Put layer of meat, then put tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° until potatoes and carrots are cooked, at least 1 hour.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Put chicken in large pot filled about 3/4 full of water.
Cook until tender.
Remove chicken and debone.
Add remaining ingredients, except tortillas, back into boiling water.
Cut flour tortillas in strips and drop in boiling broth (do not use corn tortillas).
Cook about 20 minutes or so until done. this makes a large quantity, so it can be halved if you desire.

title: banana cooler
directions: Peel and mash the bananas.
Put the bananas in a big pitcher. Add the buttermilk and ice cubes.
Stir well.
Pour into tall glasses and serve with long spoons.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Even better the next day.

title: feta cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients except parsley and shape into ball. Wrap in plastic wrap, then in foil and refrigerate several hours or overnight.

title: quick applesauce crunch
directions: Mix cinnamon and nutmeg with applesauce and put in pie pan.

title: pecan kisses
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar together.
Add nuts and stir well. Spread on cookie sheet and bake in preheated oven at 250° for 30 minutes.
Turn off oven and leave kisses in for another 30 minutes.

title: cherry pecan logs
directions: Fondant Base:
Combine 2 tablespoons evaporated milk and rum flavoring in mixing bowl; stir in sugar until blended.
Knead until smooth and shiny, to make logs.

title: cocoa fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa and salt in a heavy saucepan.
Add milk and bring to a boil, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Do not stir again.
Cook to soft ball stage.
Add butter and place pan in cold water.
Add vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Put into buttered pan.

title: walking tacos
directions: Fry beef with taco seasoning; cook until liquid is reduced. Place meat in a large pan or casserole dish.
Layer refried beans on top of meat.
Layer on onion, chilies, olives and tomato.
Pour salsa over top, then sour cream and guacamole dip.
Top with cheese.
Put in oven until cheese melts.

title: aunt fanny's baked squash
directions: Wash and cut up squash.
Boil until tender.
Drain, then mash. Add rest of ingredients except 1/2 of butter.
Melt remaining butter.
Pour mix into baking dish, then spread melted butter over top and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: barbecue relish
directions: Mix and seal at once cold.

title: jean's sandwich
directions: Split bread and dig out center; put on meat, cheese and sauce. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Slice with electric knife.

title: hawaiian chess pie
directions: Combine eggs, milk, sugar, flour, lemon juice and margarine. Beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and coconut.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes, or until center of pie is set.
Cool and serve.

title: moon cake
directions: Boil water and butter.
Remove from heat.
Stir in flour. Beat in eggs, one at a time, in flour mixture.
Spread thin on jelly roll sheet (10 x 15-inch) pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Cool 30 minutes.

title: coconut cake
directions: Cook about 15 minutes.
Pour over cake while both are hot. Let cool completely.
Then cover cake with 8 ounces of Cool Whip and sprinkle another 6 ounce package of frozen coconut on top. Keep cake refrigerated.

title: plain cornbread(pone)
directions: Use enough boiling water just to moisten the cornmeal.
Coat a heavy skillet with oil. Shape pones 1/2 inch thick.
Place in covered skillet, over medium flame and brown both sides. Very good with beans, greens and sliced onion.

title: nonfat apple raisin pancakes
directions: In bowl, beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, flour, baking powder, baking soda, applesauce and cinnamon.
Mix thoroughly.
Add remaining ingredients and mix just until moistened.

title: baked chicken with mushrooms and artichokes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Season chicken with salt and pepper. Place skin side up in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Drain artichokes, reserving liquid.
Cut artichokes in half and place on chicken with mushrooms and green onions.
Pour reserved marinade and white wine over chicken.
Bake until done.
Serves 4.

title: rice pilaf
directions: Lightly brown egg noodles in butter.
Add uncooked rice, chicken broth and salt if desired.
Simmer until cooked (about 20 minutes).

title: fudge
directions: Mix cocoa, sugar, salt and milk in saucepan.
Bring to a hard boil stirring constantly.
Turn down heat to low and continue to cook until it forms a ball in cold water or 234° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Mix well and transfer to platter.
Let cool and cut.

title: dilled summer squash
directions: Cook squash
in
water with onion, dill seed and pepper 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain and dot with margarine.

title: batter dipped fish
directions: Heat oil in deep pan to about 400°.
Cut fish into 7 x 2-inch wedges.
With mixer, blend flour, water, egg, sugar and salt.
Dip fish into batter, coating well.
Quickly drop into oil.
Fry each fillet until dark golden brown, about 5 minutes.
Drain on metal rack or paper towels.

title: cream cheese squares
directions: Cream butter or margarine, brown sugar and flour.
Add 1/2 cup nuts.
Reserve 1 cup of mixture for topping.
Pack remainder firmly into ungreased 8 x 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Blend 1/4 cup sugar, lemon juice and cream cheese together.
Beat together egg, milk and vanilla.
Blend together. Pour this over baked base; crumble cup of topping over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: curried baked cauliflower
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix bread crumbs and butter together. Break cauliflower into flowerets; cook 10 minutes in boiling water.
Drain.
Stir together soup, cheese, mayo and curry powder. Add cauliflower.
Mix well; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake until tender about 20 minutes.

title: easy cucumber salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 8 hours, but no longer than 24 hours.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Spray 6-cup fluted cake pan with nonstick cooking spray.
In large mixing bowl, beat sugar and oleo until smooth and fluffy. Beat in sour cream, egg whites, lemon rind and lemon juice until smooth.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt and add to batter.
Mix until smooth, about 1 minute.

title: broccoli bake
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add 1/2 stick butter and 1/2 pound cheese.
Let melt.
Put in an 8 x 8-inch buttered dish. Crush crackers.
Mix with 1/2 stick butter which has been melted. Sprinkle over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Preparation time:
20 minutes.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop cranberries coarse.
Chop unpeeled apples that have been cored into small pieces.
Remove seed and part of peel from oranges and chop them into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients together.
Freezes well.

title: chili dip
directions: Spread cream cheese in bottom of glass dish.
Layer chili over cream cheese, then grated cheese over that.
Microwave 4 minutes on High or until cheese is completely melted.
Serve immediately using scoopers.

title: mocha spice cake
directions: Mix flour, soda, cinnamon, baking powder and salt.
Combine sour cream, water, coffee and vanilla.
Cream butter.
Gradually beat in sugar; beat until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Blend in chocolate. Alternately add flour and sour cream mixtures; beat after each addition until smooth.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.

title: finger paint
directions: Dissolve the starch in a small amount of cold water, to make paste.
Then add the boiling water.
Cook the mixture until it becomes clear, stirring constantly.
Remove the pan from the stove and add the soap flakes.
Stir until the flakes are dissolved. Pour some of the mixture into as many jars as you want colors. Add food coloring to the mixture in each jar to make the colors you want.

title: cherry-nut angel food cake
directions: Make batter for angel food cake as directed, except at the last, fold in 1/2 cup chopped maraschino cherries, drained on paper towel and 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake as directed.
Cool. Frost with cherry fluffy-type frosting mix.

title: snowball cake
directions: Dissolve gelatin in cold water, then add boiling water.
Cool slightly.
Stir in pineapple, juices and sugar.
Chill until mixture sets slightly.
Prepare 1 envelope of Dream Whip.
Fold into gelatin mixture.
Break cake into small pieces into 2 x 10 x 13-inch dish.
Pour gelatin over cake, guiding around pieces. Chill overnight.

title: mexican spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet over medium heat, saute onion and garlic in 1/4 cup chicken broth, about 5 minutes.
Add chicken broth and whole tomatoes with juice.
Add spaghetti to the tomato mixture. Break up tomatoes with spoon.
Add picante sauce and cumin. Simmer covered until spaghetti is cooked and most liquid is absorbed.
Add chicken and spoon into casserole dish sprayed with cooking spray.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake covered at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a Dutch oven. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes. Strain, discarding fruit and cinnamon sticks. Serve hot.

title: punch
directions: Chop up sherbet in punch bowl with ginger ale and jello.

title: corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan; blend in flour, salt and sugar. Stir until smooth.
(Do not brown.)
Add milk; cook until thick. Stir in corn and eggs.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Set dish in a pan containing about 1 inch water.
Bake at 350° until set, about 45 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add cocoa.
Add flour and eggs alternately.
Add salt and vanilla.
Stir in pecans.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Bake in tube pan.
Do not overcook.

title: baked squash casserole
directions: Slice squash in 1/2-inch pieces. Boil for 3 minutes or until tender. Drain; add onion, eggs and seasonings. Mix until well blended. Pour into 1-quart
buttered casserole dish. Mix butter and crumbs; sprinkle over squash. Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 40 minutes until browned. Makes 6 servings.

title: sweetened sauerkraut salad
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar and oil. Stir until dissolved.
Add rest of ingredients.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
This can be added to hot dogs or bratwurst on buns.

title: butterscotch bars
directions: Cook oleo and sugar over low heat until bubbly.
Remove from heat and cool.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add vanilla, then the sifted dry ingredients, coconut and nuts; mix thoroughly.
Spread on greased 9 x 13-inch baking sheet; bake in moderate oven for about 25 minutes.
While warm, cut into squares.
Do not overbake.

title: herb and garlic fish
directions: Mix dressing and seasonings.
Place fish on greased grill over medium coals or rack of broiler pan 2 to 4 inches from heat. Brush with 1/2 of the dressing mixture.
Grill or broil 5 to 8 minutes. Turn, brush with remaining dressing mixture. Continue grilling or broiling 5 to 8 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix
pudding as directed on package.
Add pineapple and marshmallows.
Add
half
of
nuts and half of Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Spread rest of Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with nuts.

title: noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Cook noodles in separate pan; drain. Add cheese, milk, soup, noodles and corn.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer until ingredients are well blended and heated thoroughly.
Serves 6.

title: tennessee sin
directions: Slice off top fourth of 1 loaf bread and hollow out bottom leaving 1 inch shell.
Cut bread loaf into 1 inch cubes.
Place bread and shell on baking sheet and bake for 350° for 12 minutes. Beat cream cheese at medium speed until smooth add sour cream beating until creamy.
Stir in cheddar cheese and next 4 ingredients.
Spoon into shell, wrap with foil and place on baking sheet.
Bake 305° for 30 minutes. unwrap and place on serving platter.
Sprinkle with paprika and serve with toasted bread cubes.

title: mama's meat loaf
directions: Mix ingredients in small pan.
Cover with leftover tomato sauce.

title: broccoli
directions: Cut off tough parts of stalk and leaves.
If stalks are large, cut in strips.
Cook in boiling, salted water until tender. Serve with melted butter or cheese.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk; bring to boil.
Stir constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat.
Stir.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate pieces until melted.
Add Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour on buttered pan.

title: refrigerator pie
directions: Mix sugar, juice, lemon jello and eggs.
Cook to boiling point.
Let cool.
Whip cream and add to other ingredients.
Pour into 2 graham crusts and chill.
Mix strawberry (or cherry) jello according to package directions.
Let set partly, then cover top of pies.
Chill until firm.
Makes 2 large pies.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Mix in pot and boil until thickened.
Cool.
Put berries in baking pan and drop dough by spoon over berries.
Bake for 20 minutes at 400°.

title: pink party squares
directions: Mix well and put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine 4 cups coconut and 1 can condensed milk.
Put on top of mixture and bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cover with pink frosting while still warm.
Put frosting in strips on top of squares.

title: grandma sally delong's sweet potato custard
directions: Cook 8 medium sweet potatoes in 2 cups water.
Pour off water. Let cool
and peel.
Add to potatoes 1 1/2 cups sugar, 3 whole eggs
and
dash
of salt, cinnamon, ginger and nutmeg. Stir thoroughly.
Add vanilla flavoring.
Add enough hot water until consistency
is
smooth.
Pour
into 2 (9-inch) uncooked pie shells;
bake
at 350° until golden brown.
Recipe is over 100 years old.

title: heath toffee pots decreme
directions: In heavy saucepan melt chocolate chips and unsweetened chocolate with cream over low heat, stirring frequently.
Stir 1/4 cup chocolate mixture into the egg yolks.
Then quickly stir yolk mixture back into saucepan.
Cook and stir for two minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in Kahlua or coffee.
Cool to room temperature. Stir in Heath bits.
Carefully fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into small dessert cups.
Cover with plastic wrap and chill.
Just before serving, garnish with additional Heath bits.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Wash rice.
Let it come to a boil.
Drain and cool.
Saute onion in bacon fat.
Add to meat, rice, egg, salt and pepper.
Cut cabbage core head out.
Boil until leaves are tender.
Take leaves. Cut the rib from cabbage leaf and fill with meat.
The bottom of the cabbage which you can't use to make a cabbage roll, cut up and mix with sauerkraut.
If you do not like sauerkraut, omit.
Put some cabbage on the bottom and cabbage rolls on top.
Finish with cabbage and kraut.
Pour tomato soup and water to fill the rolls. Salt and pepper.
Cook slowly 1 1/4 hours.

title: meatballs and gravy
directions: Place ground beef in large bowl.
Add all seasonings.
Add remaining ingredients, except oil, flour, water and milk and mix well.
Take small portions of the mixture and form meatballs. Shape to size preferred.

title: butternut surprise
directions: Bake cake mix according to directions.	Cool.
Cut cake lengthwise	with
a
piece	of
thread
or	dental floss.
Mix pudding with milk and spread 1/2 of pudding on bottom layer of cake.
Add	3 candy bars (broken in small pieces).	Add 1/2 of Cool Whip.	Add
top
layer of cake, rest of pudding and candy bars and top with Cool Whip.
Must cover and keep cool.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix chopped chicken breasts, soup and sour cream.
Add salt as desired.
Add cracker crumbs to melted oleo and poppy seeds and mix.
Top chicken mixture with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put on rye bread for a party sandwich or use as a dip.

title: spiced apple sweet potatoes
directions: Cut two 18-inch square pieces of foil.
Place half of the sweet potatoes on each.
In a bowl, stir together the apple butter, brown sugar, water and cinnamon.
Spoon over potatoes. Dot with butter.
Fold in sides of foil and seal well.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Or can heat in barbecue.

title: quick lime cream pie
directions: In a medium bowl, stir together sweetened condensed milk and ReaLime.
Fold in whipped cream; pour into crust.
Chill 3 hours, or until set.
Garnish as desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: chocolate pudding layer cake
directions: Mix together flour, butter, salt and nuts.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: homemade noodles and pasta dough(serves 5)
directions: Pour the flour into a large mixing bowl.
Beat the eggs together with the remaining ingredients.
Make a well in the center of the flour and pour in the liquid mixture.
Work the mixture together to form a smooth, stiff dough.
Knead it until smooth, with lightly floured hands, in a bowl or a lightly floured surface.
The dough must be smooth and not one bit sticky, but don't overdo it on the flour or the dough will crumble.
Wrap the dough in a plastic food bag and leave at room temperature for about 30 minutes.

title: rhubarb pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, flour and salt.
Add rhubarb and mix well.
Arrange in pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Top with pastry strips to form a star design.
Bake in very hot oven (450°) for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: baked steak
directions: Arrange a sheet of foil on a shallow pan. Using 1/2 of the oleo, cut in pieces on foil. Place half the onion soup over this. Place steak on top of this. Then the rest of oleo and soup over steak. Lastly, cover mushrooms over all. Fold foil around meat to seal. Bake about 2 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: pork sausage and egg casserole
directions: Put sausage in bottom of 9 X 13 dish.
Cover with bread cubes then adding cheese.
Mix together eggs and milk and pour over cheese, bread and sausage.
Can be frozen at this point.
Bake at 350 for 35 minutes.
If frozen put into 350 oven for 1 hour.
Great for large family gatherings.

title: glazed strawberry pie(from national square dance cookbook, 1976)
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and 1 pint strawberries in saucepan. Cook on low heat and stir until sauce is thick and smooth.
Remove from heat; add lemon juice and food coloring.
Cool.
Sprinkle confectioners sugar over bottom of pie crust.
Fill with remaining box of berries.
Spoon cooked, cooled sauce over berries.
Chill about 4 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: supper vegetable meal
directions: Cook in peanut oil in a wok the onions, garlic and green pepper for a few minutes until it begins to brown.
Then add the sliced zucchini and corn pieces and sprinkle with vegetable seasoning salt.
As this is cooking, slice the tomatoes and add them.
Then add about a cup or so of water and steam on low heat, covered, in the wok for about 30 minutes.
The corn and zucchini absorb the delicious taste of the onions, garlic and green peppers.
Must use all fresh vegetables for this dish.

title: artichoke hot dip
directions: Mix together and bake 30 minutes.
Serve with chips.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Eject yolk from boiled eggs (after cutting yolks in 1/2).
Mix yolks with mayonnaise and relish.
Mix sugar with mustard and vinegar.
Pour into previous mixture.
Put egg yolk mixture back into half egg whites.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: butterballs
directions: Mix butter, sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Stir in flour and salt at once.
Mix in nuts.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until set, but not brown at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
When cold, roll again in sugar.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix buttermilk, oil, soda, eggs and sugar.
Mix well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° in muffin pan in bake cups. Bake about 12 to 15 minutes.
Place the mixture in an airtight container; use as needed.
Keep in refrigerator until you use it.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill well.
Serve with raw vegetables.

title: sicilian meat roll
directions: Combine eggs, bread crumbs, tomato sauce, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper and garlic in ground beef, mixing well.
On waxed paper or foil, pat meat out to a 12 x 10-inch rectangle.
Arrange ham slices, leaving a small margin around edge.
Roll up the ground meat; seal the edges.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.

title: spicy beef spread
directions: Brown hamburger, drain. Brown sausage, drain.
Add rest of ingredients while meat is hot. Put small amount on bread and freeze 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: brownie's pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt well, then cut in Crisco until real crumbly.
Add water, all at once.
Stir with a fork until just mixed (not as much as biscuit dough).
Divide in half for a two crust pie.
Will roll out easier if you chill the two rolls (wrapped in wax paper).
Take out 1 roll at a time.
Use little flour on board.
Flour one side, then turn over before rolling. Lift rolling pin (don't roll back and forth).
Turn crust around so you roll all edges.
Some flours have to have more water, almost a drop at a time.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all except dressing and chips; later add dressing and chips when ready to eat.
I sometimes add browned ground beef.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook, drain and squeeze dry the spinach.
Mix all ingredients together with the spinach.
Form into bite size balls.
Freeze on cookie sheets.
When almost frozen can be stored in plastic bags in freezer.
Cook from freezer, 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into 2 balls. Roll in chopped walnuts.

title: sopapilla cheesecake
directions: Spray 9X13 inch pan with cooking spray. Spread one can crescent rolls in bottom of pan. Mix together cream cheese, sugar and vanilla; spread on top of crescent rolls. Pour melted butter over top. Cover with remaining can of crescent rolls. Sprinkle with topping (below). Bake at 350 for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy toffee bars
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line a 13 x 9-inch pan with foil.
Grease foil with butter. Arrange crackers in prepared pan so that entire bottom is covered.
In medium saucepan, combine brown sugar and butter. Bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Pour over crackers. Bake at 400° for 5 minutes. Remove from oven.
Immediately sprinkle with chocolate chips.
When chips are soft, spread over top.
Sprinkle with nuts. Chill about 30 minutes until chocolate is set.
Cut into bars or small pieces. Store in refrigerator.

title: baked chicken(meal in a pan)
directions: Clean chicken; take neck and parts and 1 onion to make broth. While preparing rest, salt and pepper to taste.
Take chunked potatoes, apples and onions and layer in roasting pan.
Take spices and mix.
Coat whole chicken.
Place orange peel inside chicken.

title: banana ice cream
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Beat eggs until frothy. Combine sugar mixture, beaten eggs and remainder of ingredients. Beat until creamy.
Pour into freezer and finish filling freezer with milk.
Freeze according to freezer manufacturer's directions. Yields approximately 1 gallon.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Crush crackers into fine crumbs, then using whole stick butter, saute crumbs until brown.
Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Drain.
In 9 x 9-inch casserole dish, layer half the broccoli, then layer of cheese, then layer half the crumbs.
Repeat the order again.
Bake at 350° for about 30 to 45 minutes.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Cream the softened margarine, brown sugar and egg by hand. Add flour, baking powder, vanilla, nuts and butterscotch morsels. Mix thoroughly.
Spread in greased 9 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: jack liem's relish
directions: Grind all vegetables; put in pan and sprinkle salt over vegetables.
Let this stand overnight.
Next day, rinse well and drain.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill several hours or overnight before serving.

title: punch
directions: This makes 40 small cups.
Make recipe 3 times to serve between 100 and 110.

title: almond joy cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Pour cake into a large sheet cake pan; bake at 350° until toothpick inserted comes out clean.
While cake is baking, melt marshmallows mixed with evaporated milk and sugar; add coconut.
When cake is done, punch holes in hot cake with wooden spoon handle; pour coconut mixture over cake.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine at medium speed of an electric mixer until combined.
Gradually add Egg Beaters and beat well.
Combine sour cream and baking soda.
Stir well and set aside.
Combine flour and salt; with mixer at low speed, add to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream mixture, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Spoon batter into a 10-inch tube pan coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 35 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 minutes; remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 24 servings (1-inch slices).

title: cinnamon logs
directions: Cook first four ingredients to soft ball stage, stirring well. Then take off heat. Add butter and vanilla.
Let cool and set aside until cool enough to touch (set pan in sink of cold water). Beat until gloss is gone.
Take wax paper.
Put cinnamon on it. Then roll in cinnamon (roll into long logs, then cut in 1 1/2-inch logs each).

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: rye bread dip
directions: Mix and let sit overnight; slice lengthwise a whole loaf of rye bread and hollow out.
Cut bread into bite-size pieces; fill remaining bread cavity with mixture.

title: lemon cheese squares
directions: Mix together cake mix, margarine and 1 egg in large bowl, using mixer until crumbly.
Press onto bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.
In medium bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth and fluffy.
Mix in remaining 2 eggs, granulated sugar, vanilla and lemon juice until blended.
Pour over crust.
Bake 25 minutes until top edges are golden brown. Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add bacon grease, corn and buttermilk. Add pepperoni, jalapeno pepper and onion.
Beat eggs slightly and add to mixture.
Put 1/2 of mixture into well greased pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 cheese.
Pour the remaining mixture in pan and remaining cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Place butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan in warm oven just to melt. Beat eggs in large bowl.
Mix in flour, baking powder and salt. Squeeze thawed spinach very dry and add to egg mixture along with the melted butter and cheeses.
Pour into pan and bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake an additional 35 to 40 minutes.
Let stand for 15 minutes to set.
Cut into 60 squares for hors d'oeuvres.

title: tabbouli salad
directions: Mix and chill at least 2 hours.

title: baked eggplant
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread each side eggplant slices with mayonnaise, coat with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and arrange 1 inch apart on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.
Turn and bake until browned on second side. Serve immediately.

title: oatmeal drop cookies chocolate
directions: Heat sugar, butter, cocoa and milk together until boils. Boil for 3.5 minutes. Remove from heat. Add 2 cups oats, peanut butter and vanilla. Stir well. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.

title: sparkle punch
directions: Dissolve drink mix in water in punch bowl or pitcher. Refrigerate. Just before serving, stir in ginger ale. Serve in punch cups and top each serving with small scoop of sherbet.

title: easy strawberry jello pie
directions: Bring water to boiling point.
Stir sugar and cornstarch together.
Put into boiling water and cook until mixture clears. Take off stove and add strawberry Jell-O.
It will begin to thicken.
Use 1 quart strawberries and stir berries into Jell-O mixture.
Put this into 2 baked pie shells or 2 graham cracker crumbs.
When cool serve with Cool Whip.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Dissolve cherry and lemon Jell-O and sugar in 3 cups boiling water.
Add lemon juice and pineapple; chill until gelatin mixture is partially set.
Fold in cranberries, orange, celery and walnuts.
Pour gelatin mixture into 8 1/2 cup mold.
Chill until firm.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: meal-in-a-pan
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
In skillet add hot shortening, ground beef, onion, tomatoes, beans and seasonings.
Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Keep stirring.

title: fruit salad
directions: In large bowl combine all of the fruit and nuts.
Mix well. Choose the dressing of your choice and mix enough to cover fruit. Chill and serve.

title: coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan. Combine all ingredients, except streusel topping.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Sprinkle with
Streusel Topping.
Make indentations in the batter with finger so topping will bake into cake.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vegetable noodle salad
directions: Boil noodles, drain and chill. Drain corn and peas. Combine noodles, corn and peas. Add Miracle Whip to desired consistency.

title: cowboy bread
directions: Blend flour, sugar, salt, oleo, cinnamon and nutmeg until crumb like mixture forms.
Save 1/2 cup mixture for topping.
To remaining mixture, add baking powder and soda.
Mix thoroughly. Add buttermilk and eggs.
Mix until smooth.
Pour batter into greased and
floured pan (11 x 15-inch).
Sprinkle crumb like mixture on top.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: stuffed spaghetti squash
directions: Brown ground meat and well chopped seasonings.
Cut squash in half lengthwise and scoop out seeds; place squash cut side down in a large covered saucepan with 1 quart water.
Boil for about 30 minutes.
When cool enough to handle, scoop out inside, being careful not to mash pulp.
Mix pulp with meat seasoning, rice, cheese and soup.
Fill squash shells with stuffing.
Sprinkle bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese on top and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: ham and broccoli casserole
directions: Partially cook broccoli then lay in baking dish.
Sprinkle ham over.
Combine soup and mayonnaise then pour over ham and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with bread crumbs mix with olive oil.	Bake 350 degrees 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Combine.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours.

title: jarrell and katrell's favorite bacon bean bake
directions: In large frypan, cook bacon for 15 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cook onion and green pepper in bacon drippings for 3 to 4 minutes. Add chopped bacon and remaining ingredients.
Heat, covered, on low heat for 1 hour.
Remove cover.
Stir and continue heating, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate balls
directions: Crush crackers fine.
Add cocoa.
Mix in condensed milk.
Add melted margarine.
Roll into balls and roll into coconut or nuts. Place on a tray in refrigerator until set.

title: spicy crab spread
directions: Remove cartilage from crabmeat.
Mix together cheese, onion and soy sauce.
Place in a serving dish and flatten to 1/4 inch. Spread crabmeat over cheese mixture, cover and refrigerate one hour or more.
Before serving, top with cocktail sauce.
Serve with crackers.

title: baked chicken
directions: Place chicken in greased baking dish.
Pour melted margarine over chicken.
Mix celery soup, milk and onion soup and pour over chicken.
Then pour wine over top.
Bake, covered with foil, for about 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Last 15 minutes, uncover chicken to brown.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl cream together cheese, butter and sugar. Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and alternate with milk.
Pour batter into a bundt cake pan.
Bake at 300° for one hour and forty-five minutes to two hours.

title: homemade pot pie
directions: Mix well and put in a 9-inch pie crust.
Put top crust on. Beat 1 egg and drizzle over top.
Make 4 slits in top crust.
Bake for 375° for 40 minutes.

title: white on white cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Drop in Spry.
Add 2/3 of milk, then flavorings and beat.
Add egg whites and remaining milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes for 2 (8-inch) round pans and 15 to 20 minutes for cupcakes.

title: barbecued rice
directions: Melt margarine in heavy skillet.
Add celery and onion and cook until tender.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil. Pour into a casserole dish and bake in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave on High for 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes. Stir in nuts and spread in pan to cool.

title: buffalo chip cookies
directions: Mix butter, brown sugar, sugar and eggs in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Form into large 1/4 cup mounds on cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes in preheated oven.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: fisherman fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light.
Add egg yolks and beat. Sift flour and salt.
Add alternately with milk.
Add melted chocolate, then nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan for 1 hour.
Frost with favorite chocolate icing. Nuts added makes it a tasty treat.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Cover; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Uncover and broil until brown.
Let cool.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: In
large
bowl combine sugar, peanut butter and butter until moist.
Add
vanilla.
Work
mixture until it will roll into
very firm one-inch balls.
Melt chocolate bark in double boiler.
Pour melted bark into deep cup.	Using toothpicks dip peanut
butter balls
into
hot
chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper to cool.

title: banana nut cake(low-fat diabetic recipe)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 13-inch pan with nonstick spray.
Cream the sugar and margarine.
Add bananas, egg substitute and milk, mixing well.
Mix together the flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Pour into wet ingredients, mixing until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into pan. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 16.

title: banana pudding
directions: In a 13
x 9-inch dish, layer bananas and wafers. Blend together pudding mix
and
milk, then add Eagle Brand and Cool Whip and spoon
evenly
over
banana and wafer mixture.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: orange cake
directions: Blend all together and bake in 2 nine inch pans at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: pdq pickles
directions: Tie pickling spice in cheesecloth.
In saucepan, combine pickling spice bag, vinegar, sugar, salt and turmeric.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and pour over vegetables.
Cool to room temperature.
Store in covered container in refrigerator.
Remove spice bag before serving.
Makes 4 cups.

title: peanut butter cup cookies
directions: Cream the sugars, Crisco, peanut butter, egg, milk and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Roll into balls and roll in sugar. Put into a mini muffin pan and bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.
When they are done, press a miniature Reese's cup into each one.

title: belgian waffle cookies
directions: Soften butter in a mixing bowl.
Add brown and white sugar and mix until smooth.
Slowly add the eggs, one at a time, until combined.
Sift all other ingredients together and add to butter and egg mixture.
Mix until smooth and cool in refrigerator for two hours.
Place 2 ounces of mix in the center of a preheated Belgian waffle iron or machine.
Close lid and cook until dough comes loose from the waffle iron.
Remove and let cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve.

title: pan-fried calf liver
directions: Roll each slice of liver in flour, seasoned with salt and pepper.
Heat cooking oil.
Brown liver on each side, about 2 minutes.
Serve with onion rings (fried).

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix any and all kinds of fruit together with pecans, raisins and small marshmallows and let sit overnight and eat.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine sugar, butter, syrup and salt in saucepan.
Bring to boil and boil 5 minutes.
Take off, beat in soda.
Place corn in large shallow pan.
Pour over corn syrup mixture.
Stir well. Bake in oven at 200° for 1 hour, turning corn every 15 minutes. Cool.
Store in plastic bags.

title: blueberry boy bait
directions: Sift flour and sugar together and cut in shortening.
Set aside 3/4 cup of this mixture for topping.
Add baking powder, salt, egg yolks and milk to flour mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Pour into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Arrange blueberries over batter.
Sprinkle topping over all.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chicken scampi
directions: Salt cutlets with garlic salt.
Melt oleo in skillet; add garlic and cutlets.
Sprinkle cutlets with thyme.
Saute until cutlets turn white (turn once).
Sprinkle with paprika before serving.

title: broccoli cheese rice
directions: Cook all items separately.
Mix in a large bowl and add Cheez Whiz.
Let melt.
Ready to serve.

title: pork arlo
directions: Pound pork chops to 1/4-inch thickness.
Saute garlic in hot oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Remove garlic, reserving oil in skillet.
Combine flour and next four ingredients; dredge chops in flour mixture.
Brown in skillet, turning once.
Place chops in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place one slice cheese on each chop.
Top with three asparagus spears.
Fold chops in half. Secure with wooden picks.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Serve with Tarragon Sauce.

title: italian stir-fry
directions: Chop vegetables in bite size pieces.
Stir-fry in olive oil with dry Italian seasoning to taste.
Add tomatoes and basil at end.
Serve over a bed of pasta.
Sprinkle with fresh Parmesan cheese.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine all ingredients, except candy.
Shape dough into balls the size of ping-pong balls.
Roll balls in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes at 375°.
Top each cookie immediately with a candy; press down firmly, so cookie cracks around edge.
Makes approximately 20.
Three-fourths pound bag of candies does 3 batches.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Beat together egg and powdered sugar and set aside.
Melt and cool chocolate chips and butter.
Add to egg mixture.
Add marshmallows and nut meats.
Roll in waxed paper and keep in refrigerator.
Keeps approximately three weeks.

title: breakfast egg casserole
directions: Make 1 day before.
Butter bottom of 9 x 13-inch glass pan. Grate some of cheese on bottom of pan so it is covered well. Break eggs on top of cheese and poke yolks (I mix up in bowl and pour on cheese).
Brown and cut up sausage; put over eggs.
Drain mushrooms and put in pan.
Pour whipping cream over eggs, sausage and mushrooms.
Top with more cheese and cover with foil.
Let set overnight.
Refrigerate and cook with foil on.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: chicken on sunday
directions: Sprinkle the Minute rice on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Heat together the soups and milk; blend well and pour over rice.
Lay chicken breasts over soup mixture.
Sprinkle over this the onion soup mix.
Seal pan with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli in salted water until tender. Drain. Arrange stalks in greased 12x7x2 dish. Layer chicken on top.
Combine next 3 ingredients, pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine butter and bread crumbs. Sprinkle all over top. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, baking soda and salt and add to cream mixture.
Stir in oats, nuts and chocolate chips.
Drop batter by heaping teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: luck country style sausage and pintos
directions: Fry sausage until brown, on all sides.
Drain off all but 2 tablespoons of fat.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute until tender.
Add remaining ingredients.
Stir to blend.
Simmer 10 minutes and serve hot with corn bread.
Serves 6.

title: peach dip
directions: Combine all dry ingredients in medium sauce pan.
Add 3 cups liquid and cook on low heat or simmer for 30 minutes.
Once mixture has congealed, pour into large bowl and refrigerate overnight.
Next day, fold in Cool Whip and peaches.
Serve.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Stir mixture thoroughly and drop with a teaspoon on a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 8 minutes.

title: pearl's sugar cookies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients, then mix with rest of ingredients.
Put in refrigerator 2 or 3 hours.
Roll out and make cookies of all shapes and sizes.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: potato and ham casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix potatoes as directed on package in a 2-quart ovenproof dish.
Mix together ham, peas, onions, green pepper and celery and add to casserole.
Sprinkle with cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes and serve hot.
This is a great dish for working women.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour into two large or 5 miniature loaf pans, ungreased.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Then pour frosting over the loaves.

title: green beans
directions: Put green beans in small casserole dish.
Pour cream of mushroom soup on top of beans.
Put French fried onions on top of all this.
Cook until mixture boils.

title: roquefort curry dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well and keep refrigerated.

title: hot wieners
directions: Melt over low heat the grape jelly and mustard.
Put in wieners and simmer.

title: layered salad
directions: Mix ingredients together for bottom layer.

title: louisiana's bounty
directions: Melt cream cheese and butter in microwave on 1/2 power.
Saute shrimp, onion, pepper and celery in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add to the first mixture.
Add soup, mushrooms seasonings, crabmeat and rice.
Mix well.
Place in 2 quart casserole dish and top with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 30 minutes until bubbly.
Freezes well.
Makes 8 servings.

title: beef borscht
directions: In large kettle, brown meat in oil.
Add 3 cups water and bay leaves.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 50 to 60 minutes or until meat is nearly tender.
Stir in cabbage, potatoes, onion, green pepper, parsley flakes, bouillon and dill weed.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes more or until meat and potatoes are tender.
Stir in tomatoes; heat through.
Remove from heat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Stir in cream and remove bay leaves.
Serves 6.

title: the hour glass cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese until smooth; add pineapple, one cup of the pecans, green pepper, onion and seasoned salt.
When well mixed, form into a ball and roll in the remaining cup of nuts to coat. Wrap in Saran Wrap and refrigerate overnight.
May be frozen.

title: sneaky pete's
directions: Mix in order listed. Freeze overnight.

title: cocoa fruit balls
directions: Remove pits from prunes and stems from figs.
Using metal blade of food processor, process dried fruits, figs and coconut until ground and almost paste.

title: fried corn
directions: Cut corn off cob and place in skillet with enough bacon grease to cover bottom of skillet.
Add flour and butter.
Salt, pepper and sugar to taste.
Add enough water to keep it loose and from sticking.
Stir regularly over medium to low heat.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Prepare macaroni and drain.
In a large bowl, mix all ingredients together and stir until well coated.
Chill well and serve with crackers.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: 1st Day:
Cover cukes with boiling salt water (use 1 pound salt).

title: pickle rolls
directions: Generously spread cream cheese on ham slices.
Place pickle on ham and roll.
Cut into small slices.
Keep unused slices chilled.

title: pepper steak
directions: In skillet, melt butter.
Add onions and green peppers; saute 2 minutes.
Remove and set aside.
Add beef, sprinkled with garlic powder.
Saute until brown.
Add bouillon cube, melted in hot water and simmer.
Blend together the cornstarch and 1/4 cup of water.
Add soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Stir into mixture.
Cook until thickened, adding water if needed to cook meat until tender. Add onions and green peppers.
Serve with buttered rice.

title: orange julius
directions: Put all of the above ingredients in blender and blend.
Serves 6.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken
with
onion,
celery and bay leaves until soft. Debone and cut into bite size pieces.
Use small amount of broth from
chicken
and
saute
onions
and green pepper. After cooking a short time, add soup, tomatoes, seasoning and salt
to
your taste.
Now
layer
in
casserole.
First
dip tortillas in broth, cut
in
4 pieces and layer.
Add part of liquid mixture
and chicken.
Do
this
3 times, topping with cheese.
Bake in 325° oven until bubbly and cheese melts.

title: oriental spinach salad
directions: Toss altogether in salad bowl.

title: very best blonde brownies
directions: Combine sugar and butter in a bowl; stir well.
Add eggs; stir well.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Add flour mixture to sugar mixture, stirring well to combine.
Stir in chocolate morsels to the vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Let cool in pan; cut into bars.

title: turtle cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on package.
Divide batter in half.
Add one stick of butter (melted) and 1/2 can of mix.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Melt caramels, 1 stick butter and remainder of milk. Add pecans.
Pour over baked layer.
Pour remaining cake batter on top of caramel layer.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes more.
Very good and could be called a "brownie".

title: pear crunch
directions: Sprinkle cinnamon over fruit.
Pour on water.
Mix sugar, flour and margarine until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake 1 hour at 300°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger meat in skillet. Salt and pepper to taste. Drain fat; add Ragu.
While this is browning, boil lasagna noodles in separate pan until done, then drain.
In a separate bowl, add egg to cottage cheese and stir.
Layer these items in casserole dish:
sauce, noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Top with either sauce or Mozzarella cheese.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: ravioli with broccoli rabe(quincy pub ii)
directions: Saute minced garlic in a skillet with 2 ounces oil and add Broccoli Rabe for 1 minute.
Deglaze pan with white wine; simmer for 4 minutes.
Add chicken stock, salt and pepper.
Add cooked ravioli and simmer another 4 minutes.
Add Romano cheese to taste.

title: best bran muffins
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine first 7 ingredients. Make a well in the center. Combine the egg, oil, molasses, buttermilk and pineapple. Pour into well; mix until dry ingredients are moistened. Stir in nuts. Coat 18 muffin cups with nonstick cooking spray; fill 2/3 full with batter. Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until golden brown. Yield: 1 1/2 dozen. Serving size: 1 muffin.

title: salsa dip
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into canning jars.
Cover with clean lids and canning rings.
Water bath for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix together the first 4 ingredients.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a buttered casserole.
Over that, put the chicken soup and the mushroom soup.
Brown the bread crumbs in the butter. Put the bread crumbs, then the cheese on the casserole the last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: over the coals vegetables
directions: Cut an 18-inch square of heavy-duty foil.
Toss all ingredients to mix well.
Spoon into center of square.
Wrap loosely and seal securely.
Grill about 5 inches from coals.
Turn occasionally and cook 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: apricot squares
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, brown sugar and oats.
Cut in butter or margarine.
Put 2/3 of the mixture in 9 x 13 pan.
Cover with apricot jam and top with 1/3 c. of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: cheesecake jello
directions: In large bowl, mix cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Thoroughly dissolve gelatine in hot water, then add Jell-O.
Stir into cream cheese mixture and add 7-Up, stirring constantly.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and refrigerate until firm.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Drain vegetables. In bottom of roasting pan, layer in order the chicken, then vegetables. Cover with chicken soup. (Soup will be thick.) Mix Bisquick and enough milk to make medium to thin batter. Pour over soup. Top with pats of butter, salt and pepper. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until brown on top.

title: grandma's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar in pan. Arrange pineapple slices and cherries in center.
Mix cake mix as directed (use water).
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Turn onto platter. Serve warm with whip cream.

title: potatoes
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly with potatoes and pour in 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: champagne punch
directions: Mix juices and water; chill, covered.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sparkling water.
Pour over ice cubes in a large punch bowl.
Pour chilled champagne over punch.
Stir gently.
Serves large crowd.

title: pig pickin'
directions: Step 2:
Combine vinegar, brown sugar, salt and pepper and bring to boil.
Stir to mix well.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Prepare Turkey Filling.
Pour into ungreased baking dish, 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch.
Keep hot in oven while preparing topping.

title: oven-fried chicken a la creole
directions: Melt oleo in 9 x 13-inch glass dish in oven.
Mix salt, paprika, poultry seasoning, black pepper and flour in a bag.
Add chicken pieces.
Shake to coat.
Place pieces, skin side down in melted oleo.
Bake for 30 minutes at 375°.
Remove chicken from dish.
Combine rice, bell pepper, onion, pinch of salt and pepper. Spread in dish.
Place chicken on top.
Pour hot broth over all. Bake 45 minutes at 375°
or until rice and chicken are done. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: easy pie
directions: In a Pyrex dish, melt butter.
Then in a mixing bowl, combine margarine, flour, sugar and milk.
Pour into Pyrex dish.
Pour pie filling into center of dish.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cornish game hen with rice stuffing
directions: Season hens inside and out with salt and pepper.
In saucepan, cook almonds, onions and rice in butter for 5 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add water, bouillon cubes, lemon juice and salt.
Bring mixture to a boil, stirring to dissolve cubes.
Reduce heat.
Cover and cook slowly about 20 to 25 minutes or until liquid is absorbed and rice is fluffy.
Stir in mushrooms.
Lightly stuff birds.
Place birds breast side up in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Brush birds with melted butter or margarine.
Roast covered at 400° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and roast 1 hour longer.

title: fish cakes
directions: Place fish in pan and cover it with water, salt, some celery stalks, parsley, peppercorns and a small onion.
Poach slowly and cook just until fish flakes easily.
Cool and debone.
Mix together remaining ingredients and make into cakes.
Put corn oil on griddle and brown cakes on both sides.
Any extra can be put on wax paper and frozen.

title: velveeta chicken casserole
directions: Prepare stuffing mix.
Combine next 3 ingredients in saucepan or microwave.
Heat until cheese is melted.
Layer chicken and cheese mixture with stuffing in a 9 x 11-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: frosted nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly; then add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt. Beat until smooth and spread thin on a slightly greased deep cookie sheet.

title: taffy
directions: Butter a square pan (8 x 8 x 2-inch).
Mix sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Stir in corn syrup, water, margarine and salt.
Heat to boiling over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Cook, without stirring, to 256° on candy thermometer (or until small amount of mixture dropped into very cold water forms a hard ball), about 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and food color.
Pour into pan.

title: caramel icing
directions: Stir brown sugar in butter.
Boil and stir over low heat 2 minutes.
Stir in milk.
Bring to a rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Cool to lukewarm.
Gradually stir in confectioners sugar.
Cool until correct consistency to spread.
Can be used on several kinds of cakes.
Experiment.

title: kahlua
directions: You will need 1/2 gallon jug.

title: peanut cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well; bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 13 minutes.
Makes 70 to 80 cookies.

title: cookie brittle
directions: Mix margarine, vanilla and salt.
Beat in sugar; then flour. Stir in chocolate chips.
Put batter on a greased cookie sheet. Spread out; press down flat to edges.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: vegetable beef soup("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Brown stew beef in Crisco.
Let pea beans stand in enough boiling water to cover for 20 minutes.
Place spices in a piece of cheesecloth.
Combine beef, marrow bones, pea beans and salt in 1 quart of water.
Simmer 2 hours.
Skim off fat.
Remove bones. Add vegetables, spices and 1 quart of water (or more water if desired).
Cook 1/2 hour or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: one pot bean dinner
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onion; drain.
Mix all ingredients together in a big pot (crock-pot or pot on stove).
Cover and cook 4 to 6 hours in crock-pot on low or 1 hour on low on stove top.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and spoon into a prepared pie crust. Cover with top crust; crimp edges.
Slit top crust and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Let sit for 3 to 5 minutes before serving.

title: pasta shells and scallops
directions: Cook pasta shells.
Saute onion in oil until translucent (about 3 minutes).
Stir in flour; cook (stirring) approximately 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and whisk in stock and cream until smooth.
Add nutmeg, salt and pepper.
Preheat broiler.
Drain pasta and add with scallops to the sauce.
Return to the heat and cover.
Simmer until the scallops are opaque (2 to 3 minutes). Place in 2 to 3-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs, cheese and paprika.
Broil until topping is golden brown (1 to 2 minutes).

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together. Beat eggs and add to sugar mixture. Add melted oleo, milk, vanilla, salt, and chopped nuts. Pour into unbaked pie shell and cook for 10 minutes at 400°; reduce heat to 325° and bake until center is set.
Also good without nuts. May use less cocoa if you don't like a lot of chocolate.

title: crock-pot scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Put half of ham, potatoes and onions in crock-pot.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and 1/2 grated cheese.
Repeat with remaining half of ingredients.
Spoon undiluted soup over top.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Sift
dry
ingredients	together.
Beat
eggs, then add sugar until creamy.
Add oil to eggs and sugar.
At low speed, add dry ingredients,
alternating with pumpkin, egg and sugar mixture. Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.

title: sweet tea
directions: Fill 1 quart microwave safe container with water. Put in tea bags. Microwave for 10 minutes and 24 seconds. Pour sugar in gallon container. Pour in tea. Stir. Taste. Add more sugar if needed. Add water to make one gallon of tea. Stir. Taste again.

title: cheryl's surprise salad
directions: Melt margarine and mix with broken pretzels.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Cool.
Cream together 8 ounces cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Stir in the container of Cool Whip.
Spread completely over pretzel crust.
Boil 1 cup water and add to Jell-O.
Stir until Jell-O is dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries and pineapple.
Stir together until strawberries are thawed.
Pour over cheese and refrigerate.

title: pancakes
directions: Beat egg with hand beater until fluffy.
Beat in remaining ingredients just until smooth.
For thinner pancakes, stir in additional 1/4 cup milk.
Grease heated griddle if necessary.
(To test griddle, sprinkle with a few drops of water; if bubbles skitter around, heat is just right.)
Pour batter onto hot griddle. Cook pancakes until puffed and dry around edges.
Turn over and cook other side until golden brown.

title: zucchini nut bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together the flour, cinnamon and nutmeg; set aside.
In a mixing bowl, beat together sugar, zucchini and egg.
Add oil; mix well.
Stir flour mix into wet mixture.
Gently fold in nuts.
Turn into greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: ms. kitty's pie
directions: Combine all ingredients until crumbly.
Pat into an 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 300° for 15 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put apples in bowl.
Add sugar.
Let stand for 10 minutes. Sift together flour, soda, salt, cinnamon, allspice and nutmeg. Blend melted butter or oleo and egg into apples.
Add flour mixture and spices, raisins and nuts.
Mix and bake about 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry cake roll
directions: Combine first four ingredients and press into greased baking dish.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°, until golden brown.
Let cool.
Mix all other ingredients together except pie filling. Spread this mixture over cooled crust.
Spread pie filling over top.
Refrigerate.

title: mexican cornbread with meat
directions: Mix corn, cornmeal, milk, eggs, bacon drippings, soda and salt. Brown meat and onions. Drain meat and add peppers. Add cheese. Pour 1/2 of batter in iron skillet and add meat on top of batter. Then pour remaining batter over meat. Bake 50-60 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: chicken casserole(this is low in fat and cholesterol)
directions: Combine chicken breast halves and water in a medium saucepan. Cover and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until done; drain well. Remove chicken from bones; coarsely chop chicken. Place chopped chicken in a 1-quart casserole dish coated with cooking spray and sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine milk, yogurt and soup in a medium bowl, stirring until well blended. Spoon mixture evenly over chicken. Combine crushed crackers and melted margarine, stirring well. Sprinkle crackers evenly over top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: nestle crunch fudge sandwiches
directions: In a large pan, combine butterscotch morsels and peanut butter; heat until morsels melt and mixture is smooth. Add Rice Krispies; stir until well coated with butterscotch mixture.

title: oriental stuffed potatoes(microwave)
directions: Wash and dry potatoes.
With fork, pierce each twice.
Place potatoes on paper towel in microwave.
Cook on High for 15 to 17 minutes.
Remove and set aside.

title: tex mexicali dip
directions: Spread bean dip or refried beans in center of a large platter. Add in layers picante sauce, black olives, green onions, guacamole dip, sour cream and cheese.
Add more cheese and green onions on top to garnish.
Surround with chips.

title: mile high meringue
directions: Mix together cornstarch and 2 tablespoons sugar.
Add water and cook until clear.
Beat egg whites until foamy.
Add pinch of salt, vanilla and 6 tablespoons sugar, one tablespoon at a time. Beat until thick and holds a stiff peak.
Add cornstarch mixture to egg whites.
Beat 2 minutes.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until brown.

title: pineapple-raspberry jello mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add undrained pineapple and cranberry sauce.
Pour half of the mixture into a ring mold. Chill until set.
Chill the other half of the mixture.
Mix chopped pecans and sour cream.
Spread evenly over the cranberry-pineapple mixture in the ring mold.
Pour other half of the chilled mixture into ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold.

title: cranberry margaritas
directions: Pour 1/4 cup of the cranberry juice into a shallow bowl.
Pour 3 tablespoons sugar onto a flat plate.
Dip the rims of 4 to 6 wide-mouthed glasses (6 to 8 ounce size, suitable for Margaritas) into juice, then into sugar.
Set the glasses aside.

title: grilled pineapple chicken breast
directions: Marinate chicken overnight in pineapple juice and Worcestershire.
Grill chicken until fully done.
Grill pineapple slices slightly heated and serve with chicken.
Chicken may be basted while grilling for added flavor with juice-sauce mix.

title: banana split pie
directions: Beat the first 3 ingredients together.
Pour in crust. Add the sliced banana.
Spread the pineapple over the banana.
Spread the Cool Whip over top.
Chill.

title: potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes, onion and celery.
In a 6-quart pot, cover vegetables with water and cook until tender.
Add milk, soup, butter, salt and pepper; simmer for about 1 hour.

title: punch
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onion.
Pour mixture over potatoes and cook for 1 hour at 350°.
Uncover 15 minutes.

title: my mom's quick cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and eggs.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together.
Mix with remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Mash flat with fork on bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: orange glazed sweet potatoes
directions: In medium saucepan, combine sweet potatoes, juice and water. Simmer over medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Add brown sugar and margarine.
Cook until forms a glaze (5 minutes). Calories 269, fat 3.3 g, cholesterol 0 g and sodium 97 mg.

title: hummus
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Good as a dip or sandwich spread especially when spread on pita bread and served with tomatoes and sprouts.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Melt chocolate in microwave.
Pour over mixed dry ingredients and mix well.
Pour out on flat wax paper lined surface to dry. Break into chunks when dry.
Makes approximately 10 servings.

title: jello sour cream dessert
directions: Prepare jello according to package instructions and chill until partially set.
Place 1/3 cup crumbs at the bottom of a 9-inch greased pie plate.
Combine sour cream, egg, vanilla and sugar.
Blend well.
Pour half of the sour cream mixture over the crumbs.
Pour half of the jello over the sour cream.
Top with crumbs.
Repeat.
Chill 3 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: candy cane cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly butter, shortening, sugar, egg and flavors. Blend in flour and salt.
Divide dough in half and color one portion red.
Shape into ropes and roll together; twist slightly. Curve down to form cane.
Bake about 9 minutes at 375°.

title: jerri's mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef.
Layer a casserole pan with Doritos. Place a layer of meat on top of the Doritos; then layer the chips again.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake until melted and bubbly.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw broccoli and place in baking dish.
Pour both soups over broccoli.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Drain water chestnuts and pour over soup.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over water chestnuts. Crush 1 or 2 tubes of Ritz crackers and sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: beef stew
directions: Cut up carrots and place on bottom of slow cooker.
Cut 6 potatoes and add on top.
Add beef cubes.
Mix 6 cups water, 3 tablespoons of flour and beef stew seasoning.
Add to slow cooker. Add can of tomatoes (sliced or stewed).
Add onion.
Cook on high in crock-pot for approximately 1 hour.
Then turn to low setting for additional 5 to 11 hours.
Add can of peas just before serving.

title: chicken las vegas
directions: Flour, salt and pepper the chicken breasts according to your tastes.
Brown in small amount of oil.
In greased baking dish, place the 6 slices of ham, then place a slice of cheese on each slice of ham.
Place a browned chicken breast on top of the cheese slices.
Put equal amounts of the mushroom soup on each stack until all the soup is used.
Cover and bake at 350° until done, brown and bubbly, about 45 minutes.
If using glass baking dish, lower temperature to 325°.
Delicious served with rice and a salad.

title: noodle salad
directions: Soak tomatoes, broccoli and cauliflower in dressing for 3 hours or overnight.
Cook noodles and chill in cold water; drain.
Mix all ingredients together except bacon.
Add bacon just before serving. Salad shrimp can also be added.

title: chocolate frosting
directions: Mix; bring to full boil for 1 minute (or more).
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Beat until spreading consistency.

title: broccoli-lima bean casserole
directions: Cook vegetables according to package.
Blend mushroom soup, sour cream and onion soup.
Stir into drained vegetables.
Add water chestnuts.
Melt margarine and pour over Rice Krispies.
Top with Rice Krispies.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Can be made day in advance.

title: **asparagus supreme
directions: Mix crackers and cheese.
Place layer (1/2 of mixture) on bottom of greased baking dish.
Place a layer of asparagus over this, top with sliced egg.
Pour diluted soup over mixture.
Cover with remaining crackers and cheese.
Dot with butter or margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: market day meatballs and cheesy shells casserole
directions: Place thawed shells and sauce in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add meatballs.
Add extra spaghetti sauce, if desired.
Sprinkle grated cheeses on top.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: lemonade chicken
directions: Brown the chicken.
Place in baking dish.
Mix brown sugar, catsup and lemonade together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: little chicken dinners in foil
directions: Tear off 4 pieces of heavy-duty aluminum foil.
On center, place 1 carrot, 1 potato and 1 chicken breast.
Stir together soups and spoon onto top of chicken.
Top with peas.
Wrap foil well.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 50 minutes or until tender with oven set at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: meat pie triangles
directions: Brown meat in oil; drain.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add wine, tomato paste, oregano, salt, pepper and cinnamon.
Cook 3 minutes. Stir in meat and let cool 10 minutes.
Add egg, cheese and parsley and mix lightly.

title: layered crab spread
directions: In large bowl, beat cheese, lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder until fluffy.
Stir in onion.

title: creamy taco dip
directions: Melt cheese and Pet milk.
Cook meat; drain.
Add salt and green chilies.
Add cheese, Ro-Tel, mashed tomatoes, beans and chili powder.
Stir; cook 3 minutes.

title: toasted pecans
directions: Place pecans in a 17 x 12 pan in a 250° oven.
Toast at least 30 minutes to dry and add butter, sliced.
Let pecans get completely greasy, stirring once or twice.
After pecans and butter have mixed well, sprinkle with salt generously and stir very often sprinkling with salt each time as all the salt does not stick to the pecans.
Toast pecans 1 hour or more to desired taste and until butter has been absorbed and pecans are crisp.

title: chewy chocolate cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Blend well. Combine dry ingredients and blend into creamed mixture.
Bake for 8 to 9 minutes at 350°.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Salt and pepper chops.
Place potatoes in shallow baking dish, and layer with onion and cheese.
Add milk and margarine.
Arrange pork chops across top and cover with foil.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.

title: basic red sauce
