directions: Cook onion in oil until tender.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer 15 minutes.
Cool; store in refrigerator or freezer.
Makes 1 quart.

title: mexican rice
directions: Melt butter in 2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Add rice and cook over moderate heat until golden, stirring often.
Add onion, pepper and garlic, cook 30 seconds.
Add broth and cumin.
Bring to a boil; stir once or twice.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes or until rice is tender and all liquid is absorbed.
Salt to taste.

title: spring rolls
directions: Filling:
Stir-fry ground pork until brown.
Add mushrooms, nappa and carrots.
Cook until tender (5 to 7 minutes).
Add salt, sugar, pepper, soy sauce, sesame oil and green onion.
Let it cool completely, 1 to 2 hours.

title: barbecue buns
directions: Fry bacon crisp and drain.
Have meat department to chip or shave canned ham.
Combine all ingredients in skillet.
Blend and heat through.
Spoon on buns and top with a slice of cheese, if desired.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Mix tomatoes and salt thoroughly.
Let stand overnight; drain. Combine with onion, green and red peppers, sugar and vinegar. Tie spices loosely in a cheesecloth bag and place into tomato mixture.
Bring to a boil.
Boil gently for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir frequently.
Remove spice bag.
Pour relish into hot sterile jars. Fill to within 1/2-inch of the top.
Adjust screw band.
Process in boiling water bath 5 minutes.
Yields 6 pints.

title: combination cookies
directions: Cream the brown sugar, white sugar and Crisco.
Add all other ingredients except chocolate chips.
Stir in chocolate chips. Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cook cake according to directions on box.
Bake in 9 x 13 inch pan.
Divide cake into 4 sections.

Make pudding according to directions on box.	Crumble 1/4 of cake into bottom of punch bowl. Layer with vanilla pudding, cherry pie filling, cool whip, crushed pineapple, Repeat the layering for remaining 1/4 sections of cake. Top with coconut and pecans.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: In a bowl, mix together flour, ground ginger and salt and pepper to taste.
Dip chicken in this mix and then brown in oil in a large skillet with a lid.
When browned, remove chicken and discard drippings.
To the skillet, add juice drained from the pineapple chunks and the apricot/pineapple preserves; bring to a boil.
Add chicken, carrots, green pepper and red wine vinegar. Cover and simmer 45 minutes, or until chicken and vegetables are tender.
Mix cornstarch and water together and blend into sauce in the skillet to thicken it slightly.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: squash casserole
directions: Slice squash and cook until tender.
Mash in colander with a fork and let set to drain.
Combine squash, onion, carrots, sour cream, soup and 1/4 cup melted butter.
Pour 1/2 cup of melted butter over crumbs and toss.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Moisten the first 3 ingredients with French dressing and chill. Add salt and pepper to taste.
Flavor mayonnaise with soy sauce and mix all together.
Place on crisp lettuce and garnish with ripe olives and water chestnuts.

title: broccoli and cauliflower mold
directions: Lightly grease a 1 1/2-quart heatproof bowl.
Bring large pot of lightly salted water to boil.
Add broccoli and cauliflower; cook 5 to 7 minutes, until crisp-tender.
Drain.
In colander, rinse in cold water.
Arrange florets in prepared bowl with buds against sides and stems toward center, alternating broccoli and cauliflower and pressing down gently until bowl is full.
Cover bowl with foil.
Can be refrigerated overnight at this point.

title: easter egg or chocolate fondant cream
directions: Peel potato; boil in salted water until soft.
Drain.
Mash potato; measure 1/2 cup.
Blend butter and potato until cold.
Add sugar and vanilla to potato mixture.
Knead until creamy.
Mold into desired shape.
Let chill 1 hour, then dip into chocolate.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Melt butter.
Cook onion until tender.
Add flour and blend. Add milk, salt and pepper.
Cook until slightly thick, stirring constantly.
Add potatoes, pimento and bacon. Makes 6 servings.

title: sour pickles
directions: This recipe makes one quart.
Pack quart jar with medium sized cucumbers.
Add mustard seed, bay leaves, salt, garlic and hot peppers.
Mix water with vinegar, half and half.
Bring to a boil. Pour over cucumbers and seal jar.
Ready to eat in 6 to 8 weeks.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: In large bowl, combine butter, sugar and eggs; beat until light and fluffy.
Blend in sour cream.
Sift flour with soda, baking powder and add to creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and blend well.
Spoon half into buttered and floured 9-inch tube pan. Sprinkle with half cinnamon/nut mixture.
Spoon in remaining batter and top with rest of nut mixture.
Place in cold oven. Set at 350° and bake for about 55 minutes.

title: frog eye salad
directions: Acini de pepe is found in pasta department of most food stores.

title: ranch chicken
directions: Boil or bake breasts in water and cut into large pieces (save broth).
Mix last 5 ingredients, adding enough broth to make mixture soupy.
Add chicken pieces.
Layer this mixture with 12 flour tortillas.
Top with cheese and bake 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Serves 8 or more.

title: chicken continental
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute the chicken until golden brown, remove from pan.
Add onion and paprika to butter.
Cook until the onion is tender.
Blend in the flour.
Add broth and cook until thickened.
Add sour cream and wine.
Return chicken to pan.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate streusel bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Cut in margarine until crumbly (mixture will be dry). Reserve 2 cups crumb mixture; press remaining on bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.
In large mixing bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Gradually beat in condensed milk until smooth.
Add egg and vanilla; mix well.
Pour over crust.
Combine nuts with remaining crumb mix; sprinkle over cream cheese mix. Bake 25 minutes or until bubbly.
Cool.
Chill.
Cut into squares; store in refrigerator.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Preheat oven to 300°.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter, add crumbs and brown, stirring. Remove.
Add remaining butter and onion.
Blend in flour, salt, pepper and mustard.
Add milk gradually, stirring until smooth. Stir in 3/4 of the cheese.
Fold in drained macaroni and mix lightly with a fork.
Top with remaining cheese and crumbs. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake, covered, until bubbly and hot.

title: chinese chicken salad
directions: Marinate chicken overnight in your favorite marinade and cook. In a large bowl, put cabbage, onions, Ramen (crumbled) and cilantro (chopped).
Mix the next 7 ingredients to make dressing. Pour over cabbage and mix well.
Add peanuts and cut up chicken pieces.
Put together just before serving.
This keeps cabbage crisp.

title: cranberry sherbet
directions: Put water and cranberries into saucepan and simmer until the skins

title: cranberry ice
directions: Place cranberries and water in a saucepan.
Cook together 5 minutes.
Add sugar and cook another 5 minutes.
Put through ricer or food mill to remove skins of cranberries.
Add frozen orange juice and mix well.
Freeze firm in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Really good served with turkey.

title: angel food cake
directions: Slice cake in half and tunnel out a trench in the middle. (Save cake for later; set aside in bowl.)
Mix pudding and milk plus 1/2 Cool Whip.
Put pieces together and pack in trenched area of cake.
Ice with remaining Cool Whip.

title: jello salad
directions: Add 1 cup boiling water to Jell-O with a little salt.
Add to remaining ingredients.

title: sweet dill pickles
directions: Fill 4 quart jars with	pickles, any size.
Lay dill on top. Mix the ingredients and
bring
to	a
boil.
Pour	over pickles in jars.
The next day, pour liquid off and bring to a boil again. Pour over pickles and seal.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix sugar with 6 cups water in large pan.
Boil for three minutes.
Take off heat and add jello; let cool.
Add juices and 4 cups of water.
Freeze.

title: potato bake
directions: Combine 1/2 cup butter, salt, pepper, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Place hash browns in butter coated oblong baking dish.
Pour mix over potatoes.
Mix 1/4 cup butter and crushed potato chips; sprinkle over top.
Cover and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: Mix until smooth.
Refrigerate until firm enough to form a ball.
Coat with additional paprika, parsley and nuts.

title: italian spaghetti meat sauce
directions: Cook and stir meat, onion and pepper until meat is brown and onion is tender.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Beat oleo and add sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well. Mix nuts, coconut and raisins.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 300° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: whole wheat bread
directions: Combine hot water, honey, oil and salt in large bowl.
Stir; cool.
Dissolve 1 tablespoon yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add to cooled honey and water mix.
Beat in 2 cups of flour.
Mix for 5 to 10 minutes.
Slowly add the 4 cups of whole wheat flour.
Knead until smooth.
Place in a greased bowl.
Turn to grease the whole ball.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place until double in size.
Form into two loaves.
Place in greased tins.
Brush with melted Crisco.
Bake at 250° for 20 minutes for one loaf and at 375° for 40 minutes for 2 loaves.

title: enchiladas
directions: Brown ground chuck in frying pan.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Soften tortillas in frying pan with small amount of oil. Grate cheese; dice onion and take softened tortillas and add chuck, cheese and onion.
Roll into a cylinder.
Place in baking pan.
Surplus cheese and onion, place on top of tortillas.
Pour contents of sauce on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: old fashioned chicken soup
directions: Cover chicken with water and cook chicken until done. Remove chicken from bone and add the salt, onion, carrots and celery to stock, then simmer until tender. Cut chicken into small pieces and return to soup. Add noodles. Simmer. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: bourbon balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add Karo and liquor.
Mix well. Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar.
Keep covered.
These get better with age.

title: real brunswick stew
directions: Mix all ingredients except corn and cook 1/2 hour.
Add salt to taste and a dash of hot sauce, if desired. Add corn and cook until mixture thickens. During cooking, a dash of Worcestershire sauce may also be added and hot pepper, etc.
Stir mixture often after corn is added to prevent sticking.
Serves 20.

title: fruit slush(for brunch)
directions: Mix and freeze.
Remove about 30 minutes before serving. Serve in sherbet glasses.
Top with strawberries for garnish.

title: carrot and potato soup
directions: Melt margarine in stock pot and saute onion and garlic until translucent.
Add broth, potatoes and carrots; bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer until potatoes and carrots are cooked. Puree as much of the potatoes and carrot mixture as you wish return to the broth.

title: cream cheese spread
directions: Mix cream cheese until creamy.	Add chopped corned beef and rest of ingredients.
Mix
until smooth.
Spread on crackers. (Can be done in blender.)

title: beef and rice fiesta
directions: Brown ground meat in skillet.
Add onion and cook over medium heat until onion is tender.
Add water, cream of mushroom soup, corn, salt and chili powder.
Bring to a boil, stir in Minute rice.
Add tomatoes and green peppers.
Cover and simmer 5 minutes.
Fluff with a fork.

title: chicken rolls
directions: Break tops out of rolls.
Break into bits and brown in butter. Add soup and chicken, cut in small pieces.
Fill in center of rolls.
Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix and let first 3 ingredients stand overnight.
Next day, drain mixture but do not rinse.
Place in large kettle.
Add next 8 ingredients.
Mix well and add peppers.
Cook for 30 minutes at a full rolling boil.
Mix frequently to prevent burning.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.
You may use wax to seal.
Makes enough for 10 half-pint containers.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Stir strawberries and eggs together.
Mix dry ingredients together; add to strawberry mixture.
Stir until blended; add nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into two greased and floured pans (I use 8 small loaf pans).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour (toothpick for testing should come out dry if done; if not, continue to bake and check every 5 minutes until done).

title: lemon parsley chicken and rice
directions: Heat oil in large skillet on medium-high heat.
Add chicken; cook on both sides until browned and cooked through.
Move chicken to side of skillet.
Stir in broth.
Bring to boil.
Stir in rice, parsley, lemon peel and pepper; cover.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Stir.
Sprinkle with almonds.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets.
Chill, peel and grate.
Melt margarine.
Add cheese, sour cream, milk, onions and seasonings. Toss all together.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: polly's beef tips and rice
directions: Brown beef tips (roll in flour and place in cooking oil). After beef tips are good and brown place in crock-pot.
Pour mushroom and onion soup over beef tips and cook 6 to 8 hours on low temperature.
Serve on rice.

title: mexican quickie
directions: Brown hamburger and onion until meat is done; remove as much grease as possible.
Add the taco sauce and water.
Let simmer to blend flavors.

title: lena's meat rolls
directions: Slice a rump roast like bologna.
Lay slices on wax paper. Sprinkle with bread crumbs, grated cheese, garlic powder, Mozzarella and tomato sauce or puree (1 spoon on each slice).
Add bacon, pepperoni and salami, if available.
Roll each slice and stick on skewer with bay leaf between each.
Can be put in electric skillet and ingredients on wax paper sprinkled on top. Cook and, about 10 minutes before done, pour in wine and cook a little longer.

title: hershey cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add other ingredients, except candy bars.
Mix all ingredients, except candy bars.
Then add candy bars, which have been melted in double boiler.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in stem cake pan.

title: banana oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar.
Add egg.
Add bananas and beat well.
In another bowl, combine all dry ingredients, except oats and mix well.
Add together to sugar mixture and mix well.
Add oats gradually and then nuts.
Bake at 375° until brown.

title: never fail chicken n dumplings
directions: Mix together all ingredients but chicken.
Let set 30 minutes before rolling out.
Add 1 can of cream of chicken soup to broth.

title: 7-layer casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Put in 1 layer of potatoes, then 1 layer of onion, then 1 layer carrots and 1 layer of peas. Add cream of celery soup, then layer of pork chops.
Now add cream of mushroom soup. Bake at 350° for 2 hours.
If making a larger amount, you may wish to double the soup.

title: celery salad
directions: Bring jello and pineapple to a boil.
Cool.
Blend Cool Whip, cream cheese, celery and nuts.
Add to jello mixture and refrigerate.

title: beer - cheese fondue
directions: Combine in fondue pot and stir until smooth: butter, cornstarch, paprika and mustard.
Add beer, heat and stir until thickened.
Turn the heat off and add cheese.
Return to medium heat, stirring constantly, until all cheese is melted.
Turn heat to low and serve with cubes of day-old French bread on forks. This can be done on top of the stove, too.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Bake cake according to directions on box.
When cake is cooked, pierce with a fork and pour liquor over it.
Let it stand for several hours or overnight.
Mix puddings according to package directions.
Break and crumble 1/2 of the cake in large bowl. Cover with all of the vanilla pudding.
Break remaining cake and layer over pudding.
Next, pour all of the chocolate pudding over the cake.
Top with Cool Whip prior to serving and add crushed candy bars over the Cool Whip.

title: coffee cake
directions: Combine all ingredients. Beat 10 minutes with mixer. Pour half batter in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan.

title: easy no bake chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Melt butter.
Add rest; boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

title: hanky pankies
directions: Cook meat with garlic until done.
Add Worcestershire sauce and cheese.
When melted, spread onto small rounds of gourmet bread.
Put on cookie sheets and freeze, uncovered.
After frozen, put into freezer bags.
Keep frozen until ready to use. Bake on cookie sheet at 400° until golden and cheese bubbles.

title: chili pie with corn bread topping
directions: Cook onion, green pepper and ground chuck in a large ovenproof skillet over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well; set aside.
Wipe drippings from skillet with paper towel.
Return meat mixture into skillet; add corn and next 9 ingredients, stirring well.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat to medium-low and cook 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients in a bowl.
Combine buttermilk and egg white; add to dry ingredients, stirring until moist.
Spoon evenly over meat mixture.
Bake at 400° for 13 minutes or until wooden pick inserted in center of corn bread comes out clean.

title: peanut butter swirls
directions: Mix frosting and sugar by hand. It will form a stiff dough. Roll out on waxed paper into a rectangle. Top with peanut butter, enough to cover and taste. Roll up jelly roll style. Chill.
Slice into pieces before serving.

title: beef and pepper rice skillet
directions: Brown beef in 10-inch skillet; drain.
Stir in green peppers, celery and onion.
Pour rice over (do not stir), then can of tomatoes.
Mix bouillon cube in water with soy sauce.
Pour over all.
Cook covered over low heat until done.
Do not stir.

title: potato toppings(lo-fat)
directions: Combine ingredients and chill 1 hour before serving to allow flavors to blend.

title: diabetic date nut cake
directions: Cream butter, eggs, sugar substitute and vanilla.
Add flour, soda and spices; mix well.
Fold in dates, applesauce and nuts. Bake in greased, floured loaf pan at 250° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: danish pastry
directions: Dissolve yeast in the warm milk.
Separate egg yolks and save the egg whites in a separate bowl.
Beat the yolks slightly and add to the milk mixture.
Mix dry ingredients and cut in the butter with a pastry blender.
Add milk mixture and combine well. Chill the dough.
Beat egg whites and add 3/4 cup sugar slowly as the whites are beaten.
Divide chilled dough into 4 pieces.
Roll dough thin on a floured board.
Spread with the egg white mixture. Sprinkle with chopped nuts and sliced maraschino cherries.
Roll like for a jelly roll.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Let rise for about 30 minutes in a warm place.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Drizzle a thin sugar frosting if desired.

title: breast of chicken pheasant style
directions: Rub thawed chicken breasts with salt and pepper.
Put diced vegetables in roasting pan.
Break bay leaves and distribute over vegetables.
Lay chicken breasts skin side up over vegetables.
Cut bacon strips in half; lay across chicken breasts.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Remove chicken breasts to platter to keep warm.
Add chicken stock to vegetable drippings and bring to a boil.
Add wine and simmer to dissipate alcohol.
Add enough roux to make a medium sauce.
Strain.
Add sour cream; ladle over chicken and serve over wild rice.
Garnish with orange star and endive.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape meatballs and place in flat pan.

title: quick banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Blend Eagle Brand and Cool Whip into pudding mix.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding mix.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a greased casserole dish at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix all together, except Fritos. Add Fritos the last thing. Don't salt.
Let each one do their own salting.

title: aunt patty's hot chocolate
directions: Combine ingredients in a large container. Store in airtight container. To use, put 3 to 4 heaping tablespoonfuls of mix into cup. Pour in boiling water and stir.

title: red beet pickles
directions: Mix. Let mixture come to a boil.
Fill can with beets, pour in the mixture and seal.

title: baked clams
directions: Freeze clams first to allow for easy opening.
Remove clams from shells and retain shells and clam juice for later use.
Mince clams in food processor or chop finely.
Set aside.
Chop onion and peppers finely.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add egg and vanilla.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Add as much of remaining 1/2 cup flour as needed for dough to be rolled. Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out and cut into shapes.
Brush with water and sprinkle with sugar before baking at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: savory beef (buffalo!)
directions: Cut beef into thin slices.
Sprinkle with pepper and set aside.
Saute the onion in oil until golden.
Remove from skillet. Brown meat in the same skillet and set aside with onion.
Blend flour into oil in skillet.
Gradually add water and bouillon cubes.
Stir until smooth and thick.
Add remaining ingredients and blend thoroughly.
Cook until meat is tender, adding water, if necessary.
(I have to cook it longer here because the meat tends to be tougher.) Serve with noodles or rice.
Serves 6.

title: biscuit lasagne
directions: Pour sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Flatten out biscuits on counter.
Make a filling from the rest of the ingredients.
Put a heaping tablespoon of filling in each biscuit center.
Fold over and press edges shut.
Lay in sauce and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: pasta salad
directions: Steam pasta and vegetables and rinse in cold water.
Add dressing, stir together and serve hot or cold.

title: salsa(makes 1 quart)
directions: Run tomatoes through chop cycle on blender just until everything has passed through blade.
Add all ingredients.
Mix and let set at least 1 hour before serving with tortilla chips.

title: instant spiced tea
directions: Use 1/2 cup sugar when using 1 scoop of Wyler's mix.
Mix well and store in airtight jar.
Add 3 (heaping) teaspoons per cup; add hot water.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Dump in pan and mix.
(Better if refrigerated overnight.) Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° until brown.
No time given.

title: scrabble
directions: Melt chocolate.
Add peanuts and pretzels.
Pour on greased cookie sheet and put in freezer for 5 minutes.
Take out of freezer and break into pieces.

title: orange nut bread
directions: Squeeze juice in cup.
Fill to top with boiling water.
Grind rind with raisins.
Peel white lining from orange, as it makes bread bitter.
Bake in a 2 pound tin, well-greased, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: self frosted date cake
directions: Pour boiling water over chopped dates and soda.
Allow mixture to cool.
Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs and cooled date mixture.
Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Add to date, sugar, egg mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chips, brown sugar and walnuts over batter.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Dissolve the yeast
in the lukewarm water.
Combine the brown sugar, molasses, salt, shortening and hot water; stir until dissolved.
Cool to lukewarm. Add the rye flour. Add yeast and caraway seed.
Mix well. Add enough white flour to make soft dough. Use reserved for kneading.
Place in greased bowl. Cover and let rise until double (1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Punch down. Divide into 2 parts and form into balls. I use a pie pan.
Cover and let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Brush with margarine while still hot.

title: candied sugared nuts
directions: Beat egg white until frothy.
Add vanilla.
Pour over nuts and mix with hands.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together.
Pour over nuts and mix with hands.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake 1 hour at 250°, turning every 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter snacks
directions: Blend syrup and sugar in saucepan; bring to boil.
Turn off flame.
Stir in peanut butter, then cereal.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on baking sheet.
Cook at 275° for 10 or 15 minutes.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Mix and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Top with crushed Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Cook at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: buckeye cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except last two.
Shape into balls. Place on cookie sheet and refrigerate overnight.
After refrigerating, combine and melt chocolate and paraffin in a double boiler.
Use a toothpick to dip each cookie in hot mixture, leaving top uncovered.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix margarine, 1/2 cup sugar and flour together to form a crust.
Flour
hands
and
pat into a pizza pan.
Prick with fork. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese and 1 cup powdered
sugar
until
smooth.
Add Cool Whip, fold in.
Spread on crust.
Garnish with sliced berries.

title: party cheese spread
directions: Cook vinegar, eggs, sugar and butter until mixture gets thick. Add cheese, chopped olives, pimentos and onion.
Stir together and allow to cool before using.

title: mom's macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni and drain.
Add ingredients and mix.

title: peanut butter chocolate cookies
directions: Cream first 4
ingredients
in
bowl.
In another bowl, combine flour, cocoa,
baking soda and salt.
Mix two mixtures together.
Drop by
teaspoons onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Combine soup, sour cream and cheese. Pour over vegetables and mix. Pour into greased casserole. Bake in a 350° oven 30 minutes. Sprinkle with crumbs. Bake 5 minutes longer.

title: baker's dough clay
directions: Mix flour and salt in a bowl.
Add oil.
Add water. Knead your dough.
Make a shape with the dough.
Air dry or bake shapes in a 300° oven for 60 minutes.
Paint you shapes any color you wish.

title: pecan chess pie(southern)
directions: Mix brown sugar, white sugar and flour.
Beat remaining ingredients in thoroughly.
Add
one cup chopped pecans.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake
until
set, about 40 minutes in 325° oven.

title: grandma's sugar cookies
directions: Combine ingredients in order given.
Roll out on floured board and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Frost.

title: sue's o'henry bars
directions: Cream margarine.
Stir in oats, sugar, corn syrup and vanilla. Spread mixture in a 13x9 -inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
(Don't bake any longer even though bars will not look cooked.)
Cool.

title: tuna boats(microwave)
directions: Combine
tuna,	cheese,
salad dressing, pickle relish, green onion
and	mustard
and
mix well.
Fill buns with tuna mixture; garnish
with
olives.
Arrange buns in an 8 x 8-inch glass dish. Microwave
on Medium uncovered for 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese begins to melt.

title: california tamale pie
directions: In a medium skillet, cook ground beef until brown and crumbly.
Drain and set aside.
In a 2 1/2 quart casserole dish, combine corn meal, milk and egg and mix well.
Add ground beef and remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Stir to mix.
Bake uncovered, at 350 degrees for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top of casserole and continue baking until cheese melts.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Crush cookies; divide in half.
Melt margarine.
Mix 1/2 of cookie crumbs and margarine together.
Press into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat cream cheese until smooth.
Fold in 9 ounces of Cool Whip.
Spread on top of crumbs.
Mix pudding and milk until creamy.
Let set for 5 minutes, then spread on top of cheese mixture.
Spread extra Cool Whip on top.
Sprinkle reserved cookie crumbs on top.
Chill 4 hours or overnight.

title: overnight raw vegetable salad
directions: Dice vegetables small.
Mix dressing together.
Add to vegetables and let stand overnight in refrigerator.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Grease cookie sheet; mix sugar and corn syrup in a 4-cup measure (glass).
Cook on High 4 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook 3 minutes.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 to 2 1/2 minutes longer (I usually cook 2 1/2 minutes).
Blend in baking soda, stir until light and foamy; spread on cookie sheet.

title: hawaiian chicken sauce
directions: Put in a glass dish with chicken and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and spread in bottom of pan.
Put coconut over top.
Mix the next 3 ingredients and pour over top of the coconut.
Add 1/2 cup nuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: orange cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar well.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add soda to milk.
Sift flour and salt together; add alternately with milk.
Add orange peel.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Let cool.
Add frosting.

title: marks famous spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add season pkg. stir in stewed tomatoes, onion, tomato sauce, mushrooms, and water.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Add all remaining spices, simmer 20 minutes.
Cook Angel Hair pasta according to pkg. instructions. Add 2 Tbsp. of butter when noodles are finished.
Serve spaghetti according to your preference, either with sauce over pasta or mixed together.

title: summer salad
directions: Drain beans, corn, peas and pimentos well.
Add celery, green pepper and onion.
Heat vinegar, sugar, salad oil and water and pour over vegetables; refrigerate 4 to 12 hours before serving. The longer it marinates, the better it is.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Prepare pumpkin by paring and cooking until soft.
Drain and cool.
Mix in a blender.
May also be baked without crust. Sprinkle top with cinnamon.
Bake at 375° until pie is firm, approximately 40 minutes.

title: no-cook candy
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Shape in small balls.
(Roll in chopped peanuts, or chocolate sprinkles, or leave plain.) Makes 36 (1 1/2-inch) balls.

title: crock-pot vegetable soup
directions: Put hamburger on bottom of crock-pot; add remaining ingredients.
Cook 5 to 7 hours on high.

title: angel food cake with amaretto almond sauce* * * * *
directions: We have a son-in-law who loves this Smoked Turkey so much that he would raid the refrigerator for leftovers even after eating a big meal.
You don't need a covered grill to make it.
Just tent the grill and turkey with foil and make a vent hole over the turkey.
The turkey should never be directly over the coals.
The cooking is done entirely by indirect heat.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken.
Cool chicken and cut into small pieces.
Saute pecans in butter until crisp; salt lightly.
Cool and chop coarsely.
Combine pecans and chicken.
Mix with mayonnaise until moist.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: granny's pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 350° until set in middle.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Combine cinnamon, sugar and pecans; set aside.
Combine cake mix with sugar, oil and sour cream; mix well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix well after each one.
Grease and flour Bundt pan.
Put half of batter in pan, then half of nut mixture, then other half of batter.
Sprinkle rest of nut mixture on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherries 'n' cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour, salt and baking powder in large mixer bowl.
Add shortening, milk and vanilla.
Beat on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with drained cherries.
Sprinkle with 1 cup sugar, then pour on the 2 cups liquid.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cover with foil for last 15 minutes.
Serve warm with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: oat pancakes
directions: Combine all dry ingredients and mix.
Beat egg and add to milk.
Add to dry ingredients, mix well and add melted oleo.
Mix in grated apples.
Bake on hot griddle.

title: brodle cornbread
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Combine water, butter, salt and onion salt.
Bring to boil. Remove from heat and add milk, mashed potatoes, sour cream and cream cheese.
Mix with mixer to make sure it is smooth.
Put in 3-quart casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: hershey's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix wet ingredients, then mix the rest thoroughly.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Remove from oven and place Hershey's Kisses on top.

title: no-bake peanut butter chip cookies
directions: Melt peanut butter chips and shortening in top of a double boiler over hot, not boiling, water.
Stir until smooth and creamy. Combine cereal, melted chips and raisins.
Stir until cereal is coated. Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper lined cookie sheet. Cover and chill for 1 hour.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: easy toffee
directions: Spread nuts in bottom of a 6 x 10-inch pan or round pie tin. Boil butter and sugar 5 minutes or to 310°, stirring constantly. Pour over nuts, then put chips over hot mixture.
Cover pan with a bread board to hold in heat.
When chips are melted (about 5 minutes), spread chocolate smooth and refrigerate until cool.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, salt, chicken, veggies, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 cup Durkee onions.
Place in 8 x 12 dish.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into large cake pan and bake 35 to 40 minutes (350°).
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: easy peel-apart babka
directions: Separate biscuits, cut each one into 6 pieces and place into large bowl.
In small bowl, mix sugar, cinnamon and raisins.
Pour over dough and toss until all pieces are coated.
Place dough pieces into tube or Bundt pan that is sprayed with Pam.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
After 10 minutes, invert pan onto plate or platter.

title: bean soup
directions: In skillet put a little oil and saute onions.
Put in can of tomatoes and simmer 1/2 hour.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add beans and simmer 10 minutes.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Set oven for 350°.
Sprinkle brown sugar in bottom of well-greased pan, 9 x 9 x 2-inch.
Dot with butter.
Melt mixture over very low heat.
Drain pineapple.
Place slices in pan with cherry in center of each.

title: copper pennies
directions: Slice carrots 1/2-inch thick and boil in salted water until tender.
Drain and cool.
Place carrots in a bowl with onion and bell pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour this over the vegetables.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: wild rice and seafood casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and green pepper in butter.
Saute mushrooms separately in butter.
Mix all ingredients, except bread crumbs, and place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake in moderate oven (325°) for about 30 minutes, covered.
Remove cover, top with buttered crumbs and brown on top.
This rich dish will serve 10 to 12 persons.

title: corn bread patties
directions: Combine corn meal and flour.
Add egg gradually.
Beat in milk.
Drop from a spoon into hot grease.
Fry until brown.
Can do okra the same way.
Delicious.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk and yeast, dissolved in water.
Mix with a spoon until all flour is moist.
Cover bowl and put in refrigerator until ready to use or it can be used right away.
The dough will keep for several weeks in refrigerator.
Roll out as much dough as you need on floured board, 1/2 to 3/4-inch thick.
Cut out.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes on ungreased pan.

title: cinnamon bread
directions: Bring milk to scalding.
Remove from heat; stir in butter (in small pieces), sugar and salt.
Let cool.
In a bowl, mix yeast with 1/4 cup warm water.
Let stand about 5 minutes.
Add milk mixture, 1 egg, 1 egg yolk and flour; blend well.
Place dough on a well floured board; knead until smooth and velvety, about 5 minutes.
Place in a bowl.
Cover; let rise in a warm place until doubled (takes about 1 1/2 hours).
Knead again on a floured board to expel air bubbles.

title: cole slaw
directions: Prepare cabbage just before using. Shake together all other ingredients in a covered jar. Add dressing to cabbage, tossing lightly and mixing well just before serving.

title: italian pasta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Refrigerate for 8 to 24 hours before serving.
Serves a large group.
Recipe can be halved.

title: impossible pie
directions: Put all in blender; mix until smooth. Pour in a 10-inch greased pie pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes. You do not need crust.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare pastry.
Beat eggs, sugar, salt, margarine and syrup.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake until set, 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Serve warm or refrigerated.

title: cherry pudding cake
directions: Grease large rectangular dish.
Spread pie filling evenly on bottom.
Cover with all dry cake mix, spreading evenly.
Melt margarine and pour as evenly as possible over the cake mix.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Tilt dish to dampen the cake mix.
Bake until light brown on top in 325° oven.

title: chunky pimento cheese
directions: Combine cream cheese and pimento; mix well.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.

title: pineapple rice
directions: Combine rice and water.
Cook until done.
Drain the crushed pineapple.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: spicy grilled chicken(gas grilling)
directions: In plastic bag, combine 1/4 cup each of salsa and Italian dressing.
Add chicken.
Marinate for 1 to 2 hours in refrigerator.
Remove chicken and discard marinade.
Heat remaining salsa and dressing.

title: buttered cabbage
directions: Remove outside leaves of cabbage, wash cabbage and cut into wedges.
Remove core and cut wedges crosswise into 1-inch slices. Heat 1-inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt for 1 cup water) to a boil.
Add cabbage; cover and heat to a boil.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes or until just crisp and tender.
Drain.
Stir in butter and lemon juice or white wine vinegar.
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: easy oven stew
directions: In a Dutch oven, brown the steak in oil.
Add the next eight ingredients; cover and bake at 300° for 4 to 5 hours, stirring twice.
Add the peas, salt and pepper during the last 30 minutes of baking.
Yields 6 servings; 263 calories per serving, 33 mg cholesterol and 5 g fat.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Peel enough apples to fill crock-pot when cut up.
Add just enough water to start it.
Cook until mushy.
During this time, you can add the remaining ingredients. Stir until well blended. Process as desired.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook green beans in salted water for 10 minutes.
Drain in sieve.
Drain water chestnuts and mushrooms.
Make alternate layers in greased 2-quart casserole of beans, water chestnuts, mushrooms, bean sprouts and onion rings.
Pour soup with a little of the melted butter over vegetables.
If it seems dry add 1/4 cup juice from the vegetables, usually not necessary.
Mix the bread crumbs with the rest of the melted butter.
Combine them with the Parmesan cheese and sprinkle over top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: almond butter
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill in decorative crock. Excellent on nut breads.
Yields 1/2 cup.

title: chari's favorite broccoli soup
directions: Pour oil in large pot over medium heat.
Add onion and broccoli; lightly saute.
Pour chicken stock in pot.
The stock should cover broccoli and onion.
Add pepper and bring to boil. Reduce heat, cover and simmer 20 minutes.
Place entire contents of pot in food processor.
(Depending on the size of your processor, you may have to process in 1/3 to 1/2 portions.) Process until smooth.
Replace processed soup in stock pot and add dissolved cornstarch.
Slowly add milk, stirring while adding. Simmer 10 minutes.
Do not let boil.
Adjust seasoning to taste.

title: texas hash
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown beef, onions and pepper in oil.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook, covered, 1 hour, then uncovered 15 minutes more.

title: fried partridge
directions: Boil
cleaned breast in 1 tablespoon of baking soda and 3 inches
of	water
in
pan.
Boil small breast 10 minutes or large breast 15 minutes.
Dry and cut into pieces and debone. Coat meat with egg and then in flour.
Next, fry in butter and 1 tablespoon oil; fry until tender.

title: honey baked beans
directions: Saute bacon and onions until tender. Combine with remaining ingredients in shallow 2-quart oven-safe baking dish.
Cover with lid or aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Uncover and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: sausage souffle
directions: Place cubed bread in bottom of grease 8 x 8-inch baking dish and top with cheese.
Brown sausage and drain.
Place on top of cheese.
Beat eggs with milk and mustard, pour over sausage mixture.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Next day dilute soup with milk and pour over top.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.
Serves 4.

title: tian of zucchini, tomatoes and potatoes
directions: Thinly slice vegetables.
Oil a shallow casserole dish (I use an earthen ware pie plate) and arrange vegetables, alternating layers, starting with potatoes.
Coat them with olive oil and some of the basil.
Bake for 30 minutes or until potatoes are tender. I like them to crisp on the edges.
Sprinkle remaining basil on vegetables and salt and pepper to taste.
Delicious with a veal chop.
Serves 4.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix all the loaf ingredients together (first 6 ingredients) and shape like a loaf in roaster.
Bake 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 325°. Baste every 15 minutes to 1/2 hour with remaining ingredients.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Let stand in the refrigerator overnight.

title: dump cake
directions: Put each in Pyrex pan in order (3-quart dish).
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.
Browns butter on top.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a greased casserole. Bake at 350° until brown and well set.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Good on any kind of meat.

title: robby's rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water.
Mix flour and cake mix; then stir into yeast and water mixture (mix well).
Let rise 1 hour.
Shape on floured surface to 9 x 13-inches.
Cut in squares and put in pan sprayed with vegetable spray.
Let rise 1 hour.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.
Brush top with melted butter.

title: icicle pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers longways; put in crock.
Pour boiling water and salt over cucumbers.
Let stand one week.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix well the peanut butter, cracker crumbs and powdered sugar and roll into balls.
Chill in freezer.
Dip in chocolate and put on wax paper.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown the ground beef.
Drain off excess fat and add taco seasoning mix.
Let stand.
Cut onion, tomatoes and lettuce. Grate cheese.
Place all ingredients in a large bowl.
Drain and rinse beans.
Add to mixture.
Add chips and dressing at the last minute.
Mix and serve.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine all ingredients in slow cooker. Cook on low for 6 to 8 hrs. or until meat is done. If possible, stir occasionally. Serve with noodles.

title: danish puff
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut 1/2 cup butter into 1 cup flour. Sprinkle 2 tablespoons water over mixture; mix.
Round into ball; divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, put each half into a 12 x 3-inch strip.
Strips should be about 3 inches apart.
Heat 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup water to rolling boil in medium saucepan. Remove from heat and quickly stir in almond extract and 1 cup flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs (all at once) until smooth and glossy.
Divide in half; spread evenly over 12 x 3-inch strips.
Bake about 60 minutes or until topping is crisp and brown.
Cool.
As topping shrinks the custardy top of puff is formed.
Frost; sprinkle with nuts and garnish with cherries (optional).

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Bake pie shell for 8 minutes; remove from oven.
Reduce oven to 350°.
In skillet, brown meat; pour off fat.
Add tomato sauce, green pepper, onion and bouillon; cook until bouillon dissolves.
Remove from heat and stir in eggs, flour and 6 cheese slices, broken.
Pour into shell.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Arrange remaining cheese on top.
Return to oven for 3 to 5 minutes.
Garnish with tomatoes and lettuce.

title: gorecki's broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole dish and bake for 45 minutes at 325°.

title: eggplant caesar
directions: Wash and trim only tender pods, not to remove the cap unless using for soup.
Cook in boiling water one minute.
Put hot okra in jars leaving 1/2-inch on top.
Season with 1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 pint of water.
Process in pressure canner at 10 pounds for 1 pint 25 minutes or at 10 pounds 1 quart 40 minutes.
Remove from canner and adjust back in hot water for those that do not seal.

title: easy barbecue chicken
directions: Place all ingredients in large stainless or porcelain covered skillet in order given.
Do not use an iron skillet.
Cover and cook over medium heat, turning occasionally.
Cook 40 minutes, until chicken is done.
Remove chicken to serving plate.
Keep warm.
Cook remaining sauce until thick and bubbly.
Do not burn. Pour over chicken to serve, or use for dipping.
May also fix sauce to use for basting chicken cooked on the grill.

title: diet pumpkin pie
directions: Thoroughly blend all ingredients together.
Pour into 9-inch pie shell and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese-chili cubes
directions: In a large bowl beat the eggs using electric mixer for 4 or 5 minutes until light.
Add the baking mixture and mix well.
Fold in the cheese, cottage cheese and chilies.
Turn mixture into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand for 10 minutes.
Cut into small squares.
Can be served either warm or cool.
Yields 3 to 4 dozen appetizers.

title: lemon squares
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix flour, butter and cashews.
Press in bottom of pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Bake until light brown, 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: dad's skillet potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onion thin.
Heat fat in skillet over low heat.
Add potatoes, onion and seasonings.
Cover and cook about 15 minutes.
Turn and re-cover.
Continue cooking another 15 minutes or until done.
Serves 6.

title: green bean bake
directions: Blend soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper until smooth.
Stir in green beans and half a can of onion rings.
Turn mixture into a casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Cover and bake for 5 minutes.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or chicken soup

title: party potatoes
directions: Stir sour cream and cheese together; add to hot potatoes. Beat until smooth.
Add butter, chives, salt and pepper.
Pour into well-greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with butter.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: chocolate cream dessert
directions: Prepare brownie mix as directed on package. Let brownies cool completely. Beat the powdered sugar, butter and water until smooth. Spread evenly on top of cooled brownie. Cover and refrigerate until set. Place chocolate chips and remaining 6 tablespoons butter in microwave-safe bowl and microwave on high for approx. one minute or until mixture is smooth when stirred. Pour over the chilled dessert. Cover and refrigerate at least one hour before serving. Cover and refrigerate any leftover dessert.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Spread crescent rolls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing mix; spread on cooked rolls.
Sprinkle vegetables on cream cheese layer.
Cut in small squares.
Make the day before serving.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Break up head of cauliflower.
Drain, then chop or slice black olives.
Chop onions.
Mix in bowl with salad dressing.
Chill at least 3 hours before serving.

title: pineapple milkshake
directions: Combine all ingredients in container of an electric blender; process just until smooth, stopping once to scrape down sides. Yield:
3 cups.

title: corn relish
directions: Cook corn on cob and cut off.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to a boil.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Pack in hot jars and seal. Makes 12 to 14 pints.

title: carrot pudding
directions: Cream margarine with sugar and add egg and water, then carrots.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mixture. Mix and spoon into greased 6 to 8 cup ring mold or a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with meat dishes.

title: kettle gravy
directions: Pour juices into a saucepan.
Combine cornstarch and water until smooth.
Stir into juices.
Bring to a boil.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until thickened.
Season with salt and pepper. Yield:
about 3 cups.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Break eggs into bowl and beat with fork.
Add milk, salt, pepper and bread.
Beat until bread disintegrates.
Add onion, carrot, cheese and beef.
Mix well.
Pack in a loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Serve hot or cold.
Can be made and frozen or baked and frozen.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix cocoa and powdered sugar in a large bowl.
In a large saucepan, melt the cheese and butter over medium-low heat.
Stir continually until dissolved. Add vanilla and then pour mixture over cocoa and powdered sugar.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.
Mix thoroughly with a large heavy spoon.
Pour into square pans, two or more.
Chill and enjoy.
This makes over 6 pounds of fudge, so you might want to cut it in half.
But you'll wish you had the other 3 pounds if you do!

title: spinach bars
directions: Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Beat eggs, add other ingredients.
Pour over melted butter.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Cool before cutting into bars.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil 15 minutes or soft ball. Beat and spread in greased pan.

title: texas potato salad
directions: Combine all into large bowl.
Garnish with paprika.
Cover bowl and chill.

title: snickers cake
directions: Mix cake according to instructions on box.
Pour half of batter into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with oleo and milk in double boiler.
Pour over baked cake.
Sprinkle nuts and chocolate chips over this. Pour remaining batter over this mixture and bake 20 minutes at 250°.
After this time, increase to 350° and bake 10 minutes more.

title: peanut butter and cream cheese pie
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine cream cheese and peanut butter; beat with an electric mixer until combined.
Add powdered sugar and milk; beat until combined.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spoon into pie shell.
Sprinkle with peanuts, if desired.
Cover and chill in the freezer for 15 minutes.
(Can be drizzled with chocolate syrup!)
Makes 8 servings.

title: free 'n easy pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry, and set aside.
Beat the applesauce with the sugar until light and creamy.
Sift the flour with the baking powder and salt.

Blend the skim evaporated milk with the water and extract. Add the flour mixture to the creamed applesauce alternately with the milk mixture, beginning and ending with the flour mixture. Gently fold in the beaten egg whites.

title: bean bundles
directions: Make bundles of beans by wrapping 5 to 6 whole beans in a slice of bacon.
Place in a casserole dish coated with Pam. Sprinkle tops of bundles with garlic salt.
Bake in a 350° oven until bacon is crisp on top and beans are cooked (about 20 minutes).

title: silly putty
directions: Combine and knead until smooth and silky.

title: nigerian peanut soup
directions: In a saucepan, heat the broth to a bare simmer and in a small bowl, stir together the peanuts and 1/2 cup of the broth until the mixture forms a paste.
Stir the peanut paste into the simmering broth; add the chili peppers, the bell pepper and the onion and bring the mixture to a boil.
Simmer the soup, stirring occasionally, for 15 to 20 minutes, or until it thickens to the desired consistency and season it with salt and pepper.
Makes about 4 cups, serving 2 to 4.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine meal, flour, soda, salt and baking powder.
Mix well. Add eggs and buttermilk.
Mix well.
Add onions, catsup and Tabasco.
Mix well.
Using about 1 tablespoon of batter, form into a ball and fry in deep fat fryer for about 2 minutes or until evenly browned.
Yield: Approximately 2 dozen.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pour into 3 unbaked pie shells. Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 3 deep dish pies.

title: rye bread
directions: Mix potato flakes and hot water.
Add cold water.
Add yeast, salt, oil, and molasses.
Add rye graham flour.
Mix well.
Add 2 c. white flour.
Mix well.
Add remaining 2 c. white flour. Spread about 1 c. flour on pastry sheet.
Knead dough.
If sticky, add more flour.
Knead until smooth.
Oil mixing bowl.
Place smooth side of dough on bottom.
Then turn dough over.
Let stand covered (in bowl) in sink filled with hot water, about 1 hour or until rises in center.
Place on pastry sheet.
Cut into 3 equal pieces.
Place in greased loaf pans.
Let rise with pans in water, for 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350 for 1 hour.
Brush top with butter.

title: chocolate-dream pie
directions: Mix pudding, Dream Whip and milk with hand mixer (follow directions on pudding box).
Pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill at least 2 hours (can be chilled overnight).
Right before serving, spread thick layer of Cool Whip on top (approximately 1 to 1 1/2-inches).
Cut and serve.

title: marshall treats
directions: Cook in double boiler the eggs, sugar, salt and margarine; cook 20 minutes to 1/2 hour.
Stir often; cool.
In large bowl, put cracker crumbs, marshmallows, nuts and vanilla.
Mix all together.
Press in large pan and cool and spread over top.
Melt butterscotch tidbits and spread over top of treats.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and after bringing to a boil, simmer about 3 hours.
Refrigerate.
Next day skim off fat and discard vegetables and bones.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat and add remaining ingredients.

title: mexican fruitcake
directions: Mix everything together. Put in greased pan with butter, 9 x 13. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Add some cinnamon to the 1/4 cup sugar and mix together.
Add graham crackers and margarine; mix well.
Line a sheet cake pan with foil and spread the crust evenly, including up the sides of pan.

title: fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix well
all
ingredients with buttermilk until medium thickness.	Drop with large spoon in hot 10 to 12-inch skillet with 1 teaspoon
each
bacon
grease and butter.
Cook at 425° until golden brown.
Makes 7 to 10 pieces.

title: beef tips and gravy over rice
directions: Brown beef cubes (they may be cut into smaller pieces), drain any oil or grease.
Add gravy, salt and pepper to taste and let simmer while you boil your rice in another pan.
When rice is done, put a portion on your plate then spoon your beef tips and gravy over your rice and enjoy.

title: mexicali potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 400 degrees.
Brown ground beef in large skillet; drain well.
Add corn, onions, chili powder, potato slices, contents of sauce mix envelope, boiling water and milk; mix well.
Spoon mixture into ungreased 8 inch square baking dish. Top with jalapenos.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or until mixture bubbles around edges.
Cover loosely with foil and bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil hen until done, approximately 1 1/2 hours; remove chicken from broth mixture and remove skin and bones from chicken.
Place chicken meat back into broth mixture; cook and additional 15 minutes.

title: aunt lena's cake
directions: Stir all together; pour into an 8-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Cook soup, milk, mayonnaise and curry in pan.
Do not boil. Put in baking dish.
Stir in steamed broccoli and chicken. Sprinkle on bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle on Cheddar cheese.
Return to oven until cheese is soft.

title: blueberry cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, eggs, and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients. Fold in blueberries.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar and swirl top lightly with knife.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: In a small bowl, combine poppy seed and milk.
Set aside. Separate eggs.
In large bowl, cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg yolks, poppy seed mix, buttermilk and extracts.
Sift flour, soda and salt well and add to mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter.
Bake in tube pan 1 hour and 20 minutes at 325°. After three minutes, take out of pan and glaze.

title: frito salad
directions: Cook and drain ground beef; mix with lettuce, tomatoes, onion and black olives in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Add avocados and Fritos and stir in melted Cheez Whiz.
Top with jalapeno peppers.

title: dill dip for vegetables
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill for 4 hours.

title: yam 'n apple creation
directions: Parboil yams, peel and cut into pieces.
Peel apples and dice. Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan.
Add boiling water and butter.
Stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil. Butter casserole dish and place yams and apples in casserole in layers.
Pour sauce over.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 12.

title: sally lunn
directions: Put in a mixing bowl the milk and yeast. Let stand 5 minutes. Stir. Add the butter or oil, salt and eggs. Beat with a strong rotary beater or electric mixer. Gradually add the flour. Leave the mixture in the bowl and let rise until very light and about double in size. Spoon into a buttered 10-inch angel cake pan or 2 dozen 2-inch muffin pans. Let rise about 1 hour. Bake about 50 minutes at 350° in a large pan or 20 minutes at 425° in muffin pans.

title: frozen coffee cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Fold in 2 cups raw apples or fresh or frozen blueberries.
Place in 2 (8 or 9-inch) pans.

title: home style skillet chops
directions: Brown chops in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Season with salt and pepper.
Top chops with onion slices, cover.
Cook over low heat 30 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook uncovered 15 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: mom's apple crisp
directions: Peel, core and slice apples. Place in an 8 x 8-inch baking dish and dot with the butter. Combine the next 5 ingredients together and combine like pastry, with 2 knives. Do not let it become oily. Crumble topping over apples. Bake at 375° for 30-40 minutes until apples are done. Serve hot or cold with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: soy tex(numeat)
directions: Mix together and put into cans up to 1-inch from the top. Cover.
Place cans in pan and fill pan with boiling water.
Place in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together eggs, shortening, sugar, vanilla and grated zucchini.
Add dry ingredients; nuts and chips optional.
Pour into loaf pans.
Makes two large loaves.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients in a 13 x 8 x 2 1/2-inch casserole dish.
Top with chicken pieces.
Dot well with margarine. Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover with aluminum foil (this is a must). Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove foil and serve a hearty main course for 8.

title: picnic bean dish
directions: In a large pan (suitable for stovetop and oven), brown the ground chuck, then drain the excess fat.
Add the onion and celery.
Cook until tender.
Stir in soup, tomato paste and catsup and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add all remaining ingredients and stir well.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour.
Makes approximately 25 servings.

title: polish poppy seed cake
directions: Soak poppy seed overnight in scalded milk.
Cream sugar and shortening until smooth.
Add beaten egg yolk.
Add poppy seed mixture alternately with sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in the beaten egg whites.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cooled completely.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces and put into bottom of greased casserole dish.
Mix soup and sour cream; spread over chicken.
Melt margarine and add crushed crackers.
Sprinkle over soup and sour cream mixture.
Sprinkle poppy seed on top.
Bake at 325° for about 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of mushroom

title: taco salad
directions: Brown beef; slightly crush tortilla chips.
Mix together all ingredients except dressing.
Toss well.
Add dressing and mix thoroughly.
Serve immediately.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix and place in casserole dish.
Top with cheese and potato chips.
Cook at 350° until bubbly.

title: healthy muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, mix pineapple, carrots, banana and prunes.
Add vanilla and cinnamon.
Add oil and egg. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Fill lined paper cups in a muffin tin.
Bake for 10 to 15 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool.
Remove and store in refrigerator.
Makes 12 large muffins.
You may add 1/2 cup raisins for variety.

title: orange drop cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Then add rest of ingredients in order given.
Drop by spoonfuls on cookie sheet and bake in a moderate oven for 12-15 minutes.
When cool, add orange icing made with 1 Tbsp. butter, 1 tsp. orange rind, 1 c. powdered sugar, and enough orange juice to make consistency for spreading.
Spread a small amount of icing on each cookie and serve.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine in 2-quart saucepan.
Add sifted sugar.
Stir until smooth.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook over low heat.
Once heated through, let simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve warm over ice cream.

title: blueberry angel dessert
directions: Cream softened cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Cut cake into 1-inch squared and fold into mixture.
Put into 9 x 13 dish.
Top with pie filling.
Chill at least 2 hours.

title: tom sawyer's "whitewash that sticks"
directions: Take some macaroni.
You boil the macaroni in water.
Drain the water.
You put onion in it and pickles in it and cheese and Miracle Whip and then you stir it, then you eat it.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Dissolve seasonings in oil and vinegar; stir.
Pour over black-eyed peas.
Add other ingredients.
Stir carefully.
Mix well and refrigerate.
Allow salad to marinate for several hours.

title: yellow coconut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Beat with electric beater. Bake according to directions on cake mix.
Frost with white frosting and decorate with coconut on top.
(Delicious!)

title: holiday herb cheese spread
directions: With electric mixer, beat together cream cheese and butter until fluffy.
Add remaining ingredients except bell pepper.
Beat well.
Place a piece of plastic wrap on small cookie sheet.
Spoon mixture onto plastic wrap to form a log, about 3-inches thick and 12-inches long.
Fold plastic over cheese.
Refrigerate until firm (overnight).
Unwrap cheese log.
Bend 1/3 of log to form a candy cane shape.
Place on serving plate.
Decorate with bell peppers to form stripes.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray rectangular casserole dish with Pam. Dip chicken in melted butter and coat with combined remaining ingredients.
Place in pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix with next 3 ingredients.
Broccoli should be thawed.
Mix all together, then add muffin mix.
Makes 12 muffins. Grease muffin pan. Muffins will be moist.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: salmon log
directions: Drain salmon.
Remove skin and bones.
Add all ingredients together in a small bowl.
Mix well.
Shape into log.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Chill and serve with crackers or raw veggies.

title: winter fruit compote
directions: Drain well all fruit; mix together. Butter a casserole and pour in fruit.
Combine brown sugar and crumbs; sprinkle generously on top. Sprinkle juice of lemon and orange and bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Serve warm or cold, with or without whipped cream.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: potato casserole
directions: Melt margarine into 13 x 9-inch glass dish or pan.
Spread potatoes over the margarine.
Mix together in a bowl the sour cream, soup, onion, salt and pepper.
Spread mixture over potatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: Southern Style frozen hash brown potatoes

title: crunchy stir-fry
directions: Pour oil in skillet or wok and preheat to 350°.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce and water in small bowl; set aside.
Add celery to skillet and stir-fry 1 minute; push to side.
Stir-fry onion 1 minute; push to side.
Add mushrooms; stir-fry 1 minute. Combine with onion and celery.
Stir in cornstarch mixture.
Cook and stir constantly until liquid is thickened, about 2 minutes. Reduce heat to 250°.
Add water chestnuts and turkey and stir gently.
Heat about 3 minutes.
Stir in almonds.
Serve over chow mein noodles.
Serves 6.

title: golden shrimp or ham casserole
directions: About 1 hour before serving, preheat oven to 375°.
In large saucepan over medium heat, heat undiluted soup, milk, sherry, parsley, curry powder and salt until soup starts to boil, stirring occasionally.
In greased 2-quart shallow casserole, combine soup mixture, shrimp (or ham), macaroni and peas.
Bake 55 minutes or until shrimp is pink and tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: vegetarian stuffed shells
directions: Cook the stuffing shells until tender.
Stuff with crumbled tofu seasoned with Mozzarella, yeast, Vegesal and herbs.
Put shells into a baking dish lined with tomato sauce.
Top with additional cheese and sauce.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken breast in water until done.
Mix soup, sour cream, and water.
Pour over chopped chicken.

title: corn fritters
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Drop spoonfuls of batter into fat in hot frying pan.
Brown both sides.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Wash and drain lettuce; tear into pieces in a large Tupperware bowl.
Break up cauliflower (small pieces).
Make layers. Sprinkle on cheese.
Crumble bacon, then green onion.
Last spread mayo on.
Then sprinkle sugar on top.
Spread mayo like cake icing.
Refrigerate with lid for
8 to 12 hours before serving. Toss before serving (about 15 minutes).

title: mama iris' pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and shortening until creamy and smooth.
Add sugar; cream with margarine and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Measure dry ingredients; sift together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Add vanilla and other flavorings. Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° until done, approximately 1 hour to 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: tuna rice casserole
directions: Add to the cooked rice the fish, lemon juice, butter, and egg yolks which have been mixed together. Season to taste with salt and pepper, then fold in the egg whites which have been beaten stiff but not dry. Put into a buttered casserole dish, and cover the top with buttered crumbs.

title: chocolate angel dessert
directions: Divide cake cubes and raspberries evenly among 7 dessert dishes or layer in an 8-inch square pan.
Pour milk and vanilla into medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with wire whisk until well blended.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fold in Cool Whip. Spoon into dessert dishes.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Diabetic Exchange Per Serving:
1 starch and 1/2 fat.

title: pat's favorite casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, sugar and tomato sauce and cook for 15 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain. Mix with butter; add onion, sour cream and softened cream cheese. In a 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan, place a layer of noodle mix, then meat mixture, then grated cheese.
Repeat once more and end with grated cheese.
Cook uncovered for about 20 minutes, at 350°.

title: squash patties
directions: Cook squash until done in salted water; drain well.
Smash squash; drain again.
Add crackers, coarsely crumbled, a few at a time until mixture resembles a mush consistency.
Add onion, egg and garlic salt to taste.
Heat oil in frypan on medium heat.
Fry spoonful of mixture as you would a pancake.
Patties will be crisp golden brown on both sides.
Can be served as an appetizer or side dish.

title: ham, broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: In a frying pan, saute onion in oil with fresh garlic to taste (or garlic powder) until soft.
Slice and peel eggplant and then cube and place into pan.
Cover.
Let cook for about fifteen minutes, adding a little water, if necessary.
Check periodically until eggplant becomes soft and mushy.
Stir occasionally until consistency is right.
Beat one egg and when eggplant is soft enough, turn up heat slightly and pour in egg, whipping up mixture until binding takes place.
Chill and serve with olives on bed of lettuce with tomato or on toast.

title: 15 minute meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients together; pack mixture level into greased muffin pans.
Bake 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: garlic soup(sopa de ajo)
directions: Cook and stir garlic in oil in a 3-quart saucepan until brown. Add the bread and cook, stirring, until lightly browned.
Stir in chicken broth, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 20 minutes.
Stir about half of the hot mixture very gradually into the egg.
Blend into hot mixture in saucepan; boil and stir 1 minute.
Garnish as desired.
Yields 4 cups.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt butter, remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Gradually add sugar until it looks crumbly.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Melt chocolate, remove form heat, then roll balls in it and drop on foil.

title: triple fill cake
directions: ortening as for pie dough.
Beat together last three ingredients, then mix with first mixture.
Divide into 3 parts. Roll out dough layers to fit 11 x 16-inch greased pan.
Arrange as follows:
layer dough, layer nut filling, layer dough, layer apricot filling, layer dough, meringue, sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: sausage balls
directions: After sausage is soft enough, mix together with biscuit mix, flour and cheese.
Knead together and make into small balls.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cream cheese delight
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, spread 1 can of crescent rolls.
Cream cheese, sugar and vanilla.
Spread mixture on top of crescent rolls.
Top mixture with second can of rolls.
Poke hole in top layer.
Melt margarine and pour over top layer.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt connie's homemade biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix flour, sugar and grate in margarine (just enough to even out; do not overmix).
Add buttermilk to mixture.
Roll out dough on flour surface one time (do not knead or overwork dough).
Shape biscuits or use cookie cutter.
Place on greased pan and bake for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening until fluffy. Add eggs and milk. Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: strawberry butter
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Use to spread on strawberry bread.

title: cinnamon sticks
directions: Cream butter and sugar and add egg yolk.
Mix well.
Sift cinnamon with flour and add.
Then pat as thin as possible on nongreased cookie sheets.
Rub unbeaten egg white onto dough and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cut in strips.
Remove from heat while hot!

title: old fashioned cream pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into an unbaked pie crust and bake 40 minutes in 350° oven.
May add a spice on top like nutmeg or cinnamon to taste.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: In a greased 9	x 13-inch glass baking pan add rhubarb. Shake dry jello over
rhubarb;
add drained pineapple. Add dry cake mix (to pineapple juice,
add
water to make 1 cup).
Cut margarine into thin slices
and lay margarine slices over cake mix.
Pour juice over all.
Add
nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes. Cool slightly. Serve with Cool Whip.

title: tomato and veggie pie
directions: In a frying pan, melt butter and saute onion, garlic, squash and zucchini. Add salt and pepper to taste. In the meantime, heat pie shell until about half way cooked. When the ingredients in the frying pan have been sauteed, layer them into the bottom of the pie shell. Add a generous layer of sliced tomatoes and sprinkle with the grated cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes. Hint: You may want to carefully tilt the pie shell after about 15 minutes of baking to let some of the water from the vegetables drain off. The pie freezes well and makes a great wintertime treat when you are craving fresh tomatoes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well and bake in loaf pan for approximately 40 minutes at 350°.

title: clam chowder
directions: Cook carrots, potatoes and celery in pan.
Melt butter; add cornstarch and flour.
Add milk and thicken.
Gradually add hard-boiled eggs and clams; add to the cooked vegetables.
Simmer.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with beaten egg yolks and buttermilk.
Add vanilla, bananas and nuts and fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake in a large, greased Bundt pan at 325°.

title: granny's pound cake
directions: Cream shortenings together.
Add sugar and cream together.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add milk and dry ingredients alternately, starting and ending with the milk.
Add flavoring.
Put in greased and floured pound cake pan.
Cook one hour and 45 minutes at 275°.

title: fat-free oatmeal cookies
directions: In large bowl combine flour, oatmeal, sugar, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in egg whites, corn syrup and vanilla.
Mix until well blended.
Add raisins (batter will be stiff).
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet greased with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake for 10 minutes at 375°.
Do not overbake.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 30 cookies.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients. In separate bowl, mix next 3 minutes in order. Pour over salad. Chill for several hours before serving.

title: harvey wallbanger cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat 4 minutes at medium speed. Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Poke holes in cake and pour warm glaze over it.

title: easy vegetable soup
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot.
Sprinkle Mrs.
Dash over the top and season to taste.
Heat on high for most of the day and low 1 hour before serving.
Cook at least 6 hours.
Stir every so often.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: In oleo, saute onions, celery and mushrooms until soft.
Set aside.
Heat soup and Cheez Whiz together on low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Add cooked rice and broccoli to celery mixture. Then add soup/cheese and seasoning.
To taste, use Tony Chachere's. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle fried onions on top 5 minutes before casserole is done.

title: beau's cheese dip
directions: Mix ingredients together, adding Velveeta cheese last.
Cook about 2 hours on low in crock-pot.

title: low-fat rigatoni casserole
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, saute ground turkey, onion and garlic until turkey is browned.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and pepper.
Reduce heat; simmer 10 minutes.
In bowl, combine Ricotta cheese, skim milk and salt.
Add rigatoni; toss to coat well.
Spoon half the rigatoni mixture into an 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Top with half the Mozzarella cheese and half the sauce; repeat.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes or until heated thoroughly.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Fry bacon and crumble.
Brown onions.
Pour Cheez Whiz, onions and bacon over green beans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: 1-2-3 peanut butter cookie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend peanut butter, shortening, sugar and water; stir until smooth.
Stir in Bisquick.
Drop by teaspoons onto lightly greased baking sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in Bisquick.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 6 1/2 dozen.

title: conch fritters
directions: Chop or grind conch, green pepper and onion.
Add flour, unbeaten egg and lime juice and mix.
Drop by spoonful into hot fat and fry until golden brown.
Enjoy.

title: coca-cola ham
directions: Place ham in roasting pan. Score top of ham. Pour Coke on top. Rub brown sugar on outside of ham. Place in 300° oven. Bake for 3 hours, basting with Coke in the bottom of pan every 30 minutes. During last hour of baking, place pineapple slices on top. Slice and enjoy. This is the juiciest ham recipe you may ever try.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a skillet, brown meat and onion. Layer meat mixture, zucchini, seasoning, tomato paste, mushrooms and rice in large baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before serving.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Shake chicken pieces in bag with cornstarch until coated.
Fry in oil until medium brown.
Remove chicken.
Put pineapple chunks, onions, celery and green peppers in deep Dutch oven or roaster. Mix remaining frying oil with brown sugar, soy sauce and ginger. Pour over vegetables.
Add chicken.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes or until tender.
Lightly mix so that chicken will be under vegetables and cornstarch will cook into sauce.
Cook until thickened.
Serves 10.

title: easy spoon bread
directions: Mix sugar, salt and corn meal.
Add butter and pour boiling water over all.
Beat eggs with baking powder until light and fluffy, then add to corn meal mixture.
Stir in hot milk.
Pour into a greased baking dish.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add tomato sauce, carrots, potato soup, onion and Mrs. Dash; mix well.
Have the pie crust at room temperature.
