Place 1 crust in large pie pan.
Pour in mixture. Place second pie crust on top.
Seal and crimp the edges with your fingers.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until crust is brown.

title: porcupines(or rice and meat balls)
directions: Mix rice with ground beef, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 cup tomato juice or stewed tomatoes.
Shape into balls, size of English walnuts.
Place in skillet and brown (until meat is done).
Remove from skillet; place in baking dish.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix all together. Pour in tube pan. Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: healthy vegetable soup
directions: Peel potatoes and carrots.
Combine first 7 ingredients in saucepan and bring to a boil over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat, cover saucepan and simmer 10-15 minutes.
Remove from heat and add spinach.
Transfer mixture to a blender and mix well.
Return soup to saucepan.
Add sour cream and stir until hot.
Serve with croutons.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and save juice.
Add grated cheese to drained pineapple.
In another bowl, sift flour and add sugar.
Mix with pineapple juice.
Pour over pineapple, stir well.
Spoon into a 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Crush Ritz crackers and combine with butter.
Spread over top of mixture in the casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mustard custard
directions: Place all ingredients in a 2-quart glass dish and beat slightly with wire whisk.
Cook for 1 1/2 minutes on medium-high heat.
Stir well.
Cook 1 1/2 minutes and beat with whisk.
If slightly thickened, it is done.
Cool slightly and add equal amounts of mayonnaise.
More mayonnaise may be added if desired. This is great for ham sandwiches.

title: banana muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients.
Stir just until moistened.
Spoon batter into greased muffin pans, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.

title: cucumber pickles
directions: Wash and dry cucumbers. Slice. Add lime to water in non-aluminum pan, add cucumbers. Soak 24 hours. Remove from solution. Rinse 4 times 1 hour apart.

title: herbed spinach bake
directions: Cook and drain spinach; mix with rest of ingredients.
Pour mixture into 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 20 to 25 minutes or until knife inserted halfway between center and edge comes out clean.
Cut into squares.
Serves 6. May be prepared ahead and baked at the last minute.

title: apple au flauf
directions: Melt the oleo in an 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Add the brown sugar and apples.
Bake in a 350° oven until soft.

title: vegetable delight
directions: Spread crescent rolls on large cookie sheet and bake at 350° until crisp.
Cool.
Mix the cream cheese and salad dressing and put on rolls.
Chop vegetables (broccoli, cauliflower, radishes, carrots, green peppers, celery, etc.) on top.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Empty can of chili into crock-pot on high setting.
Slice cheese and add to chili.
Stir occasionally until cheese is completely melted.
Turn to low setting.
Great with nacho chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Prepare rice according to directions. Add margarine. Stir until melted.
Add corn and soup. Combine grated cheese with mixture.
Spoon into a 10 x 13-inch casserole dish which has been buttered or sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove from oven.
Sprinkle some grated cheese and paprika for color on top.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and cool for 2 hours.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Fry meatballs in skillet until done.
Add 1 large can of tomato puree.
Put in crock-pot and cook for 2 to 3 hours.

title: strawberry punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake in 8 or 9-inch round pan. Cool.
Cut one layer of cake into small pieces; place in bottom of punch bowl.
Prepare pudding.
If cooked, let cool first.
Cover cake pieces with 1 package of pudding, 1/2 of the pineapple, 1 package strawberries, one or two bananas and 8 ounces whipped topping.
Repeat layers with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While cake is still hot, spread on one jar marshmallow cream.
Let cool completely before frosting with frosting made from last 4 ingredients.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt caramels and milk over
medium-low heat.
Add nuts and drop by teaspoonfuls onto
greased cookie sheet.
Freeze 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, Karo and salt.
Microwave on High 5 minutes.
Add peanuts; microwave on High 4 minutes.
Add vanilla.
Add teaspoon butter and teaspoon of soda and stir until all melts.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool; break up and serve.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix together and pour in graham cracker crust.
Chill until served.
Makes 2 pies.

title: anniversary cake
directions: Bake cake mix.
Spread pineapple over top of cake.
Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese together.
Spread on top of pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip and grated coconut.

title: cherry chocolate pudding
directions: Pour pudding into a bowl.
Add the milk; mix well.
Add cherry pie filling to pudding; mix together.
Pudding will thicken.
Chill and serve.
Serves 12.

title: parslow's devil's food cake
directions: Combine cake flour, sugar, cocoa, salt, Crisco and 3/4 cup buttermilk in bowl.
Mix thoroughly at medium speed for 2 minutes. Stir in soda and baking powder.
Add 1/2 cup buttermilk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly at medium speed for an additional 2 minutes.
Bake in greased and floured 9-inch round cake pans for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: lamb stew
directions: Coat lamb pieces with a mixture of flour, salt and pepper. Heat olive oil in large skillet; add lamb and brown evenly on all sides.
Add beef broth slowly, then stir in green peppers, marjoram and garlic.
Cover and cook over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, onion and celery.
Cook covered about 10 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Mix in tomatoes and olives and heat thoroughly.
If a thicker stew is desired blend in a mixture of seasoned flour and water prior to adding tomatoes and olives. Bring to a boil and cook about 2 minutes longer, then add tomatoes and olives.

title: crab dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and top with 1/3 cup almond slices. Bake in casserole dish at 375° for 15 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate berry trifle
directions: Pour milk into large bowl.
Add pudding mixes.
Beat with wire whisk 2 min. or until well blended.
Gently stir in 1 c. whipped topping.
Place 1/2 the brownie cubes in 2-qt. serving bowl. Top with 1/2 each of the pudding mixture, raspberries and remaining whipped topping.
Repeat layers.
Refrigerate 1 hr. or until ready to serve.
Makes 12 servings.

title: walnuts and rice
directions: The walnuts represent the things God would have us do, and the rice represents the fun things we like to do.
If you pour the rice into the jar first, the walnuts will not fit.
If you put the walnuts in the jar first, the rice poured over fits just fine. The lesson is if we put time with and for God before time for other things, we'll have plenty of time for both.
If, however, we put things we want to do first, we'll never fit time for God into our lives.

title: diet italian spaghetti
directions: Combine onion and ground beef.
Place in nonstick skillet and brown, draining off fat as it accumulates.
Add tomato paste, water, spices, herbs and tomatoes.
Simmer 1 or more hours, adding more water if needed.
Serve 1/2 cup sauce over 1/2 cup cooked spaghetti.

title: creamy rice and tomatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger meat and drain fat.
Add butter and chopped onion and bell peppers.
Let simmer until onion
and bell peppers are soft, then add the other ingredients in a large casserole dish and bake for one hour in a 250° oven.
This recipe is also good in a crock-pot, just cook until you're ready to eat.

title: pop candy
directions: In a heavy saucepan, combine maple syrup, butter and nutmeg, boiling until mixture reaches 270° on a candy thermometer (soft crack stage), stirring occasionally.
Mix popcorn, almonds and pecans.
Dribble syrup mixture onto popcorn and nut mixture until well covered.
May be made into bite-size popcorn balls and wrapped in wax paper or pressed into a large oiled pan and broken into smaller pieces when hardened.
Keep in a container with a tight lid.
Makes 7 to 9 balls.

title: buttermilk pie(9-inch)
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add flour, buttermilk and vanilla. Add eggs.
Beat well.
Pour into prepared pie crust.
Bake until firm at 350°.

title: quick chili
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add tomato sauce, beans and chili powder.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix well.
Add milk, a little at a time.
Make stiff dough. Roll out on a floured wax paper, very thin.
Put in a greased pan. Trim edges off.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: toffee cookie bars
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and vanilla.
Beat. Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Spread on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: cake frosting(good on wedding cake)
directions: Cook flour and milk together until it forms a paste.
Cool. Add Crisco and oleo; beat well.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine dry jello, cheese and mayonnaise.
Add hot water and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple with juice.
If desired, add nuts.
Pour mixture into mold and place in refrigerator.

title: marinated chicken wings
directions: Cut chicken wings in two pieces and discard end piece.
Mix ginger, soy sauce, sugar, vinegar and garlic powder.
Pour over chicken and marinate overnight.
Then place chicken in large metal pan(s) in single layer.
Baste with leftover marinade.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 45 minutes.
Baste every 15 minutes until done.
Yields 25 to 30 servings.

title: old fashioned stack cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and shortening.
Add egg; beat well. Stir in molasses.
Sift and add alternately with buttermilk the flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg, allspice and salt. Add additional flour to make dough stiff enough to handle.
Knead dough on a floured board.
Divide into 5 portions.
Pat each portion into greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 370° for about 10 minutes.
Stack layers with fruit preserves, such as apple butter, and serve.

title: baked sweet potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes
well.
Let
dry
and
grease thoroughly. Place in baking pan and bake in hot oven at 350° for 1 hour or until potatoes are
tender.
Serves 4.
Each potato is considered a serving.
So more or less potatoes may be used.

title: stuffed peppers
directions: Mix hamburger, rice, crackers, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can of tomato sauce together.
Cut bell peppers in half.
Stuf with hamburger mixture.
Cover with tomato sauce and a little water. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: five hour stew
directions: Combine beef, celery, onions, carrots, potatoes, tapioca, tomato juice, bread, sugar, bay leaves, salt and pepper in 2-quart baking dish; mix well.
Bake at 250° for 5 hours.
Remove bay leaves.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: party punch
directions: Combine Hi-C and sherbet.
Gradually stir in ginger ale. Serve over an ice ring.
Makes 12 to 16 servings.

title: forgotten cake
directions: Beat ingredients
until
stiff.
Set oven to 450°.
Get hot! Put cake
in
ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan and place in hot oven. Turn
off oven and let bake overnight.
Use your favorite filling with Cool Whip topping.

title: baked sandwiches for 8
directions: Marinate the meat for 1 hour, then drain in a colander. Place on trays to dry. For faster drying, do not overlap the meat on the trays and turn the meat over at least once during the drying period. Dry at 145° for 8 to 10 hours. It is ready when it bends like a green willow without breaking. Long term storage should be in the refrigerator.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream shortening, butter and sugar until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Sift flour and dry ingredients together 3 times.
Add vanilla to milk.
Add flour and alternately blend well.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Melt shortening and cocoa.
Then add sugar, eggs (one at a time) plus salt and vanilla.
Then add nuts and flour. Cook at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: stuffed burger bundles
directions: Prepare stuffing according to package directions.
Set aside. Combine evaporated milk and meat.
Divide into 5 patties on waxed paper.
Pat each to 6-inch circles.
Put 1/4 cup stuffing in center of each patty.
Draw meat over stuffing and seal.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients. Pour over meat.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 5 servings.

title: cracker snacks
directions: Place in large airtight container.

title: cherry chocolate cake
directions: Follow directions on cake mix.
Use butter instead of oil. Mix at low speed for proper time.
Fold in cherry pie filling. Bake in sheet pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Frost with chocolate icing; cut into squares.
Top each square with a cherry with a stem.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Add 1 cup flour and the baking powder; beat well.
Add 3 eggs and the vanilla; beat well.
Add 1 cup flour and 3 more eggs; beat well.
Add 1 cup flour; beat well.
Put into a greased tube pan. Bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Let the cake cool for an hour on a rack, then remove from the pan.

title: strawberry-spinach salad
directions: Remove stems from spinach; wash leaves thoroughly and pat dry. Tear into bite size pieces.
Combine spinach, strawberries and almonds in a large bowl; cover and chill.
Just before serving, pour Poppy Seed Dressing over salad; toss gently.
Yield:
12 to 16 servings.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cherry Jell-O and boiling water.
Chill.
(Do not let Jell-O jell.)
Combine Jell-O with other ingredients and chill.

title: corn flake cookies
directions: Melt sugar in syrup over low heat.
Add peanut butter and cook until mixture is smooth.
Pour over corn flakes; mix well.
Pour into buttered dish; let get firm.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a 10 inch Bundt pan. Sift together flour, baking powder, and salt.
Set aside. In a large bowl, cream butter, cream cheese and sugar until light and fluffy.

title: golden peach cobbler
directions: Drain peaches, reserving 1 cup syrup.
Combine sugar, flour, nutmeg and salt; add reserved syrup.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens; add next 4 ingredients, then peaches.
Put in baking pan, top with crust, then sprinkle with sugar.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 40 to 45 minutes.
If cobbler browns too quickly, cover with foil.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Add broccoli.
Cook rice according to directions.
Add soup and cheese to rice.
Mix together and cook for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Uncover for the last 15 minutes.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello and boiling water and add blueberries, juice and pineapple.
Jell and when set add topping.

title: pepperoni squares
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in an 8 x 8-inch greased pan at 400° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm or cooled. When doubling recipe, bake the same amount of time.

title: hot crab dip
directions: Cream together cream cheese and cream.
Lightly brown almonds in butter.
Mix together almonds, onions, cream cheese mixture, salt, pepper and horseradish. Put into greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with crackers or party breads.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Bone and cut into cubes.
Mix together flour, milk and margarine.
Mix together soup and broth.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Spread Veg-All over chicken.
Pour soup over all, then pour batter over this.
Bake, until brown on
top, at 400°.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush vanilla wafers and place in a large bowl.
Add coconut, raisins and pecans.
Mix well.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over mixture and mix thoroughly with hands until it begins to form a ball. Press firmly into pan.
Decorate top with candied cherries.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.

title: pork shoulder to ham
directions: Boil pork slowly in water 1 hour.
Pour off liquid.
Add 3 cups water, brown sugar, vinegar, cloves and mustard.
Boil slowly about 1 hour.
Let stand in mixture several hours or overnight. Slice.

title: richard's lasagne
directions: Saute onions and garlic in 2 tablespoons of the oil in large heavy saucepan for 5 minutes.
Stir in beef and cook over medium heat until browned.
Add salt, tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, basil, oregano, sugar and parsley flakes. Bring sauce to a boil; simmer for 45 minutes.

title: party tetrazzini
directions: In a saucepan, cook the onion, celery and garlic in margarine until tender. Blend in soup, water, cheese, sherry, parsley and pimento. Cook over low heat until cheese is melted.
Stir often. Add meat or shrimp and heat for a few minutes.
Pour over spaghetti and mix.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.

title: nirmit's fried won tons
directions: Blend chicken (deboned) in blender.
Mix with all seasonings, blending altogether.
Put 1 teaspoon chicken in middle of each won ton wrapper; deep fry until golden brown.
Seal the wrappers (with chicken in them) with water (make sure).
Eat with sweet and sour sauce.

title: raspberry dessert
directions: Stir raspberries, water, cornstarch and sugar over medium heat until thick and clear.
Remove from heat and add extract.
Pour into stemmed dishes and chill.
Serve topped with whipped cream and a sprinkle of almonds.
Serves 4.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch. Gradually stir in milk. Cook and stir over medium heat until bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes.

Remove from heat. Stir small amount hot mixture into yolks; immediately return to hot mixture. Cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Add 1/2 cup coconut and stir. Pour into cooked pastry shell. Top with meringue.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup coconut and bake until golden.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Blend all together well.
Roll dough in balls and roll in sugar.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: cappuccino mix
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Store in an airtight container.
To prepare one serving, add 3 tablespoons mix to 6 ounces hot water.
Stir well.
Yield:
3 cups dry mix.

title: chicken barbecue sauce(makes 3 cups)
directions: In a large mixing bowl, beat the egg, then add the oil and beat again.
Add salt, poultry seasoning and pepper.
Pour into jar, cover and refrigerate.
The sauce will keep for several weeks.
Don't let it become contaminated with chicken before using.
This mixture is enough to use for 10 chicken halves. Makes 3 cups.

title: catalina salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together and shake.

title: holiday pecan pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube or Bundt pan.
In large mixer bowl, beat shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until smooth. Meanwhile, sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg.
Add to sugar mixture alternately with sour cream and milk, beginning and ending with flour.
Beat just until blended.
Fold in pecans.
Turn into prepared pan and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done. Cool in pan 15 minutes.
Then turn out on a wire rack and finish cooling.
Pour glaze over cake and decorate with pecan halves.

title: crustless quiche lorraine
directions: Cook bacon in microwave oven between layers of paper toweling about 8 to 10 minutes. Drain well and crumble bacon.
Sprinkle cheese, bacon and onion in a 9-inch glass pie plate bottom.
Beat remaining ingredients with a rotary beater until well blended. Pour over bacon-cheese-onion mixture.
Bake in microwave for 9 minutes. Turn dish 1/4 turn every 3 minutes of cooking time. Allow to stand for 10 minutes for center to finish cooking before cutting.
Serves 6.

title: shrimp butter
directions: Put all ingredients into a bowl and mix well by hand or with an electric mixer.
Place into a mold or a small bowl which has been rinsed out in cold water or lightly buttered.
Chill.
Unmold on platter and surround with crackers or Melba toast.
Garnish with parsley or watercress if desired.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter in medium bowl.
Stir in crushed pretzels and sugar.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Microwave 3 minutes or bake 5 to 10 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: easy jello
directions: Mix jello with hot water as directed on package.
While hot, add pineapple and cream cheese.
Stir and pour into cake pan type container.
Place in fridge to set.
It's easy and it's good!

title: squash dressing
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into dish and bake at 350° until done.

title: carrot pecan crunch pie
directions: Cook carrots until tender (30 minutes); drain.
Puree in blender until smooth.
Combine eggs, sweetened condensed milk, pie spice and salt in bowl.
Add carrots.
Mix well and turn into pastry shell.
Mix brown sugar and butter; stir in pecans. Sprinkle evenly over pie.
Cover edge of pie with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Remove foil.
Bake additional 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.
Very good; tastes like pumpkin pie.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix together soups, 1/2 cup bean juice and cheese.
Layer this mixture with green beans and water chestnuts.
Cook at 375° until bubbly all over.
Put onion rings over top and cook until brown. Bake in an ovenproof casserole dish.
Serve.

title: whipped cake icing
directions: Beat sugar and shortening until creamy.
Beat flour and milk into paste.
(Important: Heat flour and milk just enough until lukewarm, not hot.)
Add flour and milk paste to sugar and Crisco. Add vanilla.
Beat well.

title: mark's strawberry cake
directions: Mix the boiling water into jello.
Mix in frozen strawberries; mix well.
Put in refrigerator until barely lumpy.
Tear cake into small pieces.
Put half of it in a 13 x 9-inch pan or serving dish.
Whip cream (or use Cool Whip) and fold into strawberry mixture.
Pour half of mixture over cake, then the other half of cake on top and the rest of strawberry mixture on top of it.

title: apple-oatmeal cookies(makes about 6 dozen cookies)
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and spices.
Cream butter and sugars.
Beat in eggs and orange rind gradually.
Add flour mixture and mix well.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by level tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 17 minutes.
Cool and store between layers of waxed paper in tightly covered tin box.

title: meringue pie topping
directions: In electric mixer, beat egg whites on high for about 3 to 4 minutes.
Gradually add sugar.
Beat on high, stirring often, until stiff peaks form.
Add vanilla the last few minutes.
Spread onto cream pie tops.
Will top 2 pies.
Bake in a 350° oven until peaks are browned.

title: meat balls
directions: Beat eggs with 2 tablespoons water.
Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
(Meat should be moist.
If too dry, add a little more milk or water.)
Form meat balls to desired size. Place on cookie pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seafood fettucine
directions: Melt butter in a skillet.
Saute onion in butter.
Add garlic powder.
Add shrimp and cook until pink.
Add crab meat and mushrooms and heat.
Remove from heat.
Add cooked fettucine noodles; stir well and place in a casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with grated Italian cheese and heat until cheese is melted.

title: applesauce and oatmeal bars
directions: Mix flour, sugar and shortening together.
Add oats.
In 8 x 8-inch pan, put half of the mixture and pat down with your hands. Pour applesauce over the top of the mixture, staying about 1/2-inch from sides.
Cover with remaining oat mixture and pat firmly.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes and then enjoy!

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil boned chicken breasts in salt water until tender (done). Cut up into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
Thaw frozen broccoli and cook 5 minutes or use fresh broccoli, cooked until tender.
Grease baking dish.
Lay broccoli, then chicken.
Make a sauce with soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder, mixed together.
Add butter to bread crumbs.
Pour sauce over chicken, then bread cubes. Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° until melted, approximately 30 or 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Spread the refried beans on the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Mash the avocados, onion, lemon juice and hot sauce together; spread on top of beans.
Blend together the taco seasoning mix and sour cream; spread on top.
Sprinkle with lettuce, olives, tomatoes and cheese.
Chill for 1 hour.
Serve with taco chips.

title: the bramble inn quiche
directions: Saute vegetables in oil until zucchini is tender-crisp.
Cool. Beat eggs and cream.
Add cheeses, bread, salt and pepper. Blend.
Add vegetables; mix well.
Pour into 10-inch spring-form pan (or 2 shallow quiche pans or pie plates). Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.
Cool 20 minutes.

title: scones(irish soda biscuits)
directions: Preheat oven to 350° to 375°.
In large mixing bowl, combine 3 3/4 cups of flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Use pastry blender to cut in Crisco until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Gradually add buttermilk, using a spoon to blend in buttermilk and when mixture is a bit dry, knead with your hands. Add raisins and stir to combine.
Sprinkle one tablespoon of flour on work surface and turn dough out onto floured surface; sprinkle remaining tablespoon of flour over dough.
Take half of batter and roll out with rolling pin.
It should be rolled out round and about 1/4-inch thick.
Then with sharp knife, cut into triangles. Put them on floured cookie sheet.
Bake approximately 25 minutes or until brown.
Before putting in oven, brush a little buttermilk on top of scones.
Thicker they are, the higher scones will rise. Cool on wire rack.

title: dump cake
directions: Butter grease a 9 x 13 inch cake pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 box dry cake mix into pan.
Add cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple. Sprinkle the rest of dry cake mix over cherry pie filling and pineapple.
Cut 1 1/2 stick margarine over mix.
Then add nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 30-40 minutes.
For fewer calories, use light cherry pie filling.

title: california tamale pie
directions: Add to meat mixture and mix.
Cook in crock-pot on high for 4 to 6 hours or on low all day.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mince onion fine.
Mix all ingredients together well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls in deep fat fryer.
Fry until golden brown.

title: horseradish mustard
directions: Combine all ingredients; cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Serve with beef.
Yield: 1 cup.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute squash and onions until slightly tender.
Mix together mayonnaise, sour cream and cream of mushroom.
In a casserole dish layer squash and onions, sour cream mixture and cheese.
Repeat layers topping with cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake, covered, at 350° for approximately 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, the last 10 minutes to brown the bread crumbs.

title: green punch
directions: Mix and chill everything except ginger ale.
Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll in crumbs. Serve with Sociables crackers.

title: nina's pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Alternate dry ingredients with flavorings and milk.
Start in cold oven. Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Step 1:
Mix Jell-O by box directions (less 1 cup water). Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Chill until it begins to thicken. Add pineapple and let mixture congeal.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and stir in tomatoes, mixing well.
Add the rest of ingredients.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to low and simmer for 2 hours (a soup bone may be added for extra flavor).

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook together chicken broth, mushrooms and onion.
Pour over cooked spaghetti in casserole dish. Warm cream of mushroom soup and add cooked chicken.
Pour over spaghetti and other ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese over the top. Bake at 375° to heat all the way.

title: pineapple zucchini bread
directions: Beat first 4 ingredients together, then add next 2 ingredients.
Sift together remaining ingredients and beat into the liquid.
Bake muffins for 30 minutes at 350°.
Bake loaf or Bundt pan 1 hour at 350°.

title: carrot pineapple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana cinnamon french toast
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients in processor until smooth.
Transfer to a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place bread in milk mixture and soak until all liquid is absorbed.
Melt small amount of butter in a heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add bread and cook until golden brown, about 3 minutes per side.
Serve, passing syrup separately.

title: crispy oven-baked potato wedges(serves 4)
directions: Wash potatoes thoroughly; cut into large wedges (like broasted potatoes).
Do not peel.
Place potatoes in a large bowl.
Add cold water to cover and let soak for 15 minutes.

title: chicken breasts
directions: Arrange in baking dish the chicken; baste with a little butter.
Brown in 400° oven about 3/4 hour, turning every 15 minutes.
Combine soup and water; pour over chicken.
Cover with foil, reduce heat to 325° and bake 1 hour to 1 1/4 hours longer. Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: betsy blakenship's reunion snacks
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in heavy saucepan.
Add pecans and bring to a boil.
Cook 2 minutes. Line greased 9 x 15-inch pan with graham crackers.
Spread with cooked mixture and bake at 300° for 10 minutes.

title: five-veggie stir-fry
directions: In a small bowl, combine the cornstarch, sugar and ginger. Stir in orange juice, soy sauce and garlic until blended; set aside.

In a nonstick skillet or wok, stir-fry the carrots, broccoli and cauliflower in 3 teaspoons of oil for 4 to 5 minutes. Add mushrooms, peas and remaining oil; stir-fry for 3 minutes. Stir orange juice mixture and add to the pan.
Bring to a boil; cook and stir until thickened.
Serve over rice.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Mix in order of ingredients and keep dough soft.
Let rise. Knead down, make buns and let rise till double in size.
To make buns, roll dough, spread butter, sugar and cinnamon on dough. Roll up and seal ends.
Cut 1/4 to 1/2 inch thick.
Butter pan real good.
Place buns in pan and let rise.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine dry ingredients and nuts in a large bowl, stir to mix. Mix together vanilla, oil, egg and water, beat slightly with wire whisk.
Combine all ingredients and stir until blended.
Drop by teaspoon onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 12 minutes.
Yields 6 dozen.
Can add chocolate chips, raisins and coconut.

title: caramel nuts
directions: Combine sugars, cream and corn syrup in 1 1/2-quart saucepan. Cook to softball stage (236°).
Add butter and vanilla.
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm (110°) without stirring.
Beat just until mixture begins to lose its gloss.
Add nuts and stir until well coated.
Turn out onto waxed paper.
Separate nuts with two forks and let cool completely.
Makes 4 cups of confection.
Store in airtight container.

title: deviled ham or chicken ball
directions: Drain the juice from the pineapple.
Blot with a paper towel. Cream all ingredients.
Roll into ball.
Roll into nuts. Refrigerate.

title: finger jello
directions: Mix unflavored gelatine with 1 1/2 cups cold water.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Mix jello, sweetener and 1 cup cold water.
Microwave for 2 minutes on High power or until hot.
Combine both mixtures. Pour into a very lightly greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
(Pam spray works perfectly.)
Let stand, approximately 1/2 hour, in cool place until hard.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown onions in oil, then meat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish, cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Add water, if necessary.
Uncover last 15 minutes of baking time for a crispy topping.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream together eggs, oil and sugar. Stir dry ingredients into egg mixture and mix well. Add squash and nuts and stir thoroughly. Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans. Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes or until toothpick test is done.

title: lemon-lime punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Bake in Bundt pan or 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan in 350° oven for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: chicken breasts with artichoke hearts
directions: On waxed paper, coat chicken breasts with 1/4 cup flour. In 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook chicken until lightly browned on all sides. Place chicken in 12 x 9-inch baking dish. Set aside.

title: 6 layer sausage casserole
directions: Partially cook sausage and drain.
Into a 2-quart casserole bowl, put a layer of potatoes, onion, carrots, sausage, rice or spaghetti (if using spaghetti cook ahead) and tomatoes with juice. Continue until all portions are used.
Combine salt, pepper and sugar and sprinkle over top.
Cover and bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Makes 6 servings.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs and mix in sugar, salt and flour.
Then add milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: cheese log
directions: Mix ingredients; roll in crushed pecans and chill until used.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in a 5 to 6-quart slow cooker. Cover and cook on low heat setting 8 to 10 hours or until apples are very tender. Mash apples with potato masher or large fork. Cook, uncovered, on low heat setting 1 to 2 hours, stirring occasionally, until mixture is very thick. Cool about 2 hours. Spoon apple butter into container. Cover and store in the refrigerator up to 3 weeks. Makes 4 cups of apple butter.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cook spinach.
Drain well.
Press out excess liquid.
In a medium saucepan, combine milk, oil, toasted garlic, salt, hot pepper sauce and cream cheese.
Cook and stir over low heat until cheese is melted and heated through.
Stir in spinach.
Serve with Keebler crackers or dip chips.

title: meatballs
directions: Shape meat into small balls.
Place them in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish or pan.
Lightly brown them at 325°.
Remove from oven and drain grease.
Mix the remaining ingredients together and pour over meatballs.
Turn oven down to about 200° and bake 30 to 45 minutes.

title: dessert
directions: Put crushed vanilla wafers in oblong dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour in dish.
Chill until ready to serve. Dessert makes globes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Sift together in bowl the flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add Crisco, buttermilk and mashed bananas.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add buttermilk and eggs.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Pour batter into prepared pans, 2 round layers 9 x 1 1/2-inches or oblong 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes. Cool.

title: corn chowder
directions: In small pot, over medium heat, cook bacon until partially browned.
Add onion and saute.
Add potatoes and water and cook until tender.
Add corn and heat.
Add milk and seasoning.
Heat and serve.
May sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: raisin and nut cream pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, spices, salt, lemon juice and butter. Stir in raisins and nuts.
Pour into pastry shell and bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: stuffed chicken breasts
directions: Prepare Stove Top stuffing as directed on box.
Place 1/2 cup of stuffing on half of each chicken breast.
Fold other half of chicken breast over stuffing.
Secure with toothpick.
Place on baking dish.
Drizzle with butter.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry flip
directions: In chilled bowl, whip cream until it will hold peaks; set aside.
Put egg, blueberries, sugar and milk in blender; run on high speed until very smooth.
Pour carefully over whipped cream and fold in gently.
Pour into 6 tall glasses; top each with a scoop of ice cream.
Yields 6 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Melt oleo, then add all other ingredients. Mix well and pour into unbaked crust. Bake for 10 minutes at 385°. Then reduce heat to 325° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes, depending on your oven.

title: layered mexican corn bread
directions: Mix eggs, cornmeal, milk and corn.
Pour 1/2 of this mixture into greased 9 x 5-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle 1/2 onion, bell pepper and jalapeno pepper over this.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese over this, next add hamburger meat, then remaining cheese, onions and peppers.
Spread remaining cornbread mixture over top.
Bake at 350°
for 45 to 55 minutes, or until brown and firm in middle.

title: cajun turkey burgers
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine egg, Worcestershire sauce, salt, garlic powder, onion powder and red pepper.
Add bread crumbs and turkey; mix well.
Shape turkey mixture into six patties.
Wrap a strip of bacon around outside of each patty; fasten with toothpick.
Place patties on the unheated rack of a broiler pan. Broil 3 to 4 inches from heat for 15 to 18 minutes or until no pink remains and bacon is done, turning once.
Serve on buns and top with tomato slices and chili peppers, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: fridge pickles
directions: Clean and slice pickles with peelings and soak in 2 tablespoons salt and 1 quart water for 2 hours.
After soaking, mix 1 cup sugar on drained pickles, then add 1/2 cup vinegar.
Mix together and put in container in fridge.
Add more or less sugar and vinegar to taste.

title: mel's spaghetti sauce(alex's favorite)
directions: Brown ground beef in Dutch oven.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer uncovered for 45 minutes.
Serve over hot cooked pasta. Serves 6.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Mix all ingredients until soft dough forms.
Dough will be sticky.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes. Delicious with your favorite soup.

title: energy cookies
directions: Cream together the granulated and brown sugars, butter and shortening.
Beat in eggs and vanilla. Combine flour, salt and soda. Beat into first mixture. Add remaining ingredients and knead into mixture.
Drop by teaspoon 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for about 8 minutes.

title: weeping salad
directions: Layer ingredients in order given.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Mix before serving.

title: poor man's cookies
directions: Combine oats, sugar, flour and salt.
Combine soda and water. Stir into oat mixture with shortening and vanilla.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 2 minutes, then remove to wire rack.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: aunt dolly's potatoes
directions: Butter pan.
Cook potatoes in skins. Cool.
Dice. Put in bowl.
Sprinkle them with parsley, salt and pepper.
Stir. Then repeat again. Dice onion.
Add and stir.
Add bread and stir.
Cut cheese into 16 slices, then quarter.
Add and stir.
Add enough milk to moisten.
Stir.
Melt butter and pour over potato mixture.
Stir again.
Pour into buttered pan.
Top with crushed corn flakes.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in bowl.
Pour in greased baking dish and bake 1 hour at 325°.
Save 1 tablespoon of corn flake crumbs to sprinkle on top after putting in dish to bake.

title: barbecued leg of lamb
directions: Wipe leg of lamb with a paper towel.
Combine the ingredients listed.
Marinate the lamb in glass Pyrex dish, spooning marinade over lamb for several hours.

title: skillet cornmeal biscuits
directions: Blend oil and margarine in skillet.
Stir Bisquick, cornmeal and milk with a fork until a soft dough.
Knead 10 to 12 times on a lightly floured cutting board.
Roll dough 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with a floured 1 1/2 inch cutter.
Fry half the round at a time over medium heat until a delicate brown, turning only once.
Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: great hero sandwich
directions: Cut bread in half lengthwise.
Drain artichoke hearts, reserving liquid.
Spoon liquid over cut sides of bread.
On bottom half of bread, layer lettuce leaves, roast beef, half the cheese, salami, bologna, artichoke hearts, red peppers and remaining cheese.
Top with remaining bread.
Secure with wooden picks and garnish as desired.
Cut into quarters and enjoy.

title: white barbecue chicken sauce
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour over chicken.
Let stand 15 minutes at room temperature or overnight in refrigerator.
Grill chicken and baste with white sauce several times.
This makes enough sauce for 2 cookings.
Refrigerate leftover sauce for later use.

title: bacon crisps
directions: Wrap bacon around width of cracker-ends should hang out. Place on rack in baking pan.
Bake at 375 degrees until bacon is brown, about 15 to 20 minutes, serve hot.

title: salsa chicken
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan. Stir in flour and cook, stirring for 30 seconds. Stir in milk and seasonings. Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture bubbles and thickens.
Remove from heat. Rinse chicken breasts and roll in flour.
Brown on both sides in skillet.
Remove from heat. Stir in salsa, cheese and rice into white sauce, then pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top and cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: layer salad
directions: Layer in order given, topping with the mayonnaise, sugar and cheese combination. Refrigerate, preferably overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook until smooth and slightly thick.
Add red coloring; cool. Pile washed and towel dried berries into pie crust.
Pour cool filling over berries and top with whip cream.

title: jimmy carter dessert
directions: Mix together and press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: cranberry christmas salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into a measuring cup; reserve pineapple. Add water to juice to make 1 cup liquid.
Bring liquid to a boil in a saucepan over medium heat.
When boiling, remove from heat and stir in jello powder; stir until jello is dissolved.
Add cold water.
Chill until jello is of the consistency of unbeaten egg whites.

title: baked chicken with almond sauce
directions: Dredge chicken in flour mixed with salt and pepper.
Place chicken, skin side down, in buttered baking dish.
Melt margarine; pour over chicken. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Turn chicken; bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Pour mushroom soup and water over chicken.
Sprinkle almonds on top. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°. Makes 4 to 5 servings.

title: chili rolled sandwiches
directions: Mix all ingredients except bread.
Cut crusts from bread, spread with mixture.
Roll sandwich up.
Fasten with toothpick. Place under broiler and toast on all sides.
Serve immediately. Makes 8 servings.

title: orange date cake
directions: Mix the ingredients together.
Pour in tube pan.
Bake 2 1/2 hours at 250°.

title: chocolate chunk cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together with flour, oatmeal, salt, baking powder and baking soda. Add chips, candy and nuts.
Roll into balls and place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake for 6 to 11 minutes at 375°.
Makes 9 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: cherry banana cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl; add eggs and oil. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Do not beat.
Add vanilla, pie filling, bananas and nuts.

title: mexican layered dip
directions: On the bottom of dish, spread bean dip.
Next mix the avocados with the guacamole dip and spread
over the bean dip.
Mix the sour cream with 1 package of taco seasoning and mayonnaise. Spread over guacamole.
Sprinkle a thin layer of cheese.
The next layer is the hamburger already cooked with 3/4 package of taco seasoning.
Layer with tomatoes and top with cheese.
Black olives can be sprinkled on top, if desired.

title: slender chicken piccata
directions: In a pie plate, beat together egg white and 1 tablespoon of lemon juice.
In another pie plate, combine flour, garlic powder and paprika.
Dip each chicken breast half in egg, then in flour mixture.
In a large skillet, melt margarine or butter over medium heat.
Add chicken; brown well on both sides.
In a small bowl, combine bouillon powder, broth, boiling water and remaining lemon juice.
Pour mixture over chicken.
Cover; simmer for 20 minutes, or until tender.
Stir in capers.
Sprinkle with parsley; garnish with lemon slices.
Serve with rice and vegetables.

title: chris' special rice
directions: Brown rice in butter.
Pour soups and rice into casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Delicious with beef brisket.

title: nell's rolls
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients and mix well.
Add dissolved yeast.
Now, gradually add flour to mixture.
Cover with a cloth and let rise in a warm place until dough doubles in size (2 hours).
Punch down and shape into rolls.
Let rolls rise until doubled (about 30 minutes).
Bake 20 minutes in a preheated 400° oven.
Brush tops with butter and serve hot.

title: pineapple dream
directions: Mix together everything, but the cherries, in a large bowl. Garnish with the cherries.

title: honey mustard chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts between 2 pieces of waxed paper; flatten with meat mallet or rolling pin.
Set aside.
Combine honey and mustard; coat both sides of chicken.
Roll chicken in pecan pieces.
Bake in a lightly greased baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes, or until tender.

title: bean dip
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease.
Add taco mix and 3/4 cup water.
Simmer.
Add refried beans and tomato sauce.
Add Cheez Whiz; stir until Cheez Whiz melts.
Layer nacho chips into an oblong casserole dish.
Add bean mixture.
Layer more nacho chips and then bean mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: pistachio nut swirl cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, eggs, sour cream, oil and almond extract; blend.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nuts.
Pour 1/3 of batter into greased Bundt pan. Sprinkle with 1/2 of the sugar mixture.
Repeat layers and top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: magdalene's sweet potato sonker
directions: Blend flour and Crisco.
Add enough milk to make a soft dough. Roll out dough.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut peeled eggs lengthwise in half.
Slip out yolks; mash with fork.
Mix in seasonings and mayonnaise.
Fill whites with egg yolk mixture, heaping it up lightly.

title: hamburger cornbread pie(casserole)
directions: Brown meat; drain excess grease.
Add cooking oil and onions and cook until onions are clear, about 1 minute.
Add seasoning and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Then add beans and heat. Put in very large oiled baking dish or large skillet and top with cornbread batter.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes, or until bread browns.
Good on cold days.

title: strawberry french pudding
directions: Combine
eggs, margarine and sugar over low heat.
Pour over crushed
wafers
in
shallow dish.	Add strawberries and juice. Top with Cool Whip and pecans.

title: dieter's marinated carrots
directions: Cut up carrots; cook until tender.
Drain.
Cut up bell pepper and onions in rings.
Add to carrots in a container that can be turned upside down.
Mix in saucepan all other ingredients; heat thoroughly.
Pour this mixture over carrot mixture.
Marinate overnight, turning container several times.

title: cranberry-strawberry mold
directions: Mix cranberries, apples and sugar.
Leave set overnight or for a few hours.
Prepare gelatin.
Chill until slightly thickened and fold in the cranberries, apples, pineapple and marshmallows. Chill until firm and serve with whipped cream if desired.

title: honey apple pandadowdy
directions: Combine the apples, 2 tablespoons of sugar, spices, honey and water in a well-buttered, 1 1/2-quart, flat-bottom baking dish. Dot with butter.

title: cake mix cookies
directions: Drop 1/2 teaspoon onto sprayed cookie sheet. Place approximately 2-inches apart on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes 75 cookies or more.

title: whole wheat pizza crust
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add honey and salt.
Let stand to thicken.
Add oil, then flours, gradually.
Knead for 5 minutes, until elastic.
Place in greased bowl, cover and let rise until doubled (approximately 45 minutes).
Punch down, and divide into two portions for spreading out with fingers onto two greased cookie sheets.
Top with pizza sauce and your favorite toppings. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: bleu cheese dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients except milk and chill for 30 minutes. Beat milk until peaks form.
Fold in cheese mixture.
Yield: 2 1/2 cups.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Grease and flour 3 9-inch round cake pans.
Separate 5 eggs (save yolks) and beat whites until stiff; set aside.
Cream together 1/2 c. butter with shortening and sugar.
Add the 5 egg yolks one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Alternately add buttermilk and flour to batter.
Beat well after each addition.
Add coconut, nuts, vanilla and coconut flavoring.
Fold in stiff egg whites.
Divide batter among 3 prepared pans (about 2 c. per pan).
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Let cool completely.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, syrup and salt in a saucepan over medium heat until edge gets bubbly.
Cook for 5 minutes; stir in soda until foamy.
Drizzle over popcorn that has been placed on cookie sheet.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: raisin crisscross cookies
directions: Mix together shortening, sugar and egg until thoroughly blended.
Stir in milk and lemon extract.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, baking soda and salt.
Thoroughly mix together the wet and dry ingredients until they are well blended.
Stir in raisins.
Roll into balls about the size of a small walnut.
Place balls about 3 inches apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten each with a fork dipped in flour making a crisscross pattern. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix 1 stick oleo and crumbs.
Press in a 13 x 9-inch pan. Combine 2 sticks oleo and powdered sugar; beat for 15 minutes. Spread over crumbs.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Spread crushed pineapple over that.
Spread Cool Whip over top.
Sprinkle with nuts and garnish with cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: hot baked sausages
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly oil a large foil-lined roasting pan with vegetable oil.
Cut sausages into 1/2-inch slices and place in pan.
Add peppers and onions to pan.
Place in preheated oven and bake, uncovered, for 35 to 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Slip under the broiler and brown for a few minutes, if necessary.

title: brown eyed susans
directions: Cream oleo.
Add sugar, vanilla, flour and salt.
Roll level tablespoon of mixture in balls; flatten slightly.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 20 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: taco salad
directions: Pull lettuce apart and put in a large bowl; add chopped tomato, onion, cheese and beans.
Leave chips, dressing and mayonnaise until just before serving time.
Then mix all together and serve.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Cook and rinse macaroni. Add cheese first, then celery seed. Mix this. Add all the rest. Add Miracle Whip to coat well. You can add some onion if you like.

title: sausage-cheese turnovers
directions: Roll each biscuit into a 4-inch diameter circle.
Sprinkle with cornmeal.
Center cheese strips and sausages on biscuits. Fold over and seal edges with fork dipped in flour.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: ham casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn flakes or bread crumbs. Pour into casserole dish; cover with corn flakes or bread crumbs. Cook in preheated 350° oven for 20 minutes or until the mixture is hot and bubbly throughout.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: texas hash
directions: Brown beef in skillet and drain off the fat.
Mix all ingredients in crock-pot (slow cooker); cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: marinated carrot coins
directions: Combine all together; cover and refrigerate.
Keeps in refrigerator up to 5 weeks.
Makes 10 ample servings.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Mix thoroughly 1/2 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion and salt.
Shape firmly into loaf, 8 x 4-inch.
Place in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal raisin cookie mix
directions: In a bowl combine the first five ingredients; set aside.
In a 1 quart glass jar, layer the brown sugar, sugar, raisins and oats, packing well between each layer.
Top with reserved flour mixture.
Cover and store in a cool dry place for up to 6 months.

title: the "best" cake icing
directions: In shaker or jar, blend until smooth the milk and flour.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Mixture will be very thick. Cool.
Cream remaining ingredients together until light and fluffy with mixer in a medium sized bowl.
Gradually add cooled milk/flour mixture to sugar/butter while beating at high speed until all sugar granules are dissolved.
Ready to frost cooled cake.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Add sugar, egg, oleo and vanilla.
Add soda and flour which have been combined.
Add pecans.
Blend all ingredients on medium speed for about 5 minutes.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hamburger special
directions: Form 4 patties of ground beef and place on individual sheets of tinfoil.
Dice potatoes and place on top of beef patties.
Add a small amount of onion on top of potatoes.
Salt and pepper. Secure tinfoil by folding tightly and place on baking sheet.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: wild rice salad
directions: Cook rice according to package directions, substituting seasoned salt.
Drain well; cool to room temperature.
Spoon into a large bowl.
Add chicken, grapes, water chestnuts and mayonnaise.
Toss gently with a fork.
Chill.
Add cashews just before serving.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: lemon squares(bar cookie)
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Measure flour, butter and confectioners sugar thoroughly. Press evenly in a square pan, 8 x 8 x 2. Bake 20 minutes. Beat rest of ingredients together. Pour over crust and bake 20 to 25 minutes more. Do not overbake. (The filling puffs during baking but flattens when cooled.) Makes 16 bars.

title: best rice pudding
directions: Rinse medium size saucepan with cold water.
Pour in 6 cups milk and bring to a boil over medium heat.
Stir in rice and return to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer.
Stirring often, cook, uncovered, until rice is tender (45 to 50 minutes).

title: italian potato casserole
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil.
Mix other ingredients together and add to onions and garlic.
Place in an 8x8x2-inch casserole dish and bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350 degrees.

title: mac and cheese quick fix
directions: Brown hamburger and add onion.
Fix macaroni and cheese per package directions.
In pan, put hamburger, macaroni and cheese and onion with mushroom soup.
Heat and add cheese; mix well and serve.
Make sure you add cheese mix last.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: key lime pie
directions: Combine milk, egg yolks and 1 stiffly beaten egg white.
Mix well.
Pour into baked and cooled pie shell.
Beat remaining 3 egg whites and gradually add 6 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Spread egg whites on top of pie.
Bake at 250° until egg whites are golden brown.

title: hot 'n spicy fried chicken
directions: Stir together hot sauce and garlic salt until blended.
Pour over chicken in large bowl.
Set aside.
Stir together Bisquick mix, onion salt and pepper in medium bowl.
Remove chicken from sauce; drain.
Coat chicken with Bisquick mixture.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and put in casserole dish.
Bake uncovered for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: red cabbage
directions: Cook in deep skillet with top:
1 layer of onions in wine; add apples and simmer 20 minutes.
Add layer of cabbage and simmer 30 minutes.
When cooked, stir in 2 to 3 tablespoons Horseradish Jelly.
Serve warm.

title: apple enchiladas
directions: Spoon fruit filling evenly down center of each tortilla. Sprinkle evenly with cinnamon. Roll up and place seam side down in a lightly greased 2-quart baking dish. Bring butter and next 3 ingredients to a boil in a medium saucepan. Reduce heat and simmer, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes. Pour over enchiladas. Let stand for 30 minutes. Then bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: 5 hour oven stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl. Mix gently but well. Turn into a 3-quart casserole; cover and bake at 275° for 5 hours. Serves 6.

title: mustard glaze
directions: Combine ingredients.
Brush on ham or ribs (or whatever meat you want) frequently during baking.
Makes enough for a 10 to 15 pound ham.
You can use this on roast chicken or turkey or as a sauce to dip shrimp or chicken nuggets.

title: tuna roll
directions: Drain tuna.
Mix tuna, cheese, onion and nuts; make a roll of the mixture.
Roll in crushed corn flakes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In a cooking pot mix all ingredients except hot dogs and macaroni.
Put on low heat until cheese is melted.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Line with hot dogs (cut lengthwise and in 1/2 for quarter pieces).
Add melted cheese mixture to cooked and drained macaroni.
Pour over hot dogs.
Bake for 35 minutes at 375°.

title: green and gold casserole
directions: Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Unroll 1 package of crescent rolls; press evenly in pan to cover bottom, sealing perforations. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup of the Parmesan cheese. Bake in a 350° oven for 10 to 154 minutes or until golden.

title: cinderella crisps
directions: Using 2 forks, roll bread strips in milk, then coconut.
Place on well-greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes. Makes 24 tea crisps.

title: oreo cake
directions: Layer 1/2 cookie mixture on bottom of 9 or 10-inch pan. Layer chocolate ice cream on top	of
this.
Pour
syrup	over chocolate ice cream; layer on
rest
of cookie mixture.
Layer vanilla
ice cream over cookie
mixture.
Cover	with
whipped cream and sprinkle with peanut
brittle,
crushed.
Wrap
well with foil and freeze overnight.

title: jamaican chicken
directions: Place pineapple slices in baking dish.
Top each slice with a breast.
Dissolve bouillon in water.
Combine with coffee, soup and salt.
Pour over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese.
Return to oven until cheese melts.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Mash cheese with a fork; then add remaining ingredients. Using more mayonnaise for creamy and using less for thick.
Spread on bread or crackers.

title: singapore stew
directions: Brown meat well in shortening.
Add celery, onions, green pepper and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer about 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender, but firm.
Add salt, sugar and soy sauce. Add spinach and cook 5 minutes longer.
Serve over rice.

title: stained glass cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and margarine until blended.
Remove from heat and stir in beaten egg; let cool.
Put confectioners sugar, marshmallows and nuts in bowl; stir well.
Pour chocolate mixture over marshmallow mixture and blend.
Pour coconut on foil.
Pour mixture over coconut and roll.
Refrigerate, then slice roll into slices.
It will look like stained glass when finished.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine sugar, water and cinnamon.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice.
Flatten each biscuit to a 4 1/2-inch circle.
Place small amount diced apples in center of each, fold in half.
Seal by pressing with fork.
Brush with butter.
Place in casserole and pour syrup around dumplings.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 5.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place beans in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place onion ring slices over beans.
Put bacon on top of onions.
Sprinkle almonds on bacon.
Add sugar and vinegar to bacon drippings and heat.
Pour over beans and marinate several hours or overnight.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: microwave grannie's peanut butter cookies
directions: Place butter in a microwave-safe bowl, breaking it up into pieces.
Microwave at High power for about 45 seconds.
Cover with wax paper to prevent splattering.
Beat in the sugars, vanilla, peanut butter and eggs.

title: mock apple pie
directions: Combine water and sugar, along with the lemon juice.
Have water just hot enough to dissolve sugar.
Add lemon juice.
Crush crackers and add to mixture, letting stand a few minutes.
You may, at this point, want to add a few more crackers.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and dot with butter.
Preheat oven to 400°; bake 40 minutes.
You may use NutraSweet (same exchange).

title: creamed corn casserole
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together; pour into baking dish (9 x 9-inch).
Add the corn bread mix.
Cut this into first mixture; do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cheddar chicken pot pie
directions: Cut butter into flour.
Add water until it forms a ball. Refrigerate 1/2 hour.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter for 30 minutes.
Add flour.
Stir for 1 minute.
Add broth, wine, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour soup in bowls.
Add 1 slice toasted bread to each and top with Swiss cheese.
Broil until cheese bubbles.

title: new england boiled dinner
directions: Cook ham according to directions for only 1/2 the time suggested.
Then add vegetables and finish cooking.
Drain broth and serve ham and vegetables with vinegar or butter or both.
This should be cooked in crock-pot.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Mix Bisquick, sugar, egg,
margarine
and milk.
Fold in 1/2 cup drained crushed pineapple.
Bake
to
20 minutes at 375°. Makes 12 to 18 muffins.
While warm, frost with icing.

title: western meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly. Put in loaf pan.
Top with 2 strips of bacon.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until done through middle.

title: grilled shrimp kabobs
directions: Thread shrimp onto wooden skewers, using 2 skewers per kabob to facilitate turning (1 skewer through the meaty part, 1 skewer through the tail part of each shrimp).
Brush grill with oil. Combine melted butter and honey (or substitute 1 cup Italian dressing for butter and honey).
Cook shrimp over hot coals, basting frequently with honey mixture or Italian dressing for 10 minutes per inch of thickness or until shrimp are tender and no longer translucent in the center.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: tennessee snow cream
directions: Mix all ingredients with mixer and add fresh (clean) snow, one cup at a time, until you reach the desired consistency.

title: potato-cheese patties
directions: Combine potatoes and water to cover in a large saucepan; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until tender.
Drain; reserve potatoes in saucepan.
Add milk and beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until smooth; stir in cheese. Cover and chill mixture overnight.
Combine remaining ingredients in a small bowl, stirring well.
Shape 1/3 cup potato mixture into a 3-inch patty.
Coat with cereal mixture.
Place on an ungreased baking sheet.
Repeat procedure with remaining potato mixture and cereal mixture.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Yield: 11 servings (87 calories per serving).

title: cheddar stack cakes with spiced fruit sauce
directions: In medium saucepan, combine 2 cups water, dried fruit, brown sugar, lemon juice and nutmeg.
Heat to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 20 to 25 minutes or until thickened, stirring occasionally.
Stir in peaches; keep warm.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Blend together flour, brown sugar, fruit juice and cinnamon. Dot butter over fruit. Pour liquid over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(I let the fruit drain for an hour or so before preparing the casserole.)

title: alice rae's broccoli salad
directions: Wash and dry broccoli, then chop stalks and tops into medium-to-fine size cubes; leave some flowerets large enough so that they are indentifiable.
Chop and add remaining ingredients. Add juice from lemon or lime and salt and pepper.
Add mayonnaise and mix all.
May be served immediately.
Keeps well in refrigerator for several days.
Serve as a main dish salad or serve over a slice or two of whole wheat bread for a delicious open-face sandwich.
Good for a crowd.

title: biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Melt shortening.
Mix together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Make a hole in the center, and add the buttermilk and melted shortening; stir just until ingredients are mixed.

title: cinnamon flop coffee cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together and put in pan.
Then mix brown sugar,
1 1/2 tablespoons butter and cinnamon together and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs.
Add water and pumpkin.
Mix all the dry ingredients together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Pour into 3 large or 4 small loaf pans. Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: double chocolate brownies
directions: In large bowl, combine cocoa and soda.
Blend in 1/3 cup butter; add water and stir until blended.
Stir in sugar, eggs and rest of butter.
Add flour and vanilla.
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Use whisk or spoon to mix.
Pour in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: cinderella crisps
directions: Use 2 forks to roll bread strips in the milk, coating on all sides.
Roll in coconut. Place on well-greased baking sheet and bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 24 crisps.
Scrumptious!

title: delicious topping for any cake
directions: Place egg yolks in heavy pan.
Gradually add the entire can of milk.
Gradually add all the sugar.
Turn burner to medium heat, stirring constantly.
Add all the margarine.
Bring to a boil; boil for 7 minutes.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla.
Let cool completely before putting on cake, or it will soak into cake.

title: pecan balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well with hands.
Chill for 15 minutes in refrigerator.
Remove and form into small balls and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°; cook for 5 minutes on bottom rack, then 10 minutes on top rack.
While hot, roll in powdered sugar.
Let cool and roll again in sugar.

title: hoppin' john
directions: Saute ham, onion and hot sauce in oil at medium heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Stir until onion is soft.
Combine peas, ham mixture and rice.
Heat.
Garnish with chopped pimentos and green onions. Serves 8.

title: *finikia 3
directions: In a large saucepan, melt together the butter and Crisco. Remove pan from heat and add the milk, eggs and vanilla.
Add the flour and baking powder.
Mix until dough pulls away from sides of pan.
Knead slightly, then let dough rest.
Shape into small balls, then flatten dough in palms and fill with mixture of the dates and walnuts.
Place on baking sheets and pierce each one with toothpick before baking at 350° for 35 minutes until light brown.
Before removing from oven, test a cookie by cutting in half to see if it is cooked through. Remove cookies, 6 at a time and drop into the following Syrup.

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Mix cake mix, pudding mix and poppy seed. Add water and oil. Add eggs 1 at a time, beating after each one. Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan. Can just spray with Pam and not flour the pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Let cool in pan 15 minutes before taking out.

title: ambrosia parfait
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk with wire whisk 1 to 2 minutes.
Mix in 1/2 cup marshmallows, banana and pineapple with juice.
Spoon some of the mixture into glasses.
Add layer of remaining ingredients; alternate with layers of pudding.
Chill.
Serves 6.

title: chicken or pork chops no peek
directions: Put uncooked rice in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then place chicken or pork chops on top of rice.
Mix soups and milk together; pour over chicken or pork chops.
Sprinkle Lipton onion soup mix over that.
Seal tightly with foil.
Don't peek.
Bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: corn meal dumplings
directions: Beat egg; stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into simmering chicken or beef broth and cover for 15 minutes.

title: mexican ripe olive casserole
directions: In baking dish layer, starting with Fritos, beef, soup, olives, enchilada sauce and cheese.
Makes 2 layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: taco pie
directions: Press biscuits into a 9-inch pie pan, forming a continuous crust.
Brown turkey.
Sprinkle with beef bouillon.
Add onions, green pepper, salt and pepper.
After the meat mixture is cooked, add tomato paste, water and taco seasoning.
Put half of the mixture in unbaked crust.
Spread half of the cheese on top. Cover with remaining meat mixture and top with remaining cheese. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes or until crust is brown.
Cut into 8 equal pieces and serve warm.

title: jello cake
directions: Bake white cake mix per box directions in two 8 or 9-inch cake pans.
Cool cake.
Poke holes about 3/4 inch apart all through cake rounds.
Prepare jello (each flavor) in separate bowls, using only the 1 cup of hot water (do not use the cold water or ice cubes; do not set jello).
Spoon lime jello into holes in one cake layer and raspberry jello into holes in the other layer (use all jello).
Chill both layers about 1 hour.
Remove from cake pans; frost with Cool Whip.

title: grandad irish coffee
directions: Combine whiskey and brown sugar in a tall glass and stir. Pour in hot coffee.
Top with whipped cream.
Garnish with cinnamon, if desired.
Makes 1 serving.

title: potato soup
directions: Bring chicken broth to a boil and add potatoes and carrots and let simmer for 30 minutes. Saut onions in a separate pan. Add flour to onions. Add onions to broth mixture. Add cheese and spices, stirring until cheese melts. Let simmer 15 minutes or until ready to eat.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, salt and mustard.
Cut in shortening and cheese.
Mix well; add milk and mix well.
Put meat mixture in pan, then top with topping and spread evenly over meat mixture.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: bread pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread 1 package of crescent rolls onto cookie sheet to form a crust.
Repeat with second package of crescent rolls onto second cookie sheet.
Bake both crusts for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool.
Mix together cream cheese, mayo and dressing mix.
Spread over crusts.
Dice the vegetables up very small and sprinkle on top of the mix.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.

title: meat stuffed zucchini
directions: Parboil zucchini for 5 minutes.
Scoop out pulp until 1/4-inch thick wall.
Fry onions and bacon.
Add beef and sausage.
Brown, add garlic, tomatoes and rice.
Cook 5 minutes and add bread crumbs and spices. Stuff shells.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Top with cheese and melt.

title: recipe for one gallon of ice cream
directions: Put milk in double boiler and add the beaten eggs, which have been mixed with the sugar and cornstarch, to the double boiler. Cook the custard until slightly thickened; remove from stove and cool.

title: gingered carrots
directions: Steam carrots 15 to 20 minutes or until barely tender.
In a medium sized frying pan, melt margarine until it bubbles.
Add carrots and toss.
Sprinkle with sugar and ginger; toss lightly to coat carrots.
Continue cooking until carrots are lightly glazed, about 1 to
2 minutes.
Just before serving, sprinkle with parsley.
Yield:
5 servings.
Approximate calories/serving:

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars; add eggs.
Add baking powder, soda and flour.
Add coconut and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon on Pam-sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: orange fluff
directions: Mix (with mixer) cottage cheese and jello.
Add Cool Whip. Fold in nuts and oranges before serving.

title: old fashion souse
directions: Clean all hair from ears and feet.
Wash all meat clean.
Place into a large pot and cook until the meat is tender enough to fall off the bones.
When cool, put meat in a large pan or bowl and separate the bones from the meat.
Add pepper, sage and red pepper to meat.
Mash with a potato masher or grind in a meat grinder. Stir in vinegar.

title: j. c.'s homemade peanut butter crackers
directions: You will need a knife.

title: taco soup
directions: Do not drain any of the cans.
Simmer for 1 hour.
This may be made either hot or mild.
If you prefer mild, do not use ingredients with green chilies or jalapenos added and use Ranch Style pinto beans.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor; blend.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Serve with raw veggies or crackers.
Makes 8 servings.

title: layered salad
directions: Use a large, deep salad bowl.
Tear lettuce into small pieces; place in bowl.
Add celery, onion, green pepper and raw peas. Spread mayonnaise or salad dressing over top of peas to seal top of mixture, about 1/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle top with bacon bits and Parmesan cheese.
Cover.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight.
Toss before serving.

title: simple chocolate cheesecakes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line muffin pans with foil paper cups (2 1/2 inches in diameter).
Place 1 vanilla wafer in bottom of each cup.
In large mixer bowl, beat softened cream cheese and sugar. Blend in cocoa and flour.
Add eggs; beat well.
Blend in sour cream and vanilla.
Fill each prepared cup almost full with cheese mixture.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes, or just until set.
Remove from oven.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes.
Spread heaping teaspoonfuls of topping (below) on each cup.
Cool completely.
Chill.
Garnish with cherry pie filling just before serving.

title: baked haddock
directions: Pour soup over fish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Combine other ingredients.
Sprinkle over fish and bake 10 more minutes.

title: chicken luncheon casserole
directions: Grease a large baking dish with margarine.
Lay 8 slices of bread, flat.
Slice a chicken breast on each piece of bread.
Top with a slice of cheese and another slice of bread.

title: nutty bananas
directions: Peel bananas and dip in orange juice; then roll in nuts.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Place crushed Doritos in the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.
In a medium bowl, mix all ingredients except shredded cheese.
Pour over chips.
Top with shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix artichoke hearts, mayonnaise and cheese. Put in casserole dish and bake at 300° for 30 minutes. Serve with Ritz crackers.

title: mam maw's spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Refrigerate until serving. Serve with party rye or party crackers.

title: cheese dip
directions: Warm to melting in crock-pot.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: taco dip
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning. Spread on a 12-inch plate, leaving 1/2 inch from edge.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Top with taco sauce, shredded lettuce, grated cheese and diced tomatoes.
Surround plate with tortilla chips.

title: stewed bananas
directions: Peel bananas, cut in half length ways and stew in the butter until golden brown.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon and serve warm.

title: favorite broccoli salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients except mayonnaise or salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
In another bowl, combine mayonnaise or salad dressing, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well. Just before serving, pour dressing over salad and toss well.

title: crab and spinach quiche
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs.
Add milk, mustard, nutmeg and sherry.
Mix well.
Drain spinach.
Add spinach, cheese and crabmeat to egg mixture.
Stir well.
Place pie shell in glass pie plate.
Pour mixture into pie shell.
Microwave on Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, or until set in center.
Rotate dish 1/4 turn at 10 minute intervals during cooking time.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Put butter and onion in 2-quart bowl; cover.
Micro on High 5 to 6 minutes, stirring once, until onion just begins to brown. Stir in flour to make a smooth paste.
Gradually stir in water until well blended, then broccoli, bouillon and pepper.
Cover and micro on High 10 to 12 minutes until broccoli is tender and soup thickened.
Carefully stir in milk.
Makes about 4 cups.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients together in a bowl and add the blueberries.
Beat egg in another bowl.
Stir in buttermilk and oil. Pour liquid mixture into dry ingredients, stirring just to moisten.
Do not beat.
Fill a dozen muffin molds (use paper or foil liners) about 3/4 full.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from molds to cool.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Separate and cook in microwave for 10 minutes the cauliflower and water.
Drain.
Add peas and mushroom soup.
Mix and put in buttered casserole.
Top with grated cheese.
Top with bay leaf. Remove before serving.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: fruity fresh apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Grease and flour a 9-inch round pan thoroughly.
Spread mixture in pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Frost if desired.

title: batter bread(makes 2 loaves)
directions: Soften the yeast in warm water.
Add scalded milk to sugar, salt and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 2 cups of flour.
Beat well with a spoon or mix 1 minute on medium-low speed of mixer. Add softened yeast and egg.
Beat well again.
Add remaining flour to make a thick batter.
Beat until smooth.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (80° to 85°) until doubled.
Stir down and smooth into the two greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pans.
Cover and let rise until almost doubled (about 50 minutes).
Bake 25 to 35 minutes at 375°.

title: banana-pecan biscotti
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Lightly spoon flour, sugar, baking powder and salt until blended.
Combine banana, oil, egg and vanilla in a bowl; stir in flour mixture and pecans (dough will be sticky).
Turn dough out onto floured surface. Shape into 2- 8 in. rolls. Place on sprayed baking sheet and flatten to 1/2 in. thick.
Bake at 350 degrees for 23 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool 10 minutes.
Cut each roll into 1/2 inch slices.
Place sides down on pan.
Bake at 250 degrees for 15 minutes, then turn over and bake another 15 minutes.
Remove from sheet and cool completely.
Cookies will harden as they cool.

title: hawaiian delight cake
directions: Mix together sugar and flour.
