Mix dry ingredients to eggs and pineapple mixture.
Add nuts.
Bake in greased and floured baking dish.
Bake at 350° until center feels done and cake is brown, approximately 37 minutes.

title: brenda's aunt moe's dressing
directions: Melt 3/4 stick of margarine in skillet.
Mix all ingredients (except soups) and pour margarine from skillet into mix.
Bake until browned.
Add remaining 3/4 stick of margarine while hot. Crumble bread and add soups and broth until desired consistency. Bake at 350° until brown.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and shortening.
Add egg, then coffee.
Sift salt, soda and flour and fold into creamed mixture.
Add vanilla and apples.
Put in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts, mixed and sprinkled over cake.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Grease or spray a 1 1/2-quart round casserole dish.
In a large bowl, mix flour and the next 4 ingredients with a fork.
With a pastry blender or 2 knives used scissor fashion; cut in butter or margarine.

title: gladys beach's pink stuff dessert
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: apple sheet cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Sift together baking powder and flour.
If butter is slightly stiff, add a little milk.
Pour butter into a 13 x 14-inch sheet pan.
Slice apples and mix with cinnamon and sugar.
Place on top of batter.
Cook in oven at 350°.
Bake 40 to 50 minutes until apples are done.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix crumbs with melted butter in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix powdered sugar, cream cheese and 1/2 of the pineapple juice.
Beat until creamy.
Spread on graham cracker crust.
Sprinkle pineapple over mixture, then bananas, then Cool Whip.
Sprinkle cherries and pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: baked fish with papaya salsa
directions: Preheat the oven to 350°.
Place the fish in a baking dish. Spread the salsa on top.
Cover with foil and bake for 10 minutes. Remove the foil and continue to bake for 5 to 10 minutes longer or until the fish is tender and flaky.
Serve hot, garnished with cilantro sprigs.
Serves 4.

title: lemon cake sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir in water.
Bring to boil; stir constantly.
Cook 2 minutes; remove from heat.
Stir in ReaLemon and butter.
Serve warm over cake or gingerbread.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt and spices.
Add milk and evaporated milk; blend.
Pour into 9-inch pastry-lined pie pan (have edges crimped high).
Bake in oven at 400° for 50 minutes or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: economy peach cobbler
directions: Sprinkle bottom of pan with cake mix.
Pour in the can of peaches.
Sprinkle with sugar and nutmeg.
Cover with remaining cake mix.
Melt margarine and pour over cobbler.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Add spices to sweet potatoes according to taste. Use more cinnamon, then ginger. Mix well. Lightly spread muffin tin. Take a marshmallow and wrap sweet potatoes around it forming a ball. Lay in muffin tin. Bake at 350° for 5 minutes until marshmallows melt.

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container.
Use 1/4 to 1/3 cup for each cup hot chocolate.
Makes about 30 servings.

title: christmas pecans
directions: Combine sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Set aside.
Beat egg white until foamy.
Add pecan halves and mix until coated.

title: fruit butter
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender until smooth.
Serve with waffles, pancakes, etc.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables as directed.
Drain and combine in casserole dish.
Heat together both cans of soup and pour over vegetables. Top with croutons.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: potica(raisin bread)
directions: Roll out dough to 1/4-inch thickness.
Spread on well beaten egg.
Spread with butter or margarine.
Spread over the dry ingredients.
Add raisins and roll up tightly.
Put whole rolls in one greased loaf pan and bake about 40 minutes.

title: graham cracker cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet with graham cracker squares.
Boil oleo and brown sugar for 2 minutes. Add nuts.
Pour over crackers and bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: mimi's pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine eggs (slightly beaten), Karo, sugar, oleo (melted) and vanilla.
Mix good.
Add pecans.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Press rolls into large cookie sheet forming sides.
Bake in 375° oven for 10 minutes; cool.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing until smooth.
Spread on cool crust.
Top with assorted vegetables then cheese.
Refrigerate.
Better if made the night before and covered with plastic wrap and refrigerated.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix well flour, sugar, cinnamon, soda, salt and vanilla.
Then add eggs, oil, zucchini and pecans.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Small loaves should be baked 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Serve hot or cold.
Freezes well.

title: italian bread
directions: Heat 1 1/4 cups water and oil.
Add flour, sugar, salt and rapid rise yeast; mix together.
Work dough and then add beaten egg to mixture.
Rub 1 tablespoon oil in bowl then add dough and cover 1 hour.
Put into oiled loaf pan and cover for about 40 minutes. Bake at 375° for about 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: hershey's milk chocolate chunk macadamia cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add egg; beat well.
Combine flour and baking soda; blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in Macadamia nuts and milk chocolate chunks.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until lightly browned.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet onto wire rack.
Cool completely.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: "taramosalata" - fish roe dip or spread
directions: Rinse the tarama as much as you can.
Strain it very well and put in mixing bowl.
Beat for a few minutes.
Slowly drop by drop, add the Mazola oil until it gets very thick.
Add the remaining oil, one tablespoon at a time.
If too salty, add the 2 tablespoons lukewarm water.
Finish with the lemon juice according to taste.
If too thick, add the water.

title: baked cheese dish
directions: Spread butter on bread, break bread into 1 1/2-inch pieces to fit a greased baking dish.
Put grated cheese over bread, layer of bacon, cut in 1-inch pieces.
Beat eggs.
Add salt, paprika and milk.
Pour over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until very light and puffy.
(Good when reheated!)

title: banana strawberry treat
directions: Slice bananas from end to end.
Put round slices into large bowl.
Add strawberries and mix; put into refrigerator; chill until ready to serve.
Serve plain or top with Cool Whip.

title: white sage bread
directions: In a bowl, combine dry ingredients.
In a small bowl, dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Blend in blender the egg, cottage cheese, butter and yeast water.
Blend.
Transfer into a large bowl.
Gradually add flour mixture; knead until stiff dough is formed.
Cover with a dry cloth and let rest in a warm place until doubled in bulk, about 1 hour.

title: deli salad
directions: Prepare
rotini
according to package directions; drain. In large
bowl, combine rotini and remaining ingredients; toss to mix.
Cover; chill thoroughly.
Toss gently before serving. Refrigerate.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: sauerkraut chicken
directions: Place chicken in Pyrex dish. Top each breast with half of slice of Mozzarella cheese. Rinse and drain sauerkraut, then mix with brown sugar.
Put sauerkraut over chicken and cheese. Cover sauerkraut with bottled Thousand Island dressing.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: broccoli balls
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain well. Combine all, mixing well.
Cover and place in freezer approximately 30 minutes.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Fry balls in oil until golden brown or place on greased cookie sheet under broiler turning often until golden brown.
Drain if necessary. Serve while warm with Honey Mustard Dressing.

title: potato casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Mix with all ingredients except cheese.
Pour into 9x13-inch pan.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip, lemon juice, condensed milk, pecans and pineapple.
Stir until well mixed.
Divide mixture equally into the two crusts.
Chill and serve.
Approximate time: 15 minutes.

title: guacamole salad
directions: Cut tomatoes in halves crosswise; scoop out pulp and reserve. Sprinkle tomato shells with salt. Turn upside down to drain; chill.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Use pineapple juice and enough water to make an additional 2 cups liquid needed to complete package instructions.
Add pineapple, oranges, cranberry sauce, nuts and apples.
Mix well and pour in a 9 x 13-inch pan or mold and refrigerate at least 4 hours.

title: julie's terrible fudge
directions: Pour milk and sugar into pot.
Heat on high until mixture starts into a rolling boil.
If necessary, reduce heat, but maintain rolling boil for 3 to 4 minutes. After 3 or more minutes, remove from heat.
Mix in Marshmallow Creme and peanut butter. Pour into a 14
x 9-inch pan and cool.
As an alternative, try adding Hershey's cocoa for chocolate-peanut butter fudge.

title: apple pan dowdy
directions: Peel and slice apples into salt water to keep from turning brown.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and egg by hand. Place drained sliced apples into 8 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cover with topping mixture.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Note:
If you double recipe, use 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: sauerkraut soup
directions: Dice bacon slices and saute with diced onion.
Peel and dice potatoes.
Add to bacon and onion.
Pour in chicken broth and cook until potatoes are tender.
Drain sauerkraut, saving juice.
Add kraut.
Add juice to suit your taste.
Add pepper and salt if needed.
If chicken broth does not have enough flavor, you can add chicken bouillon cube, which is salty so be careful about adding salt.
Serve with a large spoon of sour cream on top of each bowl.

title: tortilla wrapped pickles
directions: Blend cheese and salsa.
Spread on tortillas.
Roll up pickle in tortilla; cut.

title: honey-mustard dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a mixing bowl.
Blend well with whisk for at least 5 minutes.
Chill to serve.
Refrigerate any unused portion.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes. You can also use hash brown potatoes O'Brien which already has the onions and green peppers in it.

title: chili rellenos cornbread
directions: Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart mixing bowl on High in the microwave for 45 seconds to 1 minute.
Beat in eggs, corn and sour cream.
Combine corn meal, baking powder and salt.
Stir in dry ingredients until well blended.
Pour half the batter into a greased 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Place the chilies and half the cheese over the batter.
Spread with the remaining batter and top with remaining cheese.
Cook on Low for 4 minutes.
Bake on High for 5 to 7 minutes or until golden brown.
Yield:
9 pieces.

title: potato skins
directions: Thoroughly scrub
potatoes;
prick several times with a fork. Bake at 450° for
minutes
to 1 hour or until done; allow to cool to touch.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: Cut potatoes in thin slices.
Place in pan.
Mix sugar, flour, salt and nutmeg.
Place over potatoes; add water.
Cut butter and layer over ingredients.
Cover with pie crust.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350° or until brown.

title: curried fruit
directions: Heat ingredients and
drizzle over fruit.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 1	hour.
Serves 10 to 12.
Peaches can also be used.

title: monte cristo sandwiches
directions: Beat together eggs and milk.
Set aside.
Spread butter on bread.
For each sandwich, top one slice of bread with one slice of cheese, one slice of ham, a second slice of cheese and a second slice of bread, butter side down.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix together and chill first four items.
Add ginger ale and strawberries when served.
Serves 25.

title: angel flake coconut cream pie
directions: Mix yolks, cornstarch, vanilla, sugar.
Heat milk hot but not boiling.
Then stir in egg mixture (if thick add a little water to smooth).
Remove from heat and stir in coconut to your taste. Beat egg whites stiff.
Put on top of pie, sprinkle with coconut. Place pie in oven and brown top at 350°.

title: pepped up cheese bake(makes 12 servings)
directions: Mix sour cream, mayo, flour and garlic.
Stir in grease.
Put in 7-inch microwave quiche dish.
Bake at 70% for 4 to 6 minutes, stirring twice.
Decorate outer edge with nuts.
Next rim in with diced green onion and interior with pimentos.
Serve warm with crackers.

title: stir-fried chinese cabbage
directions: Fifteen minutes before serving, cut cabbage crosswise into 1 1/2-inch pieces.
In Dutch oven over high heat in hot salad oil, cook cabbage, stirring quickly and frequently (stir-frying) until well coated.
Sprinkle with salt (use soy sauce only with nappa) and sugar.
Reduce heat.
Continue stir-frying 5 to 8 minutes more until tender-crisp.
Makes 4 servings.

title: english muffin canapes
directions: Combine all ingredients; spread on 8 split English muffins. Cut into wedges.
Freeze until ready to use.
Bake at 425° until bubbly.

title: quick seafood dip
directions: Combine ingredients and chill. Serve with cooked, chilled lobster chunks, shrimp or fried fish bits. Yields 1 cup.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Grease and flour cookie sheet.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake until done (10 to 15 minutes) at 350 degrees.
When done, put cake on a towel sprinkled with 10 X sugar.
Roll cake up in towel.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, unroll cake and spread frosting on. Roll back up and put in aluminum foil.
Store in refrigerator.

title: stupid cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order to baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.

title: cream of brie soup
directions: Saute onion and celery in a small amount of butter.
Add broth, then cheese.
Stir until cheese is melted, but do not allow mixture to boil.
Add salt and milk or cream; stir until all ingredients are blended and soup is heated through.
Do not boil!

title: fried chicken
directions: Wash the chicken.
Cut into the joint.
Put in a bowl.
Put your flour into a bowl.
Mix your seasoned salt in the flour or on the chicken.
Heat the stove eye.
Drop the chicken in a deep fryer pan.
Cook until done.

title: fried parsnip
directions: Peel and slice long ways.
Put butter or bacon grease in skillet.
Sprinkle with black pepper, a little salt and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Add just a little water (1/4 cup or less).
Let cook until brown, turn over and cook until tender or done.
They are candy when done.

title: sorrento stew
directions: Remove casing from sausage.
In Dutch oven brown sausage; drain.
Add the herb-spice mix, vegetables, tomato paste and water; bring to a boil.
Break the spaghetti into thirds; add to hot mixture.
Cover; simmer 20 minutes.
Sprinkle servings with the grated Parmesan cheese.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: Put stew beef, salt, onion and pepper in large pot and boil. Prepare vegetables and put all together in pot and cook until vegetables are done.

title: turkey enchilada stack
directions: Preheat the oven to 450°.
Set aside, in separate bowls, 1/3 cup of salsa, 1/4 cup of chopped tomato and 3 tablespoons of the cheese.
In a large bowl, combine the turkey, chilies, onion, the remaining salsa, tomato and cheese; stir until well mixed.

title: easy chicken a la king
directions: In 2 tablespoons oil cook onion until soft.
Add soup, milk, salt and pepper and mix well.
Add chicken and pimientos and heat through.
Spoon over cooked rice or noodles.
Enjoy!

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pudding, milk, spices, pumpkin and Cool Whip; let set for 4 hours.
Top with Cool Whip that you have left over.
Very good.

title: vegetable coleslaw
directions: Slice vegetables by hand or with thickest blade on food processor.
Process in batches and mix all vegetables together in a bowl.

title: twenty-four hour cole slaw
directions: Chop vegetables in water in blender.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix sugar, vinegar, celery seed, salt and mustard seed.
Stir into vegetables and place in covered container in refrigerator and let stand overnight.

title: sandies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add vanilla and water.
Add flour a little at a time.
Add 1 cup pecans.
Form into small rolls (about 2-inches in size).
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 300° for 20 minutes.
Cool and roll in powdered sugar.

title: harvard beets
directions: Cook until thick.
Pour over 1 can beets.
Let stand before serving.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Melt 1/2 pound butter or oleo margarine with 1 cup peanut butter over low heat.
Add 1 pound powdered sugar, 1 teaspoon vanilla and 2 tablespoons cocoa.
Stir and press into a buttered dish and cool.

title: shortbread cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Blend in flour gradually.
Dough will be stiff.
Knead with hand until well blended.
Put through cookie press.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheets at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: abigail's fig cake
directions: Cream butter and honey together before adding the figs and the beaten egg yolks.
Stir until smooth.
Add flour and yogurt, alternating.
Add nuts, raisins and cinnamon.
Fold in egg whites. Pour into greased cake pan and bake at 350° for 90 minutes. Serve with honey.

title: vegetable pie
directions: Grease pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch.
Heat 1 cup of water with 1/2 to 2 teaspoons salt to boiling.
Add broccoli, cover and cook until tender.
Drain; mix broccoli, onion, green peppers and cheese in pie plate.
Beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until golden brown at 350° or 325° about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: bacon and onion strata
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; drain and break into small pieces. Generously grease a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.	Arrange 6 bread slices in bottom of dish alternating bread types if desired. Sprinkle bacon pieces, cheese and onions over bread.
Top with remaining 6 bread slices, alternating or matching bread types. Beat eggs in a large bowl.	Add milk and pepper.
Pour mixture over sandwiches.
Cover and refrigerate at least 3 hours or overnight. Uncover dish.
Bake in preheated 325° oven for 50 to 55 minutes until puffed and golden brown and knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: weight watchers soup
directions: Cook down everything until tender; 25 calories per cup.

title: apricot-angel brownies
directions: Over low heat, melt together white chocolate and margarine. Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir into chocolate mixture.
Combine apricots, almonds and coconut. Mix well and pour half into chocolate mixture.
Pour chocolate mixture into greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle remaining apricot mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.
Absolutely wonderful.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Filling:
Whip cream cheese until light and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Add milk, a little at a time.
Blend thoroughly.
Fold in Cool Whip by hand.

title: but-la-wa
directions: Heat milk to hot on low flame.
Add farina.
Stir now and then. Add sugar, stirring constantly, so it doesn't stick.
Raise flame and keep stirring.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes to thicken.
When there is no milk separation, add 2 tablespoons melted butter and vanilla. Stir a couple of minutes and pour quickly into greased tray.
Pour remaining butter over the But-La-Wa and let tray stand until entirely cooled.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook over medium heat 20 minutes.
Add 3 cups hot chicken broth and pour into a 3-quart casserole.
Bake covered at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sugarless spice cake(diabetic cake)
directions: In pan, cook raisins in water until water evaporates.
Add applesauce, eggs, Equal and oil.
Mix well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until tests done.
Serve with lite Cool Whip, if desired.

title: butterscotch delight
directions: Melt margarine.
Add flour.
Mix well.
Add pecans.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: party salad
directions: Melt milk and marshmallows.
Pour hot mixture over Jell-O. Stir until dissolved.
Stir in cream cheese.
Stir until cheese is dissolved.
Add pineapple.
Cool.
Blend in whipped heavy cream and mayonnaise.
Chill until firm.

title: aunt irene's barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to boil; cook 30 minutes.

title: people puppy chow
directions: Melt peanut butter, chocolate chips and butter.
Mix in cereal.
Pour powdered sugar into brown paper grocery sack.
Dump cereal mixture into bag.
Shake well.
Pour on flat pan to dry.

title: pizzaburger
directions: Brown onion.
Add beef; cook until browned and stir often to separate meat particles.
Drain.
Add soup, cheese and oregano. Simmer about 10 minutes.
Serve on buns.
Toasted buns are even better.
Makes 8 servings.

title: overnight crab casserole
directions: Drain crabmeat (or crab substitute) and coarsely flake. Combine crab, uncooked macaroni, cheese, eggs, undiluted soup, milk and chives plus the olives, pimentos and mushrooms in a deep 1-quart casserole.
Cover and refrigerate at least 8 hours, preferably overnight.
Bake, covered, in a 350° oven for 1 hour. Sprinkle with paprika.

title: chicken and noodles
directions: Place chicken and water in cooker. Add salt and oil.
Cook chicken until done. Remove chicken from cooker.
Add your noodles in remaining chicken broth. Cook noodles until done. Season to taste.

title: peach yogurt summer nog
directions: Chill all ingredients.
Combine in a blender container. Process well until smooth.
Serve in punch cups.
Sprinkle with cinnamon or nutmeg; garnish with a mint leaf.
Makes 6 servings, under 55 calories each.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Peel and core apples; slice thin.
Mix next 6 ingredients and toss with apples.
Use a homemade pie crust, or a boxed pie crust from the refrigerator case in the store (I use Pillsbury).
Spread pie crust in large pie plate and put in half of apple mixture, compacting apples well.
Dot with remaining butter.
Top with other crust; slice vents in top.
Press top crust over and under bottom; squeeze together and flute.
Sprinkle small amount of milk on crust; spread around and sprinkle with small amount of sugar.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for about 45 minutes or until done (test with fork).

title: fudge-y brownies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Beat in syrup.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat in flour gradually.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased 15 x 20 or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Frost with Chocolate Chip Frosting.

title: katie's casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan or glass dish at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: cheesy potatoes(microwave)
directions: Slice potatoes with peelings left on to desired thickness. Put in microwave bowl and cover with water.
Cook on High temperature until tender.
Drain well.
Cook bacon until crisp. Layer potatoes, sliced cheese and bacon pieces and small pats of butter.
Keep layering until all potatoes are used.
Heat in microwave on High until cheese and butter are melted.

title: peanut butter oatmeal crunchies
directions: Beat peanut butter, sugar and margarine until light.
Add water, eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, oatmeal and soda and mix well.
Shape dough into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place on ungreased baking sheet and flatten with glass or fork and bake at 350° for 12 to 14 minutes.

title: chocolate peanut butter balls
directions: In saucepan, melt peanut butter and butter.
In a large bowl, combine powdered sugar and cereal.
Pour peanut butter mixture over cereal mixture.
Blend together with hands.
Form into balls and chill until firm.
Melt chocolate chips and 1 small birthday candle (wax) together.
Dip peanut butter into coating and then place on wax paper lined baking sheet.
Cool and serve.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into milk jugs and freeze.
Unthaw 30 minutes before serving to make slushy.
Add food color for desired color.

title: no-guilt chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees.
In a 9 inch pie plate mix soup, vegetable and chicken.
Mix milk, egg and baking mix together and pour over chicken mixture.
Bake 30 minute or until golden. Serves 4.

title: strawberry cake and icing
directions: Mix ingredients using 3/4 cup strawberries and beat well. Bake at 350° for almost 1 hour in a greased and floured Bundt pan.

title: cherry coconut cake
directions: Mix cherry pie filling and crushed pineapple together (I add 1 teaspoon almond extract to mixture).
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over cherry and pineapple mixture. Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Sprinkle coconut over butter.
Top with pecans.
Cover with foil first 1/2 hour (loosely).
Remove foil for last 1/2 hour to permit browning.
Can be served warm or cold.
Very simple.

title: roast chicken with vegetables
directions: Wash chicken and pat dry. Cut along one side of breast or backbone to butterfly.
Set chicken, cut side up, in a 9-inch square pan. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Lift chicken out of pan. Arrange potatoes and carrots in pan.
Set chicken, cut side down, on top of vegetables. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Bake at 400° for about 1 hour or until chicken is done. Keep checking on vegetables.
About 20 minutes before it is done, dribble with honey.
Can be done without the vegetables.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and water.
Place over medium heat and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Add cranberries and cook slowly, without stirring, until all the skins pop open (about 5 minutes). Soften gelatine in 1/4 cup cold water; dissolve in hot cranberry mixture.
Add lemon juice and let cool. Let congeal in refrigerator.
When cooled, add celery and nuts.
Transfer to mold.

title: speedy stroganoff with noodles
directions: Brown meat strips in hot fat in skillet.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until onion is just tender.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Pour over meat and heat through.
Don't boil, it separates the sour cream.
Cook 6 ounces noodles; toss with butter and poppy seeds.
Serve sauce over noodles.

title: wassail
directions: Boil sugar and water 10 minutes with seasonings in bag.
Let stand 1 hour.
Strain or take out bag of seasonings.
When ready to serve, add remainder of ingredients.
Heat to boiling to serve. Serve hot.
Serves 25.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together except tomato sauce.
Put in loaf pan and cook 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
When 1/2 done, pour on tomato sauce.

title: meat loaf
directions: Purpose of bread is to soak up meat "fat" as meat loaf cooks. Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
About 20 minutes before it is done, spread ketchup on top and finish cooking.

title: zucchini pie
directions: In a bowl, mix zucchini, onions and parsley.
In another bowl, add Bisquick, grated cheese, parsley, pepper, oil and eggs.
Mix everything together and put into greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 40 minutes.

title: spinach quiche(lo-fat, low-cholesterol)
directions: Combine all ingredients except onions and pour into pie crust. Sprinkle onions
on top.
Bake 10 minutes at 450° then 30 minutes at 325°.
Serves 6.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Salt and pepper pork chops; brown in oil.
Remove and set aside.
Put rice into drippings in frying pan and brown, stirring constantly.
In casserole, place browned rice and remaining ingredients.
Put pork chops on top of rice.
Cover and cook 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Make a hollow in center of flour and pour in 1 cup buttermilk. Mix well, then add 1/2 cup buttermilk.
Knead the dough lightly on a floured board until smooth and shape into a round loaf. Place on greased cookie sheet.
With a knife, cut a cross design on the top of the loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fall harvest rice
directions: Cook sausage and drain well.
Combine rice with all ingredients.
Bake in 2-quart baking dish at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: sausage, potato and kale soup
directions: Put oil in a 4-quart Dutch oven over medium-high heat.
When oil is hot, add onion and carrot.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes until onion is tender, stirring once or twice.
Add broth, potatoes and garlic.
Bring to a boil, cover and reduce heat to low.
Simmer 30 to 35 minutes until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: mandarin orange gelatin salad
directions: Prepare the gelatin according to the package directions and let set.
Mix the whipped topping and cream cheese with an electric mixer.
Add the gelatin and the orange slices and mix again.
Return to the refrigerator and let set again.

title: lime pineapple salad
directions: Drain pineapple. Heat pineapple until hot.
Add sugar and salt.
Remove from heat and add Jell-O; stir well.
Then blend in cream cheese.
Refrigerate for one hour and then fold in Dream Whip.
Put in mold. Makes 12 servings.

title: honey and apple pork chops
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well. Set aside 1 cup for basting, in refrigerator. Add chops. Cover. Marinate overnight in refrigerator, turning occasionally. Grill chops, basting frequently (40 to 50 minutes).

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind the peppers and onions with medium blade of chopper. Cover with boiling water. Let stand 10 minutes. Drain until quite dry. Add vinegar, sugar, salt and celery seed. Boil 15 minutes. Place in containers of your choice.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Dip each tortilla in hot oil to soften. Place tortillas on plate.
Drain oil from skillet; brown beef in same skillet.
Add salt, chili powder and flour.
Mix until blended.
Add water and let thicken.

title: easy penuche icing
directions: Melt butter or oleo in saucepan.
Add brown sugar; boil and stir
over	low heat 2 minutes.
Add salt and milk.
Bring to boil,
stirring
constantly.
Cool to lukewarm, 120°.
Add vanilla.
(Can
be	cooked in microwave using glass instead of saucepan.)

title: frozen canned peaches
directions: Mix and cook slowly in large cooker until thick. Cool completely. Freeze in freezer containers.
Taste is like old fashioned dried peaches.

title: wesa's chili
directions: Brown together pepper, onion, garlic and ground beef.
Add beans and tomatoes (1/2 cup water if needed) and chili powder. Cook slowly at 325°, about 1 1/2 hours.
If wanted, add 1 cup macaroni (cooked) about 30 minutes before done.

title: 1015 onion and zucchini bake
directions: Saute onion and zucchini in margarine until tender.
Place in shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Combine eggs, milk, salt, pepper, dry mustard and half of cheese.
Pour over vegetables. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: quick deviled eggs
directions: Hard-boil as many eggs as you need.
Cool eggs in cold water. Peel and cut in halves.
Place all yolks in a bowl and mash until smooth. Add to the yolks the mustard, salt and pepper to taste and Thousand Island dressing; mix well.
The mixture should be spooned back into the white of egg halves and garnished with a little paprika.

title: scratch buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add remaining wet ingredients.
After mixing, let batter sit for 15 minutes.
Cook over medium heat in greased pan.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Remove skin, dry chicken.
Squeeze 2 lemons over and put aside 2 to 3 hours.
Combine flour and paprika and coat chicken.
Saute chicken until brown.
Mix lemon peel, sugar, salt, pepper and sprinkle on chicken.
Add broth.
Cook, covered, 25 minutes on top of stove.
Add water as needed.
Slice lemon and arrange on top of chicken.
Cook 10 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar, cream, margarine and salt over medium heat until soft ball forms in cold water.
Remove from heat and stir in vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat at medium speed until fudge starts to harden.
Pour into buttered pan.
Mark and cool.

title: mom's salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a cruet and shake well.

title: quick and easy pickles
directions: Mix vinegar, salt, sugar and dry mustard.
Pack small, whole cucumbers in jars and pour mixture over them.
No need to boil the mixture.

title: pave
directions: Mix Eagle
Brand
milk	and
egg
yolks.
Cook about 10 minutes or	until thick.
Pour into a Pyrex dish and let stand until cool.
Cut
peaches
on top of mixture.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold	in sour cream.	Add a little sugar, if you prefer it sweeter.	Spread on top of peaches.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. Combine oil, eggs, sugar, zucchini and vanilla in mixing bowl; blend well. Stir in flour, soda, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Do not beat. Stir in nuts. Spoon batter into 2 well-greased loaf pans and bake for 1 1/2 hours.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix all ingredients
and
pour into 2 baked pie shells. Refrigerate.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Layer cut zucchini, sliced onion and tomatoes.
Sprinkle with grated Parmesan cheese.
Add Muenster cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat.
Top with Italian style bread crumbs and add a few pats of butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: vicki's popcorn cake
directions: Mix M&M's, peanuts and popcorn together. Melt butter with oil and marshmallows in a large boiler until smooth. Pour over popcorn mixture. Mix well and press into a well-greased tube pan. Turn out onto plate and slice.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach; drain.
Press between paper towels to remove moisture.
Mix with other ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight. Good with Wheat Thins.

title: pecan pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into 2 pie shells.
Cook at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: ham and cheese bread
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain and cool. Roll each loaf of dough into a 15 x 10-inch rectangle.
Place one in a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch baking pan.
Sprinkle with broccoli, cheese and ham to within 1/2 inch of edges.
Place second triangle on top; seal edges.
Brush top with butter; sprinkle with seed. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until golden brown.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add flour and eggs; beat well.
Stir in milk, vanilla and nutmeg.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool on wire rack completely.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Let margarine warm to room temperature.
Mix flour, sugar and margarine with electric mixer.
Add milk, eggs and vanilla, mixing well after each ingredient.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch pie pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Pour 1/4 cup of the corn oil into baking dish and warm in preheated 450° oven.
Mix remaining ingredients, including the remaining 1/4 cup corn oil.
Pour mixture into heated baking dish. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 400° until brown, approximately 40 minutes.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt together.
Add to peaches and cook until thickened.

title: scratch recipe for lipton onion soup
directions: Mix above ingredients.
Store in airtight container or Ziploc bag.
Mix with 4 cups water for soup.
Mix with 2 cups sour cream for chip dip.
Rub on roast before baking for great gravy base.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Mix together and chill.

title: turkey gumbo
directions: Cook onions in fat until it's tender, but not brown.
Add broth, tomatoes, okra, turkey, parsley and paprika.
Heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Taste for seasonings.
Add cooked rice.
Heat and serve.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat hard.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Then add bananas and chopped nuts.
Bake in 10-inch
or 5-inch loaf pan, well-greased.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Loaf will have a tendency to crack on top.
Cool on rack. Wrap in foil to keep moist.

title: refrigerator spice cookies
directions: In small saucepan over medium heat, combine honey, butter and molasses.
Bring to boil.
Let cool 3 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients in bowl.
Stir in honey mixture thoroughly.
Divide dough into four plastic wrapped logs and refrigerate for 2 to 3 hours.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly coat sheet with cooking spray.
Roll logs into thin dough and cut into shapes.
Then bake 5 minutes or until firm.

title: baked beans
directions: Drain butter, lima and kidney beans and chickpeas.
Cook bacon until crisp, crumble.
Remove bacon from pan and cook onion and garlic in drippings.
Mix all ingredients in 2 1/2-quart bean pot. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cramer's catfish chowder
directions: Fillet catfish.
Put meat into large pot.
Add three cups of water, salt and pepper.
Bring to boil.
Let simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut potatoes into small chunks, then boil until soft. Drain water from potatoes.
Add catfish.
Cook bacon in thick skillet.
When fat is out of bacon, dispose of bacon.
Cut onions into small chunks and cook with bacon fat until brown.
Strain fat from onions and add onions to catfish.
Add cream of celery and 3 cups of milk to catfish.
Let simmer for 30 minutes, often stirring until catfish is down to small chunks.
Feeds up to 6 people.

title: nachos casserole
directions: Combine taco sauce and chilies.
Set aside.
In frypan, cook meat and onions until meat is browned.
Drain.
Add cumin, beans, 1 cup cheese and half of taco sauce mixture.

title: turkey corn soup
directions: Pick meat off of carcass.
Make stock with carcass; boil for 30 minutes.
Add turkey.
Add bouillon cubes; dissolve.
Add 1 can of corn.
Add noodles; boil until tender.

title: meatballs on crisp noodles
directions: Mix ground beef, soy sauce and ginger.
Shape by rounded tablespoonfuls into balls.
Cook and stir meatballs in a 10-inch skillet over medium heat until brown, about 15 minutes; drain.

title: cold corn salsa
directions: Mix together corn, onion, pepper, mint and tomatoes.
Blend in oil, lemon/lime juice and cumin.
Chill overnight.
Stir occasionally.
Add chopped jalapenos for a real Mexican flavor. Fantastic with grilled marinated chicken.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together in blender.
Pour into greased and floured 9-inch pie plate.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a 13 x 9-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: party ham sandwiches
directions: Saute onion,
poppy seed and mustard in margarine.
Cut dinner rolls in half horizontally.
Put onion spread on bottom of	rolls. Layer
Swiss cheese and ham.
Sprinkle over bottom of rolls.
Put tops on, cover with foil and warm in 350° oven until cheese is melted (10 to 15 minutes).

title: sausage cornbread
directions: Brown sausage and onion in medium skillet.
Drain.
Combine eggs, cornmeal, corn, milk and oil in a bowl.
Pour 1/2 of cornmeal mixture into a greased 2-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with sausage mixture and cheese.
Pour remaining cornmeal mixture over top.
Bake at 425° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: low-fat pizza
directions: Cover pizza crust with Hunt's Italian spaghetti sauce.
Brown the first 4 ingredients, then add tomatoes.
Add thyme, garlic powder, lemon pepper and salt; mix well.
Spray pizza pan with Pam.
Spread pizza mixture on crust; cook 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.

title: crumb-topped coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon and salt in bowl.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Add 1 1/2 cups of cereal.
Measure 1/3 cup of the mixture; set aside.
Add milk and egg to remaining flour mixture; blend thoroughly.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan.
Mix measured crumb mixture with remaining cereal and sprinkle on batter.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean. Sprinkle with sugar if desired.

title: fresh greens(turnip, mustard, kale)
directions: First you remove stalks from the leaves.
Then you wash your greens until they are grit free.
Cut them up and put in Dutch oven with seasonings and meat.
Cover with water.
Cook until meat is done and by that time, the greens will be done.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350 degrees until done.

title: crunchy baked bananas
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Peel and half banana.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle marshmallows, brown sugar and cornflakes; drizzle melted butter over the top.
Bake 12 minutes or until tender.

title: cornbread
directions: In
a medium bowl, combine cornmeal, flour, sugar, salt and baking powder.
Make a well in center; add egg and beat as you gradually
add milk.
Heat a large cast-iron skillet with the bacon
grease until grease is hot.
Stir cornmeal mixture good and
pour in skillet and bake in preheated 400° oven for 20
to 25 minutes.
Invert cornbread onto serving plate.
Cut in pie-shape slices and serve.

title: "that" chicken
directions: Layer chicken on rice in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Combine dressing, cranberry sauce and onion soup mix and heat in saucepan. Bring to boil and let simmer 2 or 3 minutes.
Pour over chicken. Cover dish and cook until heated through, about 30 minutes.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla well.
Add egg; mix well. Spread onto bottom of pastry shell.
Mix remaining ingredients well.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool.
Brush with maple syrup and garnish with nuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package.
Drain broccoli; add cheese, mayonnaise, onions, eggs and soup mix.
Roll Ritz crackers.
Add melted butter.
Place in ovenproof dish and cover with Ritz cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350°.

title: sugar snap peas in toasted sesame seed vinaigrette *
directions: In a large saucepan of boiling salted water, cook sugar snaps until crisp-tender, about 30 seconds.
Drain; rinse under cold running water and drain well.
In a dry heavy skillet, toast the sesame seed over moderate heat, stirring until nuts brown, about 3 minutes.
Pour onto plate to cool.

title: aunt june's broccoli salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Add dressing just before serving.
